00:14:32.918 --> 00:14:37.557
TALIESIN: That's not bad.

00:14:37.557 --> 00:14:39.139
SAM: 33.

00:14:39.139 --> 00:14:40.922
TALIESIN: 21.

00:14:40.922 --> 00:14:41.992
MARISHA: 17.

00:14:41.992 --> 00:14:43.003
LIAM: 18.

00:14:43.003 --> 00:14:44.009
LAURA: 17.

00:14:44.009 --> 00:14:45.171
MATT: Pike?

00:14:45.171 --> 00:14:46.456
ASHLEY: 22.

00:14:46.456 --> 00:14:47.844
TRAVIS: Eight.

00:14:47.844 --> 00:14:50.077
LIAM: Too big.

00:14:50.077 --> 00:14:52.292
TRAVIS: I'm sorry.

00:14:52.292 --> 00:15:00.154
MATT: As you guys make your way further down one
of the, not major thoroughfares, but one of the

00:15:00.154 --> 00:15:06.099
general streets that snakes around towards the
central area of the city, some of you gently

00:15:06.099 --> 00:15:13.004
moaning and gurgling as you walk, behind you, you have
Grog Frankensteining his way down the street.

00:15:13.004 --> 00:15:25.471
(laughing)

00:15:25.471 --> 00:15:27.188
TRAVIS: Oh man.

00:15:27.188 --> 00:15:34.168
MATT: The sound of your rendition, that song. As
you're walking, a shadow seems to cross, a large

00:15:34.168 --> 00:15:40.662
hulking shadow crosses past one of the roads and
turns and begins walking your direction. And you

00:15:40.662 --> 00:15:47.858
see ahead what looks to be about a ten foot tall,
thick, burly figure of brownish red flesh, torn,

00:15:47.858 --> 00:15:57.779
and chains and hooks hanging from it. It looks to
be almost like an amalgam of large hobgoblin body

00:15:57.779 --> 00:16:02.531
parts that have been sewn and stitched together
with spikes and iron plates, jutting through,

00:16:02.531 --> 00:16:07.191
keeping it together at the seams. Where there
would be a face, you see instead a giant metal

00:16:07.191 --> 00:16:12.100
mass that looks like a cage of some kind, and
behind it these two glowing beads of yellow eyes

00:16:12.100 --> 00:16:17.282
poking through, and you watch as it just walks in
a straight line (impacts).

00:16:17.282 --> 00:16:18.694
LAURA: Coming right for us?

00:16:18.694 --> 00:16:21.658
MATT: Walking in your direction. Its arms are
curled in front of it like a gorilla, its fingers

00:16:21.658 --> 00:16:23.568
dragging in the dust below it.

00:16:23.568 --> 00:16:27.115
LIAM: Does it look like it's just happening in our
direction, or is it coming toward us?

00:16:27.115 --> 00:16:29.600
MATT: It's hard to tell. It's about 60 feet up.

00:16:29.600 --> 00:16:31.862
LAURA: Is there a road we can turn directions?

00:16:31.862 --> 00:16:36.209
TALIESIN: Is there a nonchalant way of maintaining
direction but getting out of its way?

00:16:36.209 --> 00:16:41.663
MATT: There would be enough space to give about a
ten foot berth to it as you put your back against

00:16:41.663 --> 00:16:43.975
the side of one of the nearest buildings and let
it pass.

00:16:43.975 --> 00:16:46.246
MARISHA: Like parting for the queen at the Ren
Faire?

00:16:46.246 --> 00:16:47.445
MATT: A little bit, yeah.

00:16:47.445 --> 00:16:49.433
LIAM: Or Taliesin Jaffe.

00:16:49.433 --> 00:16:52.550
MARISHA: Or Taliesin Jaffe at any party.

00:16:52.550 --> 00:16:54.851
ASHLEY: I move to the side and put my head down.

00:16:54.851 --> 00:16:57.103
SAM: What's our ploy if this thing tries to kill
us?

00:16:57.103 --> 00:16:58.117
LAURA: Kill it.

00:16:58.117 --> 00:16:59.315
SAM: Okay.

00:16:59.315 --> 00:17:00.676
TRAVIS: Same old same old.

00:17:00.676 --> 00:17:11.098
MATT: (heavy footsteps) You guys all make your way
to the side and you watch. It's autonomous, it's

00:17:11.098 --> 00:17:18.470
not being brought along with anybody. It's running
a path down the road. You all move off to the

00:17:18.470 --> 00:17:26.824
side, and as you maneuver to the side of it, it
gets close to the censer you're carrying, and it

00:17:26.824 --> 00:17:33.403
(groaning) puts its fingers out of the way,
actually crushing some of the stonework on one of

00:17:33.403 --> 00:17:38.674
the nearby buildings to pull itself aside, trying
to avoid the billowing of the smoke from the

00:17:38.674 --> 00:17:49.212
censer. It gives a dull, deep resonant (huff) in
your direction as it passes, and then eventually

00:17:49.212 --> 00:17:54.747
passes by the cluster of you that have all moved
to the side, after its head shifts and scans back

00:17:54.747 --> 00:17:59.015
in the path that it's walking and it moves past
you, following the direction you just came from.

00:17:59.015 --> 00:18:02.114
TALIESIN: Way to be Fonzies.

00:18:02.114 --> 00:18:04.681
LAURA: Nice. Very nice. So cool.

00:18:04.681 --> 00:18:06.970
SAM: Wow. This thing works.

00:18:06.970 --> 00:18:08.721
TALIESIN: Lot of Fonzies. Smells terrible.

00:18:08.721 --> 00:18:18.635
MATT: You continue further into the city. You
still hear the distant, low shrieks of the gloom

00:18:18.635 --> 00:18:28.361
stalkers (shriek) overhead, swooping past in
clusters, circling around. Occasionally you watch

00:18:28.361 --> 00:18:34.214
one or two swoop down and land on a distant
rooftop, and you hear the crunching of heavy stone

00:18:34.214 --> 00:18:40.905
and whatever materials were still remaining on the
roof of that structure as it lands and surveys a

00:18:40.905 --> 00:18:45.178
bit, and then (whoosh) takes off and joins the
rest of its kin.

00:18:45.178 --> 00:18:52.057
TALIESIN: Do any of the buildings look remarkable
or interesting? I'm trying to keep an eye out for

00:18:52.057 --> 00:18:58.691
any building that may have anything inside it of
vague importance. Either the building itself is

00:18:58.691 --> 00:19:04.069
slightly more interesting, or it looks like maybe
someone has boarded something up to try and

00:19:04.069 --> 00:19:11.294
maintain some kind of vigil against the darkness?
I'm not entirely sure. Out of the ordinary.

00:19:11.294 --> 00:19:13.291
MATT: Okay. Make an investigation check.

00:19:13.291 --> 00:19:23.463
TALIESIN: I knew you were going to say that. I'm
not good at this. Nope. Nope, nope. That's a four.

00:19:23.463 --> 00:19:25.413
That's a natural one.

00:19:25.413 --> 00:19:31.978
MATT: A lot of these buildings are hard to tell
apart when they're all just in this state of

00:19:31.978 --> 00:19:33.295
disrepair and destruction.

00:19:33.295 --> 00:19:34.926
TALIESIN: Some of them have doors.

00:19:34.926 --> 00:19:37.344
MATT: Some of them do. Some of them have windows,
kind of.

00:19:37.344 --> 00:19:39.511
TALIESIN: Holes where windows might be.

00:19:39.511 --> 00:19:45.823
MATT: Possibly. Some, you can't tell if it's a
hole, or a window. Or a door?

00:19:45.823 --> 00:19:47.915
As you press forward.

00:19:47.915 --> 00:19:49.993
TALIESIN: I felt Orthax take over again.

00:19:49.993 --> 00:19:55.980
LIAM: So this is Osgiliath, right? It's wrecked
ruin, no complete buildings, or are any of them?

00:19:55.980 --> 00:20:00.104
MATT: You see some further in. The exterior
appears to have been the most heavily sacked.

00:20:00.104 --> 00:20:08.652
There's been little intent to reconstruct from
this point. Like I said, you're still probably a

00:20:08.652 --> 00:20:16.300
good mile and a half out from the center of the
city, and as you walk further in, you can see more

00:20:16.300 --> 00:20:22.729
clusters of skeletons traveling in groups of 12 to
15, somewhat erratically. You've seen some

00:20:22.729 --> 00:20:27.635
creatures that seem to walk with an intent
pattern, like they have some sort of a sentinel

00:20:27.635 --> 00:20:32.793
path that they follow to keep watch on the
perimeter or the roads of the city. The skeletons

00:20:32.793 --> 00:20:39.009
that wander, the undead that you see clattering
about across the dusty, cracked grounds between

00:20:39.009 --> 00:20:47.168
the buildings, are erratic, uncontrolled. Mostly
it seems to be less intentionally created undead,

00:20:47.168 --> 00:20:53.907
and more just risen by the nature of the plane you
walk, and haven't bothered anyone yet, or at least

00:20:53.907 --> 00:21:01.366
those who live here. As you begin walking forward,
you watch as a cluster of them spills into this T

00:21:01.366 --> 00:21:04.872
intersection a little ways up, a few of them
falling and tumbling and getting back up

00:21:04.872 --> 00:21:10.184
(cracking). As they cluster together, some of them
bang into each other. You hear the clattering of

00:21:10.184 --> 00:21:15.748
metal from the bits of armor that still cling to
their long-rotted forms. Broken bones, some of

00:21:15.748 --> 00:21:20.667
them are missing arms, or sections of a skull is
exposed and cracked open on the side, where you

00:21:20.667 --> 00:21:25.937
can see what looks to be some sort of long-dried
and rotted away gray matter was left to slowly

00:21:25.937 --> 00:21:36.583
collapse like a flan in a cupboard. As you begin
to approach that area, they separate a bit and

00:21:36.583 --> 00:21:41.957
scatter to fill, almost diffusing in the center of
this intersection, and then they contract, almost

00:21:41.957 --> 00:21:46.641
like there's a strange hive mind magic that seems
to draw them back together. They're just moving in

00:21:46.641 --> 00:21:53.303
these autonomous clusters of chaos. You see on
them still, similar to the ones you noticed

00:21:53.303 --> 00:21:57.721
earlier, some of the armor that they're wearing
appears to be reminiscent to the armor that the

00:21:57.721 --> 00:22:04.101
black guard that you battled at the ziggurat
earlier had, or similar dark metal, and others

00:22:04.101 --> 00:22:12.502
have long-destroyed, ruined, scraped and scarred
bits of silver and gold armor that are emblazoned

00:22:12.502 --> 00:22:17.663
with long-ruined and defaced symbols of the Dawn
Father, Pelor.

00:22:17.663 --> 00:22:21.157
LAURA: Does it seem like both of those factions
are still--

00:22:21.157 --> 00:22:22.980
are they clustered in the same groups?

00:22:23.298 --> 00:22:29.695
MATT: They are. And you get the sense that
whatever battle took place here long ago was

00:22:29.695 --> 00:22:35.667
probably between these two factions, and those
that were lost in that fray have been risen over

00:22:35.667 --> 00:22:38.394
time and wander aimlessly through the streets.

00:22:38.394 --> 00:22:40.192
TALIESIN: Free range undead.

00:22:40.192 --> 00:22:47.866
LIAM: We've seen long-dead people. This is fucking
creepy in the upside-down.

00:22:47.866 --> 00:22:49.750
(airplane noise)
SAM: What's going on?

00:22:49.750 --> 00:22:56.355
MATT: I called the airport to try and coordinate
this time with you guys. Cost me 17,000 dollars

00:22:56.355 --> 00:23:00.435
for that one five-second bit, so enjoy it, guys.

00:23:00.435 --> 00:23:02.004
LIAM: Worth it.

00:23:02.004 --> 00:23:03.521
MATT: Totally worth it.

00:23:03.521 --> 00:23:09.711
LIAM: These bodies, compared to the ex-champion of
the Raven Queen, do these bodies seem even older?

00:23:09.711 --> 00:23:14.092
More decayed? Do we have any sense for how old
these fuckers are?

00:23:14.092 --> 00:23:17.470
MATT: You would have to get up close and that
would be a medicine check. Would you want to try

00:23:17.470 --> 00:23:22.468
and make your way close enough to one of these
bodies to inspect it enough?

00:23:22.468 --> 00:23:24.044
LIAM: How far off are they?

00:23:24.044 --> 00:23:27.944
MATT: If you guys continue moving forward, you'll
be at that intersection in about 30 seconds.

00:23:27.944 --> 00:23:29.742
LIAM: I'm not going to go. I'll wait.

00:23:29.742 --> 00:23:32.654
ASHLEY: I could go up close with somebody and do a
medicine check.

00:23:32.654 --> 00:23:36.866
LAURA: Keep up near the thing. Everybody get close
to the censer.

00:23:36.866 --> 00:23:39.265
TALIESIN: I'll guide us towards something.

00:23:39.265 --> 00:23:42.852
LIAM: Yeah, no one poking out ahead for this.

00:23:42.852 --> 00:23:44.423
LAURA: Hopefully they'll be affected by the
censer.

00:23:44.423 --> 00:23:45.922
TRAVIS: Let's just stop by.

00:23:45.922 --> 00:23:50.279
MATT: So who's moving forward?

00:23:50.279 --> 00:23:54.914
LAURA: The whole group. So we can all be with the
wispy smoke.

00:23:54.914 --> 00:23:59.570
MATT: Okay. So you guys make your way towards this
intersection.

00:23:59.570 --> 00:24:02.374
LAURA: We're normal people in robes.

00:24:02.374 --> 00:24:10.611
MATT: You also watch as you begin to walk further
in that elements of the ground are growing more

00:24:10.611 --> 00:24:17.088
jagged and craggy. You can see bits of stone and
earth are jutting out in large stone spikes,

00:24:17.088 --> 00:24:24.500
either through some upheaval or elements of the
tumultuous landscape long ago that just caused

00:24:24.500 --> 00:24:33.502
elements of rock to spike outward up five, ten
feet in sections. You watch as you grow close to

00:24:33.502 --> 00:24:41.977
this intersection, about half of the group all at
once (groan) turns and looks in your direction and

00:24:41.977 --> 00:24:45.178
begin to (footsteps).

00:24:45.178 --> 00:24:47.373
LAURA: Can I just waft some of the smoke towards
them?

00:24:47.373 --> 00:24:51.693
MATT: Shamble in your direction. The rest of the
group noticing-- You begin blowing the censer

00:24:51.693 --> 00:25:03.786
smoke that way. You watch as three of the closest
skeletons make their way into the fume and seem to

00:25:03.786 --> 00:25:06.546
vaguely lose interest for a brief moment.

00:25:06.546 --> 00:25:10.010
ASHLEY: Since we're close, can I do a medicine
check? Are we close enough to?

00:25:10.010 --> 00:25:12.734
MATT: Yes, but with disadvantage because of the
smoke.

00:25:12.734 --> 00:25:15.171
ASHLEY: Oh, shit. Okay.

00:25:15.171 --> 00:25:16.909
LAURA: You got this, Pike.

00:25:16.909 --> 00:25:20.589
TALIESIN: Roll like it's a stealth roll.

00:25:20.589 --> 00:25:28.524
ASHLEY: 13?

00:25:28.603 --> 00:25:34.890
MATT: With the brief glances you have, it's hard
to really tell. Plus, you're not too familiar with

00:25:34.890 --> 00:25:43.271
the overall weather of the Shadowfell. You don't
know if there's enough weather to manifest as

00:25:43.271 --> 00:25:52.029
general decay, or if they've been beaten by the
ravages of time, if it rains here or not. It's

00:25:52.029 --> 00:25:56.187
hard to tell. You gather it probably doesn't rain
often. They're definitely hundreds of years old.

00:25:56.187 --> 00:26:00.068
That's the most you can really tell. They aren't
fresh dead. These are long dead.

00:26:00.068 --> 00:26:03.587
LIAM: I'm feeling Foresighty. Can I creep up
behind and do the same?

00:26:03.587 --> 00:26:12.454
MATT: I will say you can do that, however you
still have disadvantage, because she's already

00:26:12.454 --> 00:26:16.797
taken the roll and you're supplementing her roll
in a very short period of time.

00:26:16.797 --> 00:26:19.633
LIAM: Would that be an even roll, then, since I
have advantage on everything?

00:26:19.633 --> 00:26:23.051
MATT: You have advantage on everything. I'm giving
you a chance to do this when normally you would

00:26:23.051 --> 00:26:27.004
have none, so the Foresight's allowing you to have
a roll with disadvantage. Go for it.

00:26:27.004 --> 00:26:31.012
LIAM: Oh, that's going to fail. Ooh! 18.

00:26:31.012 --> 00:26:43.084
MATT: Or not. Getting a glance at the one nearest
to you, the bodies seem to be fairly well

00:26:43.084 --> 00:26:46.631
preserved for as long as they've been here, so you
get the sense that there isn't a lot of heavy

00:26:46.631 --> 00:26:52.228
weather here at all. And given that fact, the
decay that's there, it is reminiscent, maybe not

00:26:52.228 --> 00:26:59.255
quite as old as the corpse of Purvon when you
discovered the tomb originally, but comparatively

00:26:59.255 --> 00:27:02.187
ancient. At least over 500 years.

00:27:02.187 --> 00:27:07.570
TRAVIS: Old Purvon.

00:27:07.570 --> 00:27:09.724
MATT: Good old Purvon.

00:27:09.724 --> 00:27:12.343
LAURA: These skeletons are almost as old as you,
Scanlan.

00:27:12.343 --> 00:27:15.066
SAM: Good one.

00:27:15.066 --> 00:27:27.107
MATT: As you continue to walk forward, and the
skeletons part around the cloud of the censer, you

00:27:27.107 --> 00:27:34.424
push deeper into the city, and they coalesce
behind you and follow. They're keeping a perimeter

00:27:34.424 --> 00:27:42.050
cluster now. They're still being held at bay by
the wafting of this thick blackish-green smoke

00:27:42.050 --> 00:27:47.173
that's billowing off of it, but they're staying
just outside of it and slowly shambling at your

00:27:47.173 --> 00:27:49.078
speed, waiting for an opening.

00:27:49.078 --> 00:27:54.973
LAURA: I have an idea. What if, right when we get
close to the tower, all of these trailing

00:27:54.973 --> 00:28:00.107
skeletons that we have on us, you just Turn
Undead? And then you control them all?

00:28:00.107 --> 00:28:03.399
SAM: You can do that?

00:28:03.399 --> 00:28:05.798
MATT: Destroy them, yeah.

00:28:05.798 --> 00:28:08.123
LAURA: Oh, you can't control them? I thought you
could.

00:28:08.123 --> 00:28:09.474
ASHLEY: I could turn them.

00:28:09.474 --> 00:28:11.122
MATT: Turn them means they just run away
screaming.

00:28:11.122 --> 00:28:12.578
ASHLEY: I can make them run away.

00:28:12.578 --> 00:28:18.134
MATT: You're at a level where you can just make
them explode if they roll low. Up to you.

00:28:18.134 --> 00:28:20.573
TRAVIS: We've got a little nuke in our pocket.

00:28:20.573 --> 00:28:25.731
ASHLEY: I want us to be quiet. I don't want to
make a big spectacle. Because I can make them go

00:28:25.731 --> 00:28:28.101
boom boom, but let's just wait.

00:28:28.101 --> 00:28:29.770
LAURA: She can make them poop.

00:28:29.770 --> 00:28:35.205
TALIESIN: And they don't even have bowels.

00:28:35.205 --> 00:28:40.020
TRAVIS: Is anything stalking us from above while
we're moving?

00:28:40.020 --> 00:28:42.128
MATT: How astute of you, I was just about to get
to that.

00:28:42.128 --> 00:28:45.227
TRAVIS: Did you hear that? Astute.

00:28:45.227 --> 00:28:47.640
SAM: You put the ass in astute.

00:28:47.640 --> 00:28:50.748
LAURA: Hey, did you guys know that Travis is the
smartest guy at the table?

00:28:50.748 --> 00:28:54.411
MARISHA: I could tell by his Cheers shirt.

00:28:54.411 --> 00:29:04.655
(laughing)

00:29:04.655 --> 00:29:11.903
MATT: So. In the billowing smoke that's coming
around, Grog, because you brought it up, as well

00:29:11.903 --> 00:29:16.699
as the twins who have relatively high passive
perceptions, and Keyleth as well, actually, you

00:29:16.699 --> 00:29:22.136
glance up and notice that the erratic patterns
that a lot of the gloom stalkers take in the sky,

00:29:22.136 --> 00:29:28.442
there's two that seem to be circling, and
circling.

00:29:28.442 --> 00:29:30.473
ASHLEY: I don't like it, I don't like it.

00:29:30.473 --> 00:29:37.195
MATT: One of them (shrieks), and you watch as it
goes into a dive in your direction.

00:29:37.195 --> 00:29:38.999
SAM: Oh, God! In our direction?

00:29:38.999 --> 00:29:40.915
LAURA: Is there a building we can duck into?

00:29:40.915 --> 00:29:42.714
MATT: Make a quick perception check.

00:29:42.714 --> 00:29:44.318
SAM: But quick!

00:29:44.318 --> 00:29:52.160
LAURA: 33.

00:29:52.160 --> 00:29:53.418
LIAM: 24.

00:29:53.418 --> 00:29:58.532
MATT: Okay. Both of you, really quick, you see in
two different directions, past the intersection on

00:29:58.532 --> 00:30:02.044
the right, and on the left, you see two buildings
that are mostly still intact. They've sustained

00:30:02.044 --> 00:30:06.240
some level of damage, but they still have two
solid floors, maybe a partial roof missing, but

00:30:06.240 --> 00:30:10.243
they appear to be structurally sound enough to at
least jump into. They both have doors that are

00:30:10.243 --> 00:30:12.279
partially ajar and a darkened interior.

00:30:12.279 --> 00:30:13.250
LAURA: And a roof.

00:30:13.250 --> 00:30:14.154
MATT: And a roof.

00:30:14.154 --> 00:30:15.389
LIAM: (grunting)

00:30:15.389 --> 00:30:18.540
LAURA: (grunting) Why am I? I can talk. Go in that
building.

00:30:18.540 --> 00:30:20.556
TRAVIS: Yeah, we go in there.

00:30:20.556 --> 00:30:23.440
LAURA: That way they can't dive bomb us, at
least.

00:30:23.440 --> 00:30:25.915
TALIESIN: I go in last. Censer.

00:30:25.915 --> 00:30:30.004
MATT: All right. So you guys all rush into the
building on the right or the left?

00:30:30.004 --> 00:30:33.290
TALIESIN: Yours.

00:30:33.290 --> 00:30:34.493
LAURA: The right.

00:30:34.493 --> 00:30:38.328
MATT: All right, so the one that Vex found. You
guys all rush into that building with Percival the

00:30:38.328 --> 00:30:40.043
last one in there. As you--

00:30:40.043 --> 00:30:41.805
LAURA: Weapons drawn in case there's something in
there.

00:30:41.805 --> 00:30:43.338
SAM: But also moving like zombies.

00:30:43.338 --> 00:30:53.970
