TALIESIN: Whatever the opposite of standards are,
I know we have them.

00:45:48.841 --> 00:45:51.986
MARISHA: Give some to Percy, anybody else want
some?

00:45:51.986 --> 00:45:57.752
LAURA: Yeah, yeah. I don't have any way to make
fire, but I'll take it.

00:45:57.752 --> 00:45:59.202
Definitely in my shirt now.

00:45:59.202 --> 00:46:06.773
MATT: As you guys are doing this, you hear the
(snarling), and you hear the (flapping wings).

00:46:06.773 --> 00:46:18.695
It's hunting from building to building. (impacts)
Closer. (flapping wings) (snarling) A little

00:46:18.695 --> 00:46:26.312
further away. (flapping wings)

00:46:26.312 --> 00:46:29.502
LAURA: It's gone? Did it fly away?

00:46:29.502 --> 00:46:31.424
MATT: Sounds like it, at least.

00:46:31.424 --> 00:46:36.717
LAURA: Should we leave, and go to another
building?

00:46:36.717 --> 00:46:38.037
SAM: Let's keep going.

00:46:38.037 --> 00:46:40.923
LIAM: Building to building toward the tower?

00:46:40.923 --> 00:46:44.063
LAURA: I feel like it's not really gone.

00:46:44.063 --> 00:46:47.375
LIAM: Well, we'll find out. Let's make a break for
it.

00:46:47.375 --> 00:46:55.271
MATT: Okay, who's going first? Okay. Vax, as you
dart along the side, glancing up in the air, you

00:46:55.271 --> 00:47:01.834
can still see. And it looks like there is some
communication, because where once there was maybe

00:47:01.834 --> 00:47:07.046
two, you can now see a lot of them have clustered
closer in your direction. There seems to be some

00:47:07.046 --> 00:47:08.683
sort of an overhead hunt.

00:47:08.683 --> 00:47:12.579
LAURA: Should I cast Pass Without a Trace on us
again? Are we running out of time on it?

00:47:12.579 --> 00:47:13.976
MATT: You're getting pretty close, yeah.

00:47:13.976 --> 00:47:15.885
LAURA: I'm going to cast it again, just so we
don't.

00:47:15.885 --> 00:47:18.726
MATT: Okay, so you cast Pass Without a Trace again.

00:47:18.726 --> 00:47:22.972
LIAM: And are we, Without a Trace and Dust of
Tracelessness? That's just a one time...

00:47:22.972 --> 00:47:25.569
LAURA: Dust of Tracelessness is just so they can't
track us.

00:47:25.569 --> 00:47:32.299
MATT: So the second thing you've gathered, these
creatures are not very intelligent, but they do

00:47:32.299 --> 00:47:39.818
have some sort of communication between them, and
there apparently is a rush on their end to search

00:47:39.818 --> 00:47:48.861
for whatever was recently spotted. So as you guys
make your way, following Vax's lead, down some of

00:47:48.861 --> 00:47:54.961
the alleyways, and begin slithering through the
back ways and the small side streets, avoiding

00:47:54.961 --> 00:47:58.326
your first attempt to walk straight through the
center of the town.

00:47:58.326 --> 00:48:02.668
LAURA: It's crazy how that didn't work, though. I
mean, because it was a really smart plan.

00:48:02.668 --> 00:48:09.734
MATT: It worked for a bit. Not every plan is going
to hold you to the very end. There was some

00:48:09.734 --> 00:48:19.412
cleverness to it. So you begin to move through
these buildings before-- It would be Keyleth, Vex

00:48:19.412 --> 00:48:28.491
and Vax. You guys come around one small alley and
it opens up into another main road, and this

00:48:28.491 --> 00:48:34.510
road's hard to avoid. It seems to be almost a
circular central road that marks the outer and

00:48:34.510 --> 00:48:43.397
inner rings of Thar Amphala. But you see there,
marking right across this road, a 15 foot tall

00:48:43.397 --> 00:48:50.711
wall that seems to lock in the inner cloister of
the town.

00:48:50.711 --> 00:48:53.000
MARISHA: How thick does it appear to be?

00:48:53.000 --> 00:48:55.817
MATT: Make a perception check.

00:48:55.817 --> 00:48:59.451
LAURA: Maybe we can go under it.

00:48:59.451 --> 00:49:06.315
MARISHA: Or through it. 17.

00:49:06.315 --> 00:49:11.900
MATT: It's hard to tell from this perspective. You
have to get a better glance. You have to find if

00:49:11.900 --> 00:49:19.626
there was a break in the wall anywhere. You do see
what looks to be some variation in texture a

00:49:19.626 --> 00:49:25.491
little ways to the right. It could be a gate, it
could be a door, it could be an opening, or it

00:49:25.491 --> 00:49:33.255
could be some change in its rather solid, not very
varied exterior.

00:49:33.255 --> 00:49:38.170
MARISHA: Go to the gate?

00:49:38.170 --> 00:49:39.819
SAM: Yeah.

00:49:39.819 --> 00:49:41.425
MARISHA: Okay.

00:49:41.425 --> 00:49:50.044
LIAM: Why don't the half-elves go real quick, just
to stay small and quiet. No clanking, no crushing.

00:49:50.044 --> 00:49:52.777
You take a look at the wall, and then we just call
everybody up.

00:49:52.777 --> 00:49:55.550
Just two seconds if it's the way to go.

00:49:55.550 --> 00:49:59.969
LAURA: Is it far away? It's like 15 feet from us
you said? Is it farther than that?

00:49:59.969 --> 00:50:02.172
MATT: Probably about 60 feet down to the right of
you guys.

00:50:02.172 --> 00:50:08.853
LIAM: So the change in the wall's about 60 feet,
but the wall from our hiding spot is

00:50:08.853 --> 00:50:10.300
how far away from us?

00:50:10.300 --> 00:50:16.820
MATT: Across the way it's about 30 feet from you.
it's only about 15 feet tall, it's not crazy big.

00:50:16.820 --> 00:50:25.197
MARISHA: I'll see if I can discern something here
a little bit better. You go. Go check it out.

00:50:25.197 --> 00:50:27.050
LAURA: Sure.

00:50:27.050 --> 00:50:32.602
MATT: So the two of you dart off to the side,
following Keyleth's impression of where she saw

00:50:32.602 --> 00:50:39.273
this shift, and as you make your way along the
edge, you glance over and you see two things. One,

00:50:39.273 --> 00:50:47.825
there does indeed appear to be a small, cut
doorway in the wall, maybe about six feet up,

00:50:47.825 --> 00:50:53.303
three feet wide, that's designed for a single file
passage of any creature that wishes to move

00:50:53.303 --> 00:50:59.355
through. It's open. There's no closed door there.
Above it, just above it, about eight feet up, you

00:50:59.355 --> 00:51:07.061
see what appears to be a deep cerulean blue
gemstone, about two feet across, that's embedded

00:51:07.061 --> 00:51:08.901
within the wall.

00:51:08.901 --> 00:51:11.012
LIAM: I think it's fine.

00:51:11.012 --> 00:51:12.612
SAM: Just go through the hole.

00:51:12.612 --> 00:51:14.164
LIAM: We're good. We found it.

00:51:14.164 --> 00:51:18.761
MATT: It's a big blue stone, about that big
around. It's embedded

00:51:18.761 --> 00:51:20.169
into the wall above the door.

00:51:20.169 --> 00:51:23.082
MARISHA: I ask them, how thick does the wall
appear to be around that side?

00:51:23.082 --> 00:51:26.757
LIAM: Looking through the door, can we tell how
deep?

00:51:26.757 --> 00:51:32.610
MATT: Yeah, actually, you can. It's about three
feet wide, four feet wide.

00:51:32.610 --> 00:51:35.362
LAURA: The depth of the wall?

00:51:35.362 --> 00:51:38.013
MATT: The depth of the wall, yeah. It's a big,
heavy wall.

00:51:38.013 --> 00:51:39.872
TRAVIS: Vex, I bet if you go real fast, you can
totally make it.

00:51:39.872 --> 00:51:42.053
LAURA: Good idea, Grog. I'll definitely try it.

00:51:42.053 --> 00:51:44.275
MARISHA: I can try and Stone Shape through it.

00:51:44.275 --> 00:51:51.723
MATT: You two... recognize, at least, there's
something very familiar about that stone embedded

00:51:51.723 --> 00:51:53.210
in the wall.

00:51:53.210 --> 00:51:55.175
TRAVIS: It's blue.

00:51:55.175 --> 00:52:09.149
MATT: It's definitely blue. It's very similar in
size, installation, and functional placement as

00:52:09.149 --> 00:52:12.264
the threshold crests that adorn the exterior of
Syngorn.

00:52:12.264 --> 00:52:18.757
LAURA: Which are definitely used... Wait. To
teleport things?

00:52:18.757 --> 00:52:24.002
MATT: The ones that are used to transport Syngorn
to the Feywild and back.

00:52:24.002 --> 00:52:29.357
MARISHA: Oh, weird. Oh no.

00:52:29.357 --> 00:52:37.567
LAURA: Oh my god, if the ritual finishes, they can
teleport this whole fucking city. Shit.

00:52:37.567 --> 00:52:39.012
We have to stop this.

00:52:39.012 --> 00:52:40.893
MARISHA: What if we dismantle the gems?

00:52:40.893 --> 00:52:43.709
TALIESIN: We would probably have to dismantle a
bunch of them.

00:52:43.709 --> 00:52:47.627
TRAVIS: We're out in the open. Dismantling that's
pretty tough.

00:52:47.627 --> 00:52:53.664
TALIESIN: I feel like it would be easier to wreck
the operator than try to break the machine.

00:52:53.664 --> 00:52:55.194
LAURA: I don't know.

00:52:55.194 --> 00:52:58.861
SAM: I mean, we've got a guy who crushes rocks all
the time.

00:52:58.861 --> 00:53:01.572
LAURA: Yeah, but I don't think it's safe to touch
those things.

00:53:01.572 --> 00:53:06.498
LIAM: And the moment he makes a ruckus, the air
squad is coming down on our location immediately.

00:53:06.498 --> 00:53:10.584
MARISHA: Didn't we take some of that crystal?
Didn't we take some of that?

00:53:10.584 --> 00:53:12.254
TALIESIN: Which crystal?

00:53:12.254 --> 00:53:14.672
MARISHA: Didn't we take shards of it from the
thresholds in Syngorn?

00:53:14.672 --> 00:53:17.918
LAURA: I don't remember. I don't have any in my
bag.

00:53:17.918 --> 00:53:20.522
MARISHA: One of them shattered, and I feel like we
took some.

00:53:20.522 --> 00:53:21.763
TRAVIS: Yeah, I did.

00:53:21.763 --> 00:53:22.753
LAURA: You did?

00:53:22.753 --> 00:53:24.595
TRAVIS: Yeah, shards of blue crystal.

00:53:24.595 --> 00:53:27.822
LAURA: Matt's like, uh...

00:53:27.822 --> 00:53:32.921
MARISHA: I don't know, maybe it's useful in this
case?

00:53:32.921 --> 00:53:35.778
TRAVIS: It's not pretty, it's all broken.

00:53:35.778 --> 00:53:46.036
LIAM: One question is, if these stones are used to
pull this tower into the main realms, is there

00:53:46.036 --> 00:53:50.263
another purpose to them here, or is that doorway
safe, is what I'm wondering?

00:53:50.263 --> 00:53:52.261
LAURA: No, that doorway is in no way safe.

00:53:52.261 --> 00:53:56.824
MARISHA: Where was the gem embedded in the
doorway?

00:53:56.824 --> 00:53:59.451
MATT: About eight feet up. About two feet above
the doorway.

00:53:59.451 --> 00:54:02.159
LIAM: I feel like we should go through the wall or
over it, just on principle.

00:54:02.159 --> 00:54:04.432
TALIESIN: We can go over it. We do have a magic
carpet.

00:54:04.432 --> 00:54:08.059
LAURA: Yeah, and all the flying creatures are
going to see us immediately. We either go under

00:54:08.059 --> 00:54:13.428
the wall... How far from the wall to the tower is
it? Does it seem?

00:54:13.428 --> 00:54:14.719
MATT: Probably...

00:54:14.719 --> 00:54:16.637
LAURA: Can we see the tower through the doorway?

00:54:16.637 --> 00:54:22.216
MATT: You can see across, and it's not a straight
shot, but you can get low and you can see where it

00:54:22.216 --> 00:54:27.733
breaks. Since you have a good sense of direction,
being the ranger, I'd say you know it's at least

00:54:27.733 --> 00:54:28.911
under a mile.

00:54:28.911 --> 00:54:35.070
LAURA: A mile to the tower? So it's probably two
miles wide, this whole...?

00:54:35.070 --> 00:54:39.756
MATT: Probably less. It's hard to pinpoint
directly from what little you can see, but it's

00:54:39.756 --> 00:54:44.088
definitely within a mile to a half mile of that
door, that wall.

00:54:44.088 --> 00:54:47.560
LIAM: Kiki, would you be able to Great Escape us
underneath this wall?

00:54:47.560 --> 00:54:51.526
LAURA: Yeah, that's what I'm thinking. What if we
go under the ground all the way to the tower?

00:54:51.526 --> 00:54:54.739
MARISHA: Is it unworked stone? What's the ground
like?

00:54:54.739 --> 00:55:03.260
MATT: The ground is unworked stone. It is broken
dirt and earth and stone. From what you gather, at

00:55:03.260 --> 00:55:05.415
the very least. A heavy layer of dust.

00:55:05.415 --> 00:55:11.677
MARISHA: I could attempt to tunnel us there.
Percy, I'm sure you would know more than anyone.

00:55:11.677 --> 00:55:16.368
What's the likelihood that we might encounter,
that I might bust through a dungeon or something,

00:55:16.368 --> 00:55:17.636
though, over there?

00:55:17.636 --> 00:55:20.389
TALIESIN: That would be the question. It's A,
where do we come up? B, how do we tunnel without

00:55:20.389 --> 00:55:25.705
collapsing a building on us? And C, what if
there's buried dead

00:55:25.705 --> 00:55:27.775
that haven't been able to break?

00:55:27.775 --> 00:55:31.724
MARISHA: I can get us under the wall for sure. I
can do both,

00:55:31.724 --> 00:55:34.219
it's just figuring out what we want to do.

00:55:34.219 --> 00:55:37.221
TALIESIN: If we can tunnel under the wall and then
come up in a building.

00:55:37.221 --> 00:55:40.828
LIAM: I think so. We're not trying to get all the
way there, just past this.

00:55:40.828 --> 00:55:42.965
MARISHA: Okay. Can I Stone Shape--

00:55:42.965 --> 00:55:45.128
LAURA: From within a building.

00:55:45.128 --> 00:55:47.473
MARISHA: -- a crawlspace through the wall?

00:55:47.473 --> 00:55:51.578
MATT: Yeah, you can probably do that. Let me look
at the Stone Shape spell here real fast.

00:55:51.578 --> 00:55:54.981
MARISHA: Big enough for at least Grog to marine
belly through?

00:55:54.981 --> 00:55:57.815
TRAVIS: We're all undead, so I'm a little smaller
right now, actually.

00:55:57.815 --> 00:56:00.063
MATT: Well, you look smaller.

00:56:00.063 --> 00:56:01.462
TALIESIN: You look smaller than you are.

00:56:01.462 --> 00:56:03.141
MATT: You're still your same height.

00:56:03.141 --> 00:56:06.790
TALIESIN: You would be a little zombie, floating,
stuck.

00:56:06.790 --> 00:56:08.681
LAURA: Can we be zombie cows?

00:56:08.681 --> 00:56:18.253
MATT: Stone Shape is instantaneous, and it's a
section no more than five feet in any dimension,

00:56:18.253 --> 00:56:22.628
so Stone Shape would be just a one-hit boom. You
could not create a long tunnel.

00:56:22.628 --> 00:56:26.873
MARISHA: But I can't carve a shape through the
wall to just crawl through, five feet?

00:56:26.873 --> 00:56:28.165
MATT: Oh, through the actual wall itself?

00:56:28.165 --> 00:56:32.241
MARISHA: Yeah, through the wall, not under the
ground. I want to bust a crawl space through the

00:56:32.241 --> 00:56:33.369
bottom of the wall.

00:56:33.369 --> 00:56:34.937
LAURA: Don't you think the flying guys will notice
that?

00:56:34.937 --> 00:56:37.314
MATT: Yeah, that could work. So do you want to do
that?

00:56:37.314 --> 00:56:41.211
MARISHA: It's not a dynamite blast, it's like a
(rumble).

00:56:41.211 --> 00:56:42.775
SAM: Yeah, it's just a hole in the wall.

00:56:42.775 --> 00:56:43.910
TALIESIN: It's like butter.

00:56:43.910 --> 00:56:45.311
MARISHA: Yeah, it's like butter. So...

00:56:45.311 --> 00:56:49.714
MATT: Okay. So you dart across the open road to
the other side, where the wall is.

00:56:49.714 --> 00:56:51.009
MARISHA: Cover for me.

00:56:51.009 --> 00:56:52.069
TRAVIS: How would we do that?

00:56:52.069 --> 00:56:53.307
TALIESIN: We are stealthed.

00:56:53.307 --> 00:56:54.410
LAURA: Yeah.

00:56:54.410 --> 00:56:57.780
MATT: Okay.

00:56:57.780 --> 00:57:03.763
LAURA: Can I-- Shit, well, you already rolled. Can
I have been keeping an eye on the sky and give her

00:57:03.763 --> 00:57:06.355
a go ahead when it looks like they're not going to
see her?

00:57:06.355 --> 00:57:09.623
MATT: You begin to do so as she runs across the
road.

00:57:09.623 --> 00:57:11.731
MARISHA: What?

00:57:11.731 --> 00:57:13.394
LAURA: Just go. Just fucking go.

00:57:13.394 --> 00:57:14.500
MARISHA: Okay.

00:57:14.500 --> 00:57:19.673
MATT: You hear the distant shrieks, communication
between the various gloom stalkers that (snarling)

00:57:19.673 --> 00:57:26.704
echoing in the sky. You make it all the way across
to the wall, and get low, focus, close your eyes,

00:57:26.704 --> 00:57:38.718
press your hand against the cold, dark wall, and
feel it (whoosh) as immediately, you carve a

00:57:38.718 --> 00:57:45.591
circular tunnel through that goes completely to
the other side. Seemingly to no negative effect.

00:57:45.591 --> 00:57:50.138
MARISHA: Seemingly to no negative effect, I've
made a tunnel.

00:57:50.138 --> 00:57:53.852
SAM: You sound different. Why are you using weird
words?

00:57:53.852 --> 00:57:57.804
MARISHA: I'm whispering! I'm just trying to be
more pragmatic.

00:57:57.804 --> 00:57:58.832
SAM: Let's go.

00:57:58.832 --> 00:58:00.999
LAURA: Hey, guys, we didn't eat a Heroes' Feast
yet, either.

00:58:00.999 --> 00:58:02.120
SAM: We didn't heal ourselves.

00:58:02.120 --> 00:58:03.363
MARISHA: No, we didn't.

00:58:03.363 --> 00:58:04.475
TALIESIN: We've got to get through the wall.

00:58:04.475 --> 00:58:05.685
SAM: Let's get through the wall, and then we'll
heal.

00:58:05.685 --> 00:58:08.179
MATT: Okay.

00:58:08.179 --> 00:58:18.355
TRAVIS: He is looking at each one of us and
rolling.

00:58:18.355 --> 00:58:20.901
TALIESIN: He's making eye contact and rolling a
die, like it means something.

00:58:20.901 --> 00:58:22.587
LAURA: I'm not going to look at him.

00:58:22.587 --> 00:58:24.362
MARISHA: Keeping track. Why is he keeping track?

00:58:24.362 --> 00:58:25.862
LIAM: If I don't look, he can't kill me.

00:58:25.862 --> 00:58:27.314
ASHLEY: If you don't make eye contact.

00:58:27.314 --> 00:58:29.931
LAURA: It's like in school, if you don't make eye
contact, maybe they won't call on you.

00:58:29.931 --> 00:58:36.856
MATT: Yeah, it's the old Warner Brothers rule. So
as you guys all, one by one, dart across and leap

00:58:36.856 --> 00:58:40.346
beneath the tunnel that Keyleth had created,
Keyleth, have you gone through the tunnel, or are

00:58:40.346 --> 00:58:41.768
you seeing everyone else through?

00:58:41.768 --> 00:58:44.498
MARISHA: I'll wait and see everyone else through,
just in case.

00:58:44.498 --> 00:58:46.711
TRAVIS: Oh, how generous of you.

00:58:46.711 --> 00:58:52.381
LAURA: We all are dead.

00:58:52.381 --> 00:58:55.310
MATT: You all begin darting through, one after
another.

00:58:55.310 --> 00:58:57.162
MARISHA: I'm going to try and keep a lookout.

00:58:57.162 --> 00:59:05.391
MATT: Keyleth, you glance up as, at the very tail
end of it, you have Scanlan and Pike at the very

00:59:05.391 --> 00:59:07.300
end, ready to rush through the tunnel.

00:59:07.300 --> 00:59:08.540
SAM: We're slow.

00:59:08.540 --> 00:59:14.227
MATT: Because of the gnomish feet. They both get
there as you glance up and watch as one of the

00:59:14.227 --> 00:59:23.622
gloom stalkers (shriek) and goes into a full
screeching dive towards you outside of the wall.

00:59:23.622 --> 00:59:25.309
What are you guys doing?

00:59:25.309 --> 00:59:27.298
SAM: Hurrying.

00:59:27.298 --> 00:59:30.309
ASHLEY: Jumping through as fast as our little
gnome feet can take us.

00:59:30.309 --> 00:59:35.663
MATT: Okay, so Pike, you dart through, Scanlan,
you dart through. With the size of the tunnel,

00:59:35.663 --> 00:59:38.888
it's easy enough for the both of you to just run
through while crouching as opposed to having to

00:59:38.888 --> 00:59:43.417
get on your hands and knees, so you guys start
making your way through to the side. Pike, you

00:59:43.417 --> 00:59:46.273
make it out the other side. Scanlan, you're
halfway through. Keyleth, you're still there,

00:59:46.273 --> 00:59:49.223
ready to go in after as it's about to bear down on
you.

00:59:49.223 --> 00:59:50.577
MARISHA: It's not coming up?

00:59:50.577 --> 00:59:54.204
MATT: Oh, no, it's going for a straight dive. It's
going right for you.

00:59:54.204 --> 00:59:58.653
MARISHA: Oh, god, am I trying to do anything but
get through?

00:59:58.653 --> 01:00:00.172
LIAM: You're running! Come on!

01:00:00.172 --> 01:00:01.711
LAURA: She has to duck down.

01:00:01.711 --> 01:00:03.312
MARISHA: I don't know, I've got to crawl through!

01:00:03.312 --> 01:00:05.959
LAURA: Yeah. So do you have protection? Do you
have something you could turn into?

01:00:05.959 --> 01:00:12.355
MARISHA: Yeah! Thank you! Thank you! I'm going to
see it and immediately Beast Shape into a little

01:00:12.355 --> 01:00:14.706
mouse and (crawling sounds) through.

01:00:14.706 --> 01:00:20.542
MATT: I want you to roll an initiative roll to see
whether or not it gets to you in time.

01:00:20.542 --> 01:00:22.703
SAM: Am I rolling, too, since I'm half-out?

01:00:22.703 --> 01:00:25.079
MATT: You're halfway in the tunnel. It couldn't
fit in the tunnel if it wanted to.

01:00:25.079 --> 01:00:26.578
SAM: But, I mean, am I watching this?

01:00:26.578 --> 01:00:27.673
MATT: You're watching this.

01:00:27.673 --> 01:00:29.819
SAM: I'm going to roll. Okay.

01:00:29.819 --> 01:00:32.123
LIAM: I'm going to say that I didn't leave the
other side of the wall when I realized that she

01:00:32.123 --> 01:00:34.767
wasn't coming through. So, waiting right in front
of Scanlan.

01:00:34.767 --> 01:00:36.248
MARISHA: 18.

01:00:36.248 --> 01:00:37.378
SAM: Two for me.

01:00:37.378 --> 01:00:46.425
MATT: Okay. Natural 19 plus three. So, as you
shift down into the tiny mouse-like form, its

01:00:46.425 --> 01:00:55.249
claws immediately slam into and sink into the
mouse body. Yeah, that's a 23 to hit.

01:00:55.249 --> 01:00:57.776
MARISHA: Yeah. Immediately poof.

01:00:57.776 --> 01:01:01.597
MATT: How much hit points does your mouse form
have? Like one?

01:01:01.597 --> 01:01:04.739
MARISHA: I'm assuming no more than a kitten's
worth.

01:01:04.739 --> 01:01:11.459
MATT: Right, so yeah. So, we'll say for the
purposes, one. So that would be 16 points of

01:01:11.459 --> 01:01:16.560
piercing damage, so your form immediately reverts,
its claws now fill with your regular Keyleth form.

01:01:16.560 --> 01:01:20.528
You take 15 points of piercing damage, Keyleth,
and you are grappled.

01:01:20.528 --> 01:01:23.540
MARISHA: Cool. Cool. Cool. Cool story. Cool.

01:01:23.540 --> 01:01:28.019
MATT: As soon as it grabs you, it begins to pull
you out of the tunnel

01:01:28.019 --> 01:01:29.799
and lift with you in its claws.

01:01:29.799 --> 01:01:33.152
ASHLEY: Can I grab her arms?

01:01:33.152 --> 01:01:35.748
MATT: You're on the other side of the wall.
Scanlan's on the other side right now.

01:01:35.748 --> 01:01:39.054
LIAM: I'm three feet away from you.

01:01:39.054 --> 01:01:41.224
LAURA: Yeah, but he's in front of you.

01:01:41.224 --> 01:01:47.303
MATT: Everyone else on the other side of the wall,
Scanlan in the middle, Keyleth in the front. You

01:01:47.303 --> 01:01:51.424
saw it shriek and dive down, you don't know what
happened from that point. You can glance down and

01:01:51.424 --> 01:01:55.909
you watch as Keyleth is being pulled up. You see
that happening. Scanlan, what are you doing?

01:01:55.909 --> 01:02:02.270
SAM: I'll yell to the rest: it's got Keyleth. I'll
cast Dominate Monster on it, I guess.

01:02:02.270 --> 01:02:08.237
MATT: Okay. So, what's the spell DC on that?

01:02:08.237 --> 01:02:12.809
SAM: Well, I was probably not fast enough to pull
up my horn, so 20.

01:02:12.809 --> 01:02:21.976
MATT: That's a natural four plus three. So, as you
say that and turn around, you bring your hand up

01:02:21.976 --> 01:02:27.320
and begin muttering the incantation and finish it
with a &lt;i&gt;flourish!&lt;/i&gt;

01:02:27.320 --> 01:02:31.586
SAM: I could have just done that this whole
time?!

01:02:31.586 --> 01:02:40.131
MATT: As you finish the incantation, you watch as
a small ring of glowing purple-pink glyphs appear

01:02:40.131 --> 01:02:46.990
like a crown around the outside, floating about
three inches from the gloom stalker's "head." Its

01:02:46.990 --> 01:02:50.894
shriek goes (intense to calm croaking) and it's
just there, hovering in the air, about ten feet

01:02:50.894 --> 01:02:52.339
up, clutching Keyleth.

01:02:52.339 --> 01:03:00.978
SAM: All right. Please deposit her on the other
side. Over the wall.

01:03:00.978 --> 01:03:08.609
MATT: You guys watch as the gloom stalker (wings
flapping) over the wall. Lands on the ground,

01:03:08.609 --> 01:03:11.425
slamming Keyleth. It slams you into the ground as
it lands.

01:03:11.425 --> 01:03:14.271
You take five points of bludgeoning damage.

01:03:14.271 --> 01:03:17.226
MARISHA: (wheezing) You could have told it
gently!

01:03:17.226 --> 01:03:18.978
SAM: I don't speak Gloom!

01:03:18.978 --> 01:03:20.931
MARISHA: Five points?

01:03:20.931 --> 01:03:25.837
MATT: Yes. You (wham) and almost knocks the wind
out of you, and you slam into the hard ground, but

01:03:25.837 --> 01:03:27.745
the claws unfurl and leave you.

01:03:27.745 --> 01:03:30.935
MARISHA: (wheezing) I made it, guys! I'm glad you
made it!

01:03:30.935 --> 01:03:33.426
SAM: Only 59 more minutes.

01:03:33.426 --> 01:03:36.782
ASHLEY: Maybe he can tell the others to leave us
alone!

01:03:36.782 --> 01:03:38.694
MARISHA: Yeah, call them off!

01:03:38.694 --> 01:03:42.275
TALIESIN: Or maybe there are birds on the other
side of the wall.

01:03:42.275 --> 01:03:46.078
SAM: Does he keep rerolling for breaking, or is
that it?

01:03:46.078 --> 01:03:48.725
MARISHA: Tell them it's handled, we're dead.

01:03:48.725 --> 01:03:51.350
TALIESIN: And then we can ride him!

01:03:51.350 --> 01:03:56.746
LAURA: Ask him if he has any money, and ask him if
he can make a good dinner because I'm hungry.

01:03:56.746 --> 01:03:58.882
MARISHA: Where's the nearest 7-11?

01:03:58.882 --> 01:04:04.530
MATT: Each time the target takes damage. It has to
take damage to get the save. So, it's under your

01:04:04.530 --> 01:04:06.369
control for an hour or until it takes damage.

01:04:06.369 --> 01:04:17.794
SAM: All right. First things first, please go tell
your fellow gloomy friends that the hunt is off.

01:04:17.794 --> 01:04:24.523
No more flesh down here. And come back!

01:04:24.523 --> 01:04:32.474
MATT: (croaking) You can see that it's landed, its
giant wings have folded under into these folded

01:04:32.474 --> 01:04:39.034
knuckle-like claws that hit the ground as it
(croaks) and he gets really close and snarls at

01:04:39.034 --> 01:04:44.162
you. As it gets close, the air gets colder in its
presence, it's almost like it brings this drop.

01:04:44.162 --> 01:04:50.639
It's already pretty cold here in the Shadowfell,
but it becomes pretty much freezing as soon as it gets

01:04:50.639 --> 01:04:57.619
within five feet of you. It seems to suck heat out
of the air. As it's glaring at you, (wings

01:04:57.619 --> 01:05:04.709
flapping) begins to take up. You can see three
other gloom stalkers who saw it dive earlier are

01:05:04.709 --> 01:05:12.658
all arriving towards your location. As it rides up
towards them, you hear (gloom stalker speech) and

01:05:12.658 --> 01:05:18.523
the other ones (gloom stalker speech) snap at it, circle
it and they all have what looks like an argument,

01:05:18.523 --> 01:05:26.065
if there was. And then, eventually, they break and
they begin shouting off (gloom stalker speech).

01:05:26.065 --> 01:05:31.521
You watch as the heavy clusters that had been
swarming this area of the town begin to respond in

01:05:31.521 --> 01:05:36.524
kind. You hear the echoes, the cacophony of
various screeches and screams and they all begin

01:05:36.524 --> 01:05:40.613
to slowly dissipate and diffuse amongst the entire
city of Thar Amphala.

01:05:40.613 --> 01:05:42.269
TALIESIN: Well, that went well.

01:05:42.269 --> 01:05:43.465
LAURA: Good job, Scanlan.

01:05:43.465 --> 01:05:44.829
LIAM: Welcome back, Scanlan Shorthalt.

01:05:44.829 --> 01:05:46.065
MARISHA: Thanks, Scanlan!

01:05:46.065 --> 01:05:48.985
SAM: It's good to be back. Okay, we'll need a name
for him, obviously.

01:05:48.985 --> 01:05:50.008
LAURA: Yes.

01:05:50.008 --> 01:05:52.067
SAM: So, anybody got any ideas?

01:05:52.067 --> 01:05:53.160
LAURA: Benjamin is what I'm thinking.

01:05:53.160 --> 01:05:54.635
SAM: Benjamin is great.

01:05:54.635 --> 01:05:56.421
MARISHA: Mr. Mistoffelees!

01:05:56.421 --> 01:05:58.165
SAM: That's way better.

01:05:58.165 --> 01:06:00.664
(laughing)

01:06:00.664 --> 01:06:03.584
TALIESIN: Can we ride him to the tower?

01:06:03.584 --> 01:06:10.914
SAM: Well, some of us can, right? By looking at
him, how much can he carry? Or she!

01:06:10.914 --> 01:06:20.220
MATT: You're not certain, based on its size, it
could maybe carry three medium to small people.

01:06:20.220 --> 01:06:21.639
SAM: Okay.

01:06:21.639 --> 01:06:24.024
MARISHA: (whispered) What's around us right now?

01:06:24.024 --> 01:06:25.684
(regular volume) Sorry, what's around us right
now?

01:06:25.684 --> 01:06:30.713
MATT: So, as you glance around the other side of the
wall, the city is denser within this inner

01:06:30.779 --> 01:06:43.280
cloister, and the buildings all seem to be newer.
Or repaired. It seems like this inner sanctum of

01:06:43.280 --> 01:06:50.693
Thar Amphala has garnished most of the attention
of those that currently reside within its space.

01:06:50.693 --> 01:06:59.302
As you are glancing up, too, you see the flicker,
the faint flicker of the conjoining strands of

01:06:59.302 --> 01:07:05.718
magical energy that are rising up to the pinnacle
of the tower of Entropis where you see these three

01:07:05.718 --> 01:07:11.458
heavy claw-like fingers that jut out of the top of
the tower all curve inward. The flash is in the

01:07:11.458 --> 01:07:20.207
center of it, it's just glowing brighter and
brighter. That pulsing is (pulsing). It's almost

01:07:20.207 --> 01:07:27.907
like seeing this heartbeat of pure energy that's
swelling and swelling.

01:07:27.907 --> 01:07:30.555
LAURA: I don't think we have time to stop.

01:07:30.555 --> 01:07:38.824
SAM: Well, so no more healing. But we could fly
right up there and break that thing.

01:07:38.824 --> 01:07:42.190
MARISHA: Do we really not want to do any other
healing?

01:07:42.190 --> 01:07:49.467
LAURA: Pike can heal us, but we can't rest.
There's no time for a rest. No time for a Heroes'

01:07:49.467 --> 01:07:51.811
Feast. I bought those &lt;i&gt;fucking&lt;/i&gt; chalices.

01:07:51.811 --> 01:07:53.614
TALIESIN: Next time.

01:07:53.614 --> 01:07:55.773
MARISHA: Might still be useful.

01:07:55.773 --> 01:07:57.418
ASHLEY: How long does Heroes' Feast take?

01:07:57.418 --> 01:07:59.004
SAM: Like an hour or something.

01:07:59.004 --> 01:08:00.667
TALIESIN: It will hardly matter.

01:08:00.667 --> 01:08:02.468
ASHLEY: We can't just take an hour?

01:08:02.468 --> 01:08:06.255
LAURA: I think that thing is like, going to go.

01:08:06.255 --> 01:08:11.790
MATT: It's up to you guys. It's a gradual. It's
not like all of a sudden, right now, you watched

01:08:11.790 --> 01:08:17.298
it pulse. As you've been getting towards, you've
been watching it slowly swell. So, who knows.

01:08:17.298 --> 01:08:22.150
SAM: Some of us could get on Mr. Mistoffelees and
fly around the tower and see if there's a window

01:08:22.150 --> 01:08:23.853
that we could bust in or something.

01:08:23.853 --> 01:08:28.553
LAURA: I wonder if Delilah's on the top of the
tower.

01:08:28.553 --> 01:08:31.962
SAM: Yeah, but we'll be on a thing, so maybe we
won't be very conspicuous.

01:08:31.962 --> 01:08:36.074
TALIESIN: Actually, maybe if we ask Mr.
Mistoffelees-- I'm going to never get tired of

01:08:36.074 --> 01:08:40.791
saying that!-- to go up to the tower, greet
whoever's up there, and throw them off.

01:08:40.791 --> 01:08:43.962
SAM: It's just a pulsing orb of doom, isn't it?

01:08:43.962 --> 01:08:47.808
TALIESIN: Just go up there and cause havoc.

01:08:47.808 --> 01:08:50.765
SAM: One of us needs to see what's up there.

01:08:50.765 --> 01:08:54.661
TALIESIN: No, we can just send him up there, and
then we can head in through the tower. He can just

01:08:54.661 --> 01:08:55.952
be a problem.

01:08:55.952 --> 01:09:01.210
SAM: He's dumb! What if comes back and he's like
'I don't know!'?

01:09:01.210 --> 01:09:05.077
TALIESIN: Just say, go up there and if there's
anything living up there, throw it off.

01:09:05.077 --> 01:09:10.922
SAM: Can't one of us go up there with him to scout
it out? Yeah, if someone's invisible. Can't you

01:09:10.922 --> 01:09:12.380
all be invisible?

01:09:12.380 --> 01:09:13.679
TALIESIN: Yes, all of us.

01:09:13.679 --> 01:09:14.611
SAM: Just me.

01:09:14.611 --> 01:09:16.260
TALIESIN: Yes, it's just you.

01:09:16.260 --> 01:09:17.657
LAURA: Can't you make all of us invisible?

01:09:17.657 --> 01:09:19.982
SAM: Not while I'm concentrating on Mr.
Mistoffelees!

01:09:19.982 --> 01:09:22.086
(laughter)

01:09:22.086 --> 01:09:29.322
TALIESIN: I say we head in closer on foot. If you
want to ride Mr. Mistoffelees up to the top of the

01:09:29.322 --> 01:09:31.364
tower, that's one thing. But I think just sending
him up there,

01:09:31.364 --> 01:09:33.407
or sending him to be an agent of chaos.

01:09:33.407 --> 01:09:37.807
LIAM: I could probably ride him, and if shit goes
south, I could get away.

01:09:37.807 --> 01:09:39.550
TALIESIN: You could always get swallowed.

01:09:39.550 --> 01:09:41.349
LIAM: By Mr. Mistoffelees?

01:09:41.349 --> 01:09:42.971
LAURA: By anything.

01:09:42.971 --> 01:09:46.356
TALIESIN: I get the distinct impression we're
going to have options before this day is over.

01:09:46.356 --> 01:09:52.993
MARISHA: I feel like we're going to have to do a
lot of things to stop this.

01:09:52.993 --> 01:09:56.391
SAM: We need to get into the tower! We don't even
know how to do that!

01:09:56.391 --> 01:10:00.875
LIAM: We don't know what we're talking about,
which is why I think the idea to go scope it out

01:10:00.875 --> 01:10:02.150
is a good one.

01:10:02.150 --> 01:10:06.313
LAURA: Does it look like there's any windows on
the tower, or is just a big old Rapunzel tower?

01:10:06.313 --> 01:10:07.655
MATT: Make a perception check.

01:10:07.655 --> 01:10:09.598
LAURA: Okay.

01:10:09.598 --> 01:10:11.092
SAM: Nope!

01:10:11.092 --> 01:10:12.652
LAURA: Well, hold on. 19.

01:10:12.652 --> 01:10:20.562
MATT: 19, still pretty good. Not a single window.
It's a solid tower.

01:10:20.562 --> 01:10:23.013
ASHLEY: Are there any doors? No windows?

01:10:23.013 --> 01:10:28.500
MATT: You can't tell from your perspective right
now. The base is currently obscured by the very,

01:10:28.500 --> 01:10:29.861
very dense buildings.

01:10:29.861 --> 01:10:31.452
LAURA: Ultimate challenge for Vox Machina.

01:10:31.452 --> 01:10:34.586
TRAVIS: Should we check one of the buildings, and
then we can figure out who wants to go check it

01:10:34.586 --> 01:10:36.567
out, so we can get out of the open?

01:10:36.567 --> 01:10:38.304
LAURA: Yeah, let's get in a building and hide!

01:10:38.304 --> 01:10:40.089
TRAVIS: Because he's a cleaner!

01:10:40.089 --> 01:10:45.554
LIAM: The tower, is it obscured by all this shit
happening on top of it? Vex can see there's no

01:10:45.554 --> 01:10:48.772
windows; can we see if there's a rooftop to it at
all?

01:10:48.772 --> 01:10:50.292
MATT: There is a top to the tower.

01:10:50.292 --> 01:10:53.151
LIAM: Is it this, is it this, or can we not see?

01:10:53.151 --> 01:11:00.260
MATT: The tower gently tapers and then comes to an
end. There is a top. You see there's three giant,

01:11:00.260 --> 01:11:08.709
curled finger-like black spires that curl inward
on the outside, inward. And then there's the

01:11:08.709 --> 01:11:14.029
platform where the tower stops, where it seems
like there would be somewhere to stand.

01:11:14.029 --> 01:11:17.566
LAURA: The thing that's glowing is off of the
ground of the tower?

01:11:17.566 --> 01:11:20.797
MATT: It's filling up the entirety of that space
between the fingers

01:11:20.797 --> 01:11:22.782
on the actual roof of the tower.

01:11:22.782 --> 01:11:27.160
MARISHA: What if it has to keep expanding all the
way to the crystals?

01:11:27.160 --> 01:11:36.576
TRAVIS: What's the nearest building? Is there one
building that's closest to

01:11:36.576 --> 01:11:38.207
where we came through the tunnel?

01:11:38.207 --> 01:11:40.157
MATT: Yeah, you guys are about ten feet from the
nearest building.

01:11:40.157 --> 01:11:41.681
TRAVIS: Can I walk over? Are there any windows?

01:11:41.681 --> 01:11:44.025
MATT: This building does not have any windows.

01:11:44.025 --> 01:11:45.172
TRAVIS: Does it have a door?

01:11:45.172 --> 01:11:46.199
MATT: It does.

01:11:46.199 --> 01:11:47.409
TRAVIS: Can I knock?

01:11:47.409 --> 01:12:00.374
MATT: (knocking) You watch as an older gentleman
with a very thin gray goatee, looks a little

01:12:00.374 --> 01:12:05.402
sallow, missing his left eye, he currently has a
small sack over his shoulder, he opens the door.

01:12:05.402 --> 01:12:06.874
"Can I--"

01:12:06.874 --> 01:12:08.504
TRAVIS: Hey, come here! And I grab his face.

01:12:08.504 --> 01:12:11.303
MATT: (muffled yelling)

01:12:11.303 --> 01:12:12.368
LAURA: Inside! Inside!

01:12:12.368 --> 01:12:13.940
TRAVIS: We just go in. Push in.

01:12:13.940 --> 01:12:15.247
TALIESIN: Well, we're going in now, aren't we?

01:12:15.247 --> 01:12:17.262
LIAM: And we're walking, and we're walking.

01:12:17.262 --> 01:12:25.062
SAM: I'll tell Mr. Mistoffelees to do a 90-second
loop and come back down and check in on us because

01:12:25.062 --> 01:12:26.716
he can't fit in the door, right?

01:12:26.716 --> 01:12:27.723
MATT: No!

01:12:27.723 --> 01:12:29.592
SAM: Fly around 90 seconds and swoop back down.

01:12:29.592 --> 01:12:38.867
MATT: He does a small circle as you guys all rush
into the building. You enter the inside. You see

01:12:38.867 --> 01:12:45.818
what looks to be a lot of building materials. It
looks like some of the outer buildings here were

01:12:45.818 --> 01:12:52.174
used as the storage facilities for what a lot of
the city was rebuilt as. There's nobody else

01:12:52.174 --> 01:12:56.889
inside right now. This gentleman looks like he was
on his way out of the building as you interrupted

01:12:56.889 --> 01:13:07.255
him. As now most of his head is just clasped by
your giant goliath Titanstone Knuckle-adorned

01:13:07.255 --> 01:13:13.794
hand, you see a little bit of his eye peeking over
Grog's, and he's like (muffled yelling).

01:13:13.794 --> 01:13:15.514
TRAVIS: Shh.

01:13:15.514 --> 01:13:20.215
MATT: You see he's got the heavy male pattern--
looks like the old D&amp;D Dungeon Master from the

01:13:20.215 --> 01:13:25.783
cartoon. He's bald on top, has long gray hair that
goes past his shoulders. Very thin, missing the

01:13:25.783 --> 01:13:30.983
left eye, and he's just limp. He's not even going to
fight it.

01:13:30.983 --> 01:13:35.545
LAURA: Oh hey! We were sent here by Delilah
Briarwood. You may know her.

01:13:35.545 --> 01:13:37.553
MATT: (muffled yelling)

01:13:37.553 --> 01:13:41.093
LAURA: Right. The ritual that's happening
on top of the tower. How long until that

01:13:41.093 --> 01:13:42.252
thing's done?

01:13:42.252 --> 01:13:44.085
MATT: (muffled noises)

01:13:44.085 --> 01:13:50.767
LAURA: Blink once for 15 minutes. Blink twice for
an hour or more.

01:13:50.767 --> 01:13:54.679
LIAM: Three times for a bunch of days.

01:13:54.679 --> 01:13:56.052
SAM: Maybe he doesn't know.

01:13:56.052 --> 01:13:59.109
LAURA: Yeah, do you know? Blink once for yes,
blink twice for no.

01:13:59.109 --> 01:14:01.259
MATT: (muffling noises)

01:14:01.259 --> 01:14:02.921
SAM: 15 minutes! No, that was once for 15
minutes!

01:14:02.921 --> 01:14:04.708
LAURA: No, that was an hour, at least!

01:14:04.708 --> 01:14:09.506
MARISHA: I thought he blinked before. Are we at an
hour and 15 minutes?

01:14:09.506 --> 01:14:11.680
TALIESIN: I don't think you can call it a blink if
you've got one eye.

01:14:11.680 --> 01:14:13.532
I think it's just a wink.

01:14:13.532 --> 01:14:15.700
MARISHA: A wink? Man, semantics!

01:14:15.700 --> 01:14:24.011
MATT: You get the sense that, as you say that, it
does hurt him a little. His demeanor, while

01:14:24.011 --> 01:14:27.255
already pretty shattered, just even further (sad
noise).

01:14:27.255 --> 01:14:29.688
TRAVIS: Does he have any pouches on him, or
anything in his hands?

01:14:29.688 --> 01:14:34.610
MATT: He had a small sack over his shoulder that
he was leaving with.

01:14:34.610 --> 01:14:36.777
He's just adorned in regular--

01:14:36.777 --> 01:14:39.248
TRAVIS: Is the sack on the ground now or is it
still over his shoulder?

01:14:39.248 --> 01:14:44.097
MATT: No, it's currently on the ground. He dropped
it as soon as you rushed and pushed him.

01:14:44.097 --> 01:14:46.294
TRAVIS: I take the satchel, and I give it to Pike
and say: look in here.

01:14:46.294 --> 01:14:58.293
MATT: You glance inside. As soon as you grab it,
you hear the clanging of metal. You look inside

01:14:58.293 --> 01:15:05.985
and you can see what appear to be a handful of
dark metal shortswords, daggers, simple dried

01:15:05.985 --> 01:15:11.089
rations, and, in fact, as you glance inside the
room now, you can see a lot of the supplies here,

01:15:11.089 --> 01:15:16.990
aside from construction supplies, you see a
handful of weapons that are well-made,

01:15:16.990 --> 01:15:19.117
recent-made, not seen battle yet.

01:15:19.117 --> 01:15:22.468
SAM: They're about to invade.

01:15:22.468 --> 01:15:24.809
LAURA: What if we burn the fucking city down?

01:15:24.809 --> 01:15:27.557
SAM: I mean, sure! What?

01:15:27.557 --> 01:15:32.138
LAURA: I mean, if they're planning on transporting
this whole fucking city, and setting an army loose

01:15:32.138 --> 01:15:38.003
on our world, why don't we just burn the whole
fucking city down? Destroy their rations. Destroy

01:15:38.003 --> 01:15:39.068
their weapons!

01:15:39.068 --> 01:15:40.416
TALIESIN: I am excited by this plan.

01:15:40.416 --> 01:15:43.441
SAM: Wait, what? No! That's terrible!

01:15:43.441 --> 01:15:45.577
LIAM: Let's burn down Manhattan. How do you do
that?!

01:15:45.577 --> 01:15:51.392
TRAVIS: Shall we ask this gentleman some
questions? All right. I'm going to remove my hand.

01:15:51.392 --> 01:15:58.096
Obviously, you're like really cool with the
purpose-- perspective of dying, and I'll quicken

01:15:58.096 --> 01:16:05.844
that if you make a loud noise. Right, like, if
you've ever seen, like, Jello mixed with, like

01:16:05.844 --> 01:16:09.599
apple pudding. That's what I'll do to your head.

01:16:09.599 --> 01:16:11.629
MATT: Make an intimidation check.

01:16:11.629 --> 01:16:14.941
LAURA: You did your hand signal for Arnold
Palmer.

01:16:14.941 --> 01:16:16.473
TRAVIS: I did!

01:16:16.473 --> 01:16:18.424
MATT: Universal.

01:16:18.424 --> 01:16:20.369
LAURA: Arnold Palmer?

01:16:20.369 --> 01:16:22.862
TRAVIS: 22!

01:16:22.862 --> 01:16:36.216
MATT: 22. He doesn't make a sound, more than the
gentle trickle out of his pant leg does. (laughs)

01:16:36.216 --> 01:16:37.860
TALIESIN: I think that's a yes.

01:16:37.860 --> 01:16:40.011
TRAVIS: Grab the scruff of his collar.

01:16:40.011 --> 01:16:48.096
MATT: Okay, as you release, he (gasps). His teeth
are broken and yellow, his one gaping socket is

01:16:48.096 --> 01:16:53.435
twitching a little bit from the recovery of the
sudden, rapid series of events that he was not

01:16:53.435 --> 01:16:58.616
expecting today. As he gathers his breath, and
scratches the side of his leg,

01:16:58.616 --> 01:17:04.417
"So. What do you wish to do to me?"

01:17:04.417 --> 01:17:08.378
SAM: Nothing! We've got to hurry!

01:17:08.378 --> 01:17:10.825
LAURA: No, really, do you know anything about the
ritual?

01:17:10.825 --> 01:17:13.622
MATT: "I mean, not the specifics."

01:17:13.622 --> 01:17:16.771
LAURA: Do you know if it's going to be over soon?

01:17:16.771 --> 01:17:23.727
MATT: "I know that some of the acolytes were
rushing through, expediting things recently."

01:17:23.727 --> 01:17:26.043
MARISHA: Why?

01:17:26.043 --> 01:17:27.711
MATT: "I don't know!"

01:17:27.711 --> 01:17:30.005
SAM: Did they tell you to gather weapons?

01:17:30.005 --> 01:17:31.789
MATT: "They just told us to be ready."

01:17:31.789 --> 01:17:38.845
LIAM: For what? What's the plan here, man? You're really far
away from anything fucking nice.

01:17:38.845 --> 01:17:43.492
MATT: You watch him close off as you start saying
that. He catches himself saying too much

01:17:43.492 --> 01:17:46.019
information. His demeanor goes cold.

01:17:46.019 --> 01:17:48.889
LAURA: Please, we know you're going to transport
to another plane.

01:17:48.889 --> 01:17:53.599
MARISHA: You're trying to bail, aren't you? Were
you trying to run?

01:17:53.599 --> 01:17:55.874
SAM: No, he's joining the fight.

01:17:55.874 --> 01:17:59.092
LAURA: Oh my god, he was going to leave.

01:17:59.092 --> 01:18:05.432
TRAVIS: Well, he's clearly clamming up. I put my
hand back over the front of his face, I take the

01:18:05.432 --> 01:18:09.334
other one, put it on the back of his face, and I
start making my fingers touch.

01:18:09.334 --> 01:18:20.213
MATT: (muffled groaning) He reaches up and grabs
the small symbol, familiar loop with the fork

01:18:20.213 --> 01:18:23.635
above it. He clasps it in his hand and doesn't
resist.

01:18:23.635 --> 01:18:30.325
TRAVIS: Do you want it?

01:18:30.325 --> 01:18:37.488
ASHLEY: Yeah! Put him a little lower, Grog. I rip
off the necklace.

01:18:37.488 --> 01:18:40.530
MATT: He's like clasping it in his hand. Make a
strength check.

01:18:40.530 --> 01:18:42.194
TALIESIN: Drop it! Drop it!

01:18:42.194 --> 01:18:44.378
ASHLEY: Oh my god, we're so terrible!

01:18:44.378 --> 01:18:45.737
TRAVIS: Are we?

01:18:45.737 --> 01:18:48.360
ASHLEY: Natural 20!

01:18:48.360 --> 01:18:56.138
MATT: He's clasping it, and you can see his one
eye rolls back to hold onto it and he's muttering

01:18:56.138 --> 01:19:01.459
a prayer beneath your fingers and he's (muffled
muttering) and you tear it from his grasp.

01:19:01.459 --> 01:19:03.798
(muffled panic)

01:19:03.798 --> 01:19:08.920
ASHLEY: We'll give it back! You've got to answer
some questions for us.

01:19:08.920 --> 01:19:12.268
TRAVIS: No, he won't. Look away if you want to
preserve anything, and I just squish his head.

01:19:12.268 --> 01:19:20.946
MATT: As you're saying that, you watch as one eye
opens and his hands go limp and then

01:19:20.946 --> 01:19:23.858
(face exploding) and it just (splattering).

01:19:23.858 --> 01:19:25.101
ASHLEY: &lt;i&gt;Grog&lt;/i&gt;!

01:19:25.101 --> 01:19:27.310
MATT: Spray on Pike.

01:19:27.310 --> 01:19:31.446
TRAVIS: I thought you were me giving the signal
like, end it!

01:19:31.446 --> 01:19:36.308
ASHLEY: No! I was going to-- whatever.

01:19:36.308 --> 01:19:38.762
TRAVIS: All right. We'll work on it.

01:19:38.762 --> 01:19:40.416
ASHLEY: We'll find another one. It's okay.

01:19:40.416 --> 01:19:43.509
TRAVIS: Yeah, I'm really sorry. Sorry.

01:19:43.509 --> 01:19:45.063
ASHLEY: Brains!

01:19:45.063 --> 01:19:46.716
LIAM: Pike got Dragon Aged.

01:19:46.716 --> 01:19:48.635
MATT: Yeah!

01:19:48.635 --> 01:19:51.152
MARISHA: Is there a water bucket around?

01:19:51.152 --> 01:19:55.153
MATT: Make an investigation check.

01:19:55.153 --> 01:19:59.817
LAURA: So, but, set fire to the house, right? Burn
the whole city down?

01:19:59.817 --> 01:20:01.159
SAM: No!

01:20:01.159 --> 01:20:02.849
MARISHA: 11.

01:20:02.849 --> 01:20:04.969
TALIESIN: The city is mostly stone; I don't know
if we can burn it down.

01:20:04.969 --> 01:20:08.332
MATT: As you're having this conversation, you do find a small
basin that's filled up with water. The people that

01:20:08.332 --> 01:20:13.939
live in this city still need to live. It looks
like there are the means of feeding and drinking,

01:20:14.014 --> 01:20:19.039
though you get the sense that they may or may
not-- most of the supplies do come from outside

01:20:19.039 --> 01:20:20.543
the Shadowfell.

01:20:20.543 --> 01:20:22.608
LAURA: Let's poison the water supply!

01:20:22.608 --> 01:20:28.468
MARISHA: I take a little bit of the water and
control it and let Pike wash off a little bit.

01:20:28.468 --> 01:20:29.649
MATT: Okay.

01:20:29.649 --> 01:20:33.643
ASHLEY: I think I got a little in my mouth
(gagging).

01:20:33.643 --> 01:20:38.038
LIAM: Wait, there's a little bit of skull right
there. All right.

01:20:38.038 --> 01:20:41.047
TALIESIN: That's the little chunk where the joint
is. It's just this little bit, it just breaks

01:20:41.047 --> 01:20:43.057
naturally if you put pressure on that side.

01:20:43.057 --> 01:20:49.080
MATT: There's this slumped pile of dark cloth,
thin body, and Riki-Oh mess on the ground.

01:20:49.080 --> 01:20:51.790
TALIESIN: (laughs) Wow! Way to bring that back!

01:20:51.790 --> 01:20:55.758
MATT: So, what's the plan, guys?

01:20:55.758 --> 01:20:59.342
TALIESIN: We've got a little shadow creature
coming back around in a moment.

01:20:59.342 --> 01:21:02.769
SAM: Want to jump on and do a scouting pass?

01:21:02.769 --> 01:21:05.757
LIAM: Yeah.

01:21:05.757 --> 01:21:07.968
TALIESIN: You guys do the scout, we'll heal?

01:21:07.968 --> 01:21:09.856
ASHLEY: You guys, are we not going to do a Heroes'
Feast?

01:21:09.856 --> 01:21:12.723
LAURA: It's an hour. It takes an hour, right?

01:21:12.723 --> 01:21:14.195
SAM: We can't risk it.

01:21:14.195 --> 01:21:18.193
LIAM: What do you think's going to happen in an
hour? Everything's going to kick off in an hour?

01:21:18.193 --> 01:21:21.051
SAM: Wouldn't you hate to miss it by 15 minutes?

01:21:21.051 --> 01:21:26.898
LAURA: The pulse has gotten stronger since we've
been here. I don't know if that pulse means it's

01:21:26.898 --> 01:21:29.759
about to go, or if the pulse means that it's five
minutes in.

01:21:29.759 --> 01:21:32.805
SAM: This guy was about to leave his house to go
walk over there for the final part of the ritual.

01:21:32.805 --> 01:21:36.093
MARISHA: Or he was trying to bail before the final
part of the ritual.

01:21:36.093 --> 01:21:39.140
LIAM: Where's your pet? Let's go find
some shit out.

01:21:39.140 --> 01:21:41.358
MARISHA: He had rations! No one takes rations!

01:21:41.410 --> 01:21:45.891
LAURA: He was handing out weapons.

01:21:45.891 --> 01:21:48.459
TALIESIN: It was like Carpentry of the Damned sort
of thing.

01:21:48.459 --> 01:21:51.937
MARISHA: What if the giant orb has to reach the
crystals?

01:21:51.937 --> 01:21:55.562
TALIESIN: It might, but it might just do the
(buzzing, exploding).

01:21:55.562 --> 01:21:58.329
LAURA: Technical terms.

01:21:58.329 --> 01:22:00.567
MARISHA: Yeah, the (buzzing, exploding).

01:22:00.567 --> 01:22:02.100
TALIESIN: It's magic, it's the best I've got.

01:22:02.100 --> 01:22:03.313
TRAVIS: Who's going up?

01:22:03.313 --> 01:22:05.753
SAM: Me and Vax.

01:22:05.753 --> 01:22:08.410
TRAVIS: Just you two, okay.

01:22:08.410 --> 01:22:10.886
ASHLEY: How's everybody doing right now?

01:22:10.962 --> 01:22:13.446
TALIESIN and MARISHA: I'm a little rough.

01:22:13.446 --> 01:22:15.448
TALIESIN: I could use 20 points.

01:22:15.448 --> 01:22:17.196
LAURA: Yeah, I could use 20 points.

01:22:17.196 --> 01:22:20.175
ASHLEY: Let's do a little Mass Cure Wounds
situation.

01:22:20.175 --> 01:22:21.466
MARISHA: Nice.

01:22:21.466 --> 01:22:26.982
TRAVIS: Do it!

01:22:26.982 --> 01:22:31.564
SAM: But do it with a flair!

01:22:31.564 --> 01:22:34.962
(laughter)

01:22:34.962 --> 01:22:37.693
ASHLEY: Oh, fudge.

01:22:37.693 --> 01:22:42.722
LAURA: What? Oh that's a one, not seven, isn't
it?

01:22:42.722 --> 01:22:45.012
ASHLEY: 13.

01:22:45.012 --> 01:22:47.067
LAURA: That's fine, that's fine!

01:22:47.067 --> 01:22:50.392
TALIESIN: We're taking a short rest; I can add
my--

01:22:50.392 --> 01:22:52.676
MATT: Are you guys taking a short rest?

01:22:52.676 --> 01:22:55.536
LAURA: Well, while they fly up, is it enough time
for the people staying

01:22:55.536 --> 01:22:57.080
in the house to heal a bit?

01:22:57.080 --> 01:23:02.050
MATT: You guys could take a short rest during that
time, if you want to do a full scoping. By the

01:23:02.050 --> 01:23:04.078
time you come back, that spell's about to fade.

01:23:04.078 --> 01:23:08.048
SAM: I mean, yeah, we're going to go as fast as we
can.

01:23:08.048 --> 01:23:11.035
MATT: So those that are traveling can't take a
short rest.

01:23:11.035 --> 01:23:15.305
TRAVIS: And if that fades, he's fully aware that
he was dominated, right?

01:23:15.305 --> 01:23:20.593
MATT: Well. You don't know.

01:23:20.593 --> 01:23:22.950
TRAVIS: Okay. Especially me.

01:23:22.950 --> 01:23:24.910
MATT: Yeah, you especially don't know.

01:23:24.910 --> 01:23:27.091
LIAM: Time's a-wasting, Scanlan, let's go.

01:23:27.091 --> 01:23:29.108
SAM: Let's go. Mr. Mistoffelees!

01:23:29.108 --> 01:23:42.292
MATT: As you open the door, there, just landing
(landing) (gloom stalker croaking). You guys climb

01:23:42.292 --> 01:23:43.316
onto its back?

01:23:43.316 --> 01:23:44.317
SAM: Yes, we do!

01:23:44.317 --> 01:23:48.291
MATT: You climb onto its back. Touching this
creature is like touching the inside of a freezer.

01:23:48.291 --> 01:23:53.914
Even with gauntleted hands, you have to wrap some
of your cloth around to not give yourself

01:23:53.914 --> 01:23:59.700
frostbite over a period of time. Even resting on
it, especially with your leather armors, it chills

01:23:59.700 --> 01:24:05.182
you to the bone. As you take up, and even just
ten, 15 minutes into (wings flapping) up into the

01:24:05.182 --> 01:24:09.717
air, gathering as to whether you'll be noticed or
spotted by this, you can feel it beginning to

01:24:09.717 --> 01:24:13.794
chill you, your teeth are beginning to chatter
