glowing spheres in a triangular pattern around
this that are accepting the tether of the magical

01:46:59.501 --> 01:47:04.700
energy, and then suffusing what appears to be a
small altar of some kind in the very center of the

01:47:04.700 --> 01:47:06.571
top of this tower.

01:47:06.571 --> 01:47:09.696
LIAM: Mother bitch.

01:47:09.696 --> 01:47:20.238
MATT: You've been circling here for about 15 to 20
minutes or so, and the energy (explosion noise)

01:47:20.238 --> 01:47:28.849
untethers and unfurls. There's a shockwave of
warmth that cascades outward from the top of the

01:47:28.849 --> 01:47:32.659
tower. Both of you feel it pass through you, and
that freezing cold that you've been trying

01:47:32.659 --> 01:47:38.522
desperately to hold at bay as you're clutching
onto the back of this gloom stalker, this heat

01:47:38.522 --> 01:47:44.779
wave moves past. The gloom stalker (squawks)
instinctually pulls back, and you can see for a

01:47:44.779 --> 01:47:50.014
second it drops, and you feel your stomach bottom
out as it loses about 20 feet of elevation before

01:47:50.014 --> 01:47:53.730
catching itself again. And you watch as any of the
others that are currently cycling around

01:47:53.730 --> 01:48:00.321
the stratosphere over the city of Thar Amphala
also are taken off guard by the sudden burst of

01:48:00.321 --> 01:48:08.584
energy. As you glance over, you can see the
tethers that connect have all fallen and faded.

01:48:08.584 --> 01:48:11.222
(music changes)

01:48:11.222 --> 01:48:14.318
SAM: (quietly) How does he do that? How did you do
that?

01:48:14.318 --> 01:48:22.131
MATT: You also watch as about 25 or so of these
figures at the top all collapse at once.

01:48:22.131 --> 01:48:24.810
LIAM: But some are left.

01:48:24.810 --> 01:48:30.906
MATT: There are some left. You watch and very
faintly, you can see on that altar in the center,

01:48:30.906 --> 01:48:38.413
there is a small bead of pure, vibrant, bright
white light. You watch as a robed figure that

01:48:38.413 --> 01:48:45.787
previously was held in the shadows emerge. You're
too far away to make any more details than that.

01:48:45.787 --> 01:48:52.220
LIAM: A lot of motherfuckers just died on the top
of that tower. You felt that?

01:48:52.220 --> 01:48:55.576
SAM: What do we do? Is that the end of the
ritual?

01:48:55.576 --> 01:48:58.815
LIAM: How much time left on that hour, buddy?

01:48:58.815 --> 01:49:02.034
SAM: Enough to get back to our friends, probably.

01:49:02.034 --> 01:49:03.515
LIAM: We've got to go.

01:49:03.515 --> 01:49:07.515
SAM: Should we attack now? Just the two of us?

01:49:07.515 --> 01:49:10.313
LIAM: No, we should not do that.

01:49:10.313 --> 01:49:11.508
SAM: We could.

01:49:11.508 --> 01:49:12.464
LIAM: We could.

01:49:12.464 --> 01:49:15.701
SAM: Between you and me, we're the most powerful
ones in the group.

01:49:15.701 --> 01:49:19.227
LIAM: I just don't feel like freeballing it right
now, and I'd really like the group.

01:49:19.227 --> 01:49:23.258
SAM: I know, but will you at least confirm that
yes, we are the most powerful?

01:49:23.258 --> 01:49:30.024
LIAM: Clearly. We are the most, as the kids say,
OP. Let's get back to the group.

01:49:30.024 --> 01:49:35.468
SAM: All right. Hold me tight. Mr. Mistoffeles,
back down.

01:49:35.468 --> 01:49:41.749
MATT: It goes into a rapid dive, making its way
back towards where you left the rest of your

01:49:41.749 --> 01:49:47.513
party. The rest of you, you can go ahead and
regain your short rest. You get your Wild Shape

01:49:47.513 --> 01:49:51.780
back. You can spend any hit dice to heal up if
you'd like. If you haven't already.

01:49:51.780 --> 01:49:53.475
LAURA: I already did it.

01:49:53.475 --> 01:49:56.363
MATT: Okay, good. I also need all of you to roll a
wisdom saving throw, please.

01:49:56.363 --> 01:49:58.047
SAM: Everybody?

01:49:58.047 --> 01:50:00.095
MATT: Everybody who was on a short rest.

01:50:00.095 --> 01:50:08.821
LAURA: If we had had a Feast, we'd have advantage
on this.

01:50:08.821 --> 01:50:10.718
MARISHA: We would.

01:50:10.718 --> 01:50:13.310
MATT: All right, so.

01:50:13.310 --> 01:50:14.940
TALIESIN: 14.

01:50:14.940 --> 01:50:16.443
MARISHA: 30.

01:50:16.443 --> 01:50:18.332
LAURA: 24.

01:50:18.332 --> 01:50:22.966
ASHLEY: Just to make sure: I used Gnome Cunning,
because I get advantage on wisdom.

01:50:22.966 --> 01:50:26.304
MATT: It's not a "magical" effect.

01:50:26.304 --> 01:50:33.924
ASHLEY: Okay. So then I'll take my first roll,
which was two. And then I will add my wisdom

01:50:33.924 --> 01:50:36.435
saving throw number, which is ten, so I have 12.

01:50:36.435 --> 01:50:38.298
TRAVIS: 19.

01:50:38.298 --> 01:50:41.473
SAM: I want you to explain every roll.

01:50:41.473 --> 01:50:47.267
MATT: In the rest you take, the Shadowfell does
not seem to have

01:50:47.267 --> 01:50:49.778
any adverse effect on your presence.

01:50:49.778 --> 01:50:52.610
TALIESIN: However...

01:50:52.610 --> 01:51:00.322
MATT: There's no "however." You complete your rest
fine. You guys all gather your stuff, you take a

01:51:00.322 --> 01:51:05.268
breath and prepare for the next leg of your
venture as the door to your building slams open,

01:51:05.268 --> 01:51:10.646
Scanlan and Vax arriving, just leaping off the
back of the gloom stalker that they had under

01:51:10.646 --> 01:51:13.933
their control. Who is also about to lose its...

01:51:13.933 --> 01:51:15.692
TALIESIN: How much longer do they have?

01:51:15.692 --> 01:51:17.152
SAM: Fly away!

01:51:17.152 --> 01:51:19.836
TALIESIN: Attack the tower. Tell it to attack the
tower.

01:51:19.836 --> 01:51:22.281
SAM: Really? It's going to forget halfway there.

01:51:22.281 --> 01:51:24.972
TALIESIN: Maybe we can mess one person up.

01:51:24.972 --> 01:51:27.678
SAM: Fly away! Just fly away!

01:51:27.678 --> 01:51:34.203
ASHLEY: On the rest, could I have worked a little
bit more on enchanting the silver bullets?

01:51:34.203 --> 01:51:39.913
MATT: You can spend a little more time on it.
It'll take a few days of getting that to happen.

01:51:39.913 --> 01:51:41.474
ASHLEY: I just keep working on it.

01:51:41.474 --> 01:51:45.516
LAURA: Did we feel that (whoosh) within the
building?

01:51:45.516 --> 01:51:48.777
MATT: You didn't. You may have heard something
strange, but it didn't really catch your

01:51:48.777 --> 01:51:51.647
attention. You guys spent your time resting on the
inside of the building.

01:51:51.647 --> 01:51:53.127
LAURA: What'd you see?

01:51:53.127 --> 01:51:59.292
LIAM: Saw a lot of fucking people just die on the
top of that tower. I can't guarantee it, but I

01:51:59.292 --> 01:52:03.115
think it's a safe bet that your girl Delilah is up
there.

01:52:03.115 --> 01:52:05.416
LAURA: That's where I figured she'd be.

01:52:05.416 --> 01:52:10.645
SAM: It seems they've completed at least some part
of the ritual.

01:52:10.645 --> 01:52:16.209
LIAM: Yeah, there was some sort of massive pulse
of energy, 20-something hooded figures just

01:52:16.209 --> 01:52:19.772
dropped dead on the spot. A wave of some shit
blasted through us.

01:52:19.772 --> 01:52:22.281
LAURA: Can I run out and look at the tower and see
if the orb looks different?

01:52:22.281 --> 01:52:23.884
MARISHA: I join Vex.

01:52:23.884 --> 01:52:27.974
MATT: You guys rush out and peek outside of the
doorway towards the top of Entropis. You see that

01:52:27.974 --> 01:52:34.091
the glowing pulse is gone. The energy tethers from
the siphons are gone.

01:52:34.091 --> 01:52:36.272
LAURA: Fuck.

01:52:36.272 --> 01:52:39.597
MARISHA: I look around. Are we still in the
Shadowfell?

01:52:39.597 --> 01:52:44.515
MATT: Perception check.

01:52:44.515 --> 01:52:50.681
MARISHA: That's not great. 18.

01:52:50.681 --> 01:52:52.598
MATT: That's enough. Yeah, you're still in the
Shadowfell.

01:52:52.598 --> 01:52:53.967
(sounds of relief)

01:52:53.967 --> 01:52:55.827
TRAVIS: Motherfucking Mercer. That intonation.

01:52:55.827 --> 01:53:01.307
TALIESIN: If you rolled low enough, he'd be like,
"You don't know." Seattle!

01:53:01.307 --> 01:53:03.264
You've taken us to Seattle!

01:53:03.264 --> 01:53:08.239
LAURA: Well, we should fucking get up there, then,
huh?

01:53:08.239 --> 01:53:09.975
SAM: Should we go straight up the tower?

01:53:09.975 --> 01:53:11.509
LIAM: What else are we doing here?

01:53:11.509 --> 01:53:12.922
SAM: Yeah, all right.

01:53:12.922 --> 01:53:14.277
TALIESIN: Let's head to the base.

01:53:14.277 --> 01:53:18.778
SAM: But we're going to fight an aerial battle
against super-magical things.

01:53:18.778 --> 01:53:20.344
MARISHA: Oh my god.

01:53:20.344 --> 01:53:23.321
LIAM: We're weighing risk here. What do we think
would happen if

01:53:23.321 --> 01:53:25.815
we spent an hour having that Feast right now?

01:53:25.815 --> 01:53:28.017
TRAVIS: Actually, that's true. Nothing's going to
change at this point.

01:53:28.017 --> 01:53:29.271
SAM: Maybe.

01:53:29.271 --> 01:53:35.236
MARISHA: I mean, maybe we should return to
something like sabotaging the machine, or...

01:53:35.236 --> 01:53:40.485
burning the city. Oh god, Vex is rubbing off on
me.

01:53:40.485 --> 01:53:42.482
LAURA: Did you see Delilah up there?

01:53:42.482 --> 01:53:45.631
LIAM: No. There was a ringleader, but we were too
far out.

01:53:45.631 --> 01:53:48.288
LAURA: And the ringleader was still standing?

01:53:48.288 --> 01:53:49.415
LIAM: Yeah.

01:53:49.415 --> 01:53:51.228
ASHLEY: How many people were still standing?

01:53:51.228 --> 01:53:53.471
MATT: That would have been three that you
noticed.

01:53:53.471 --> 01:53:54.911
LIAM: Precisely three.

01:53:54.911 --> 01:53:56.815
(laughter)

01:53:56.815 --> 01:54:01.470
ASHLEY: Lots of them died in the blast?

01:54:01.470 --> 01:54:03.634
SAM: Yeah, so it's not even going to be a tough
fight. We'll just

01:54:03.634 --> 01:54:05.773
take down three people and be done, right?

01:54:05.773 --> 01:54:07.016
LAURA: So easy.

01:54:07.016 --> 01:54:09.863
TALIESIN: The less people we're fighting, the
worse it is.

01:54:09.863 --> 01:54:10.989
MARISHA: Agreed.

01:54:10.989 --> 01:54:12.687
ASHLEY: It won't just be three.

01:54:12.687 --> 01:54:14.541
TALIESIN: It might be four.

01:54:14.541 --> 01:54:16.512
SAM: It'll be... less than three?

01:54:16.512 --> 01:54:22.218
LAURA: Even one with that fucking wall she had
last time, we're fucked.

01:54:22.218 --> 01:54:26.543
MARISHA: How far did the blast go that you saw?

01:54:26.543 --> 01:54:28.586
LIAM: We were 100 yards out or something?

01:54:28.586 --> 01:54:31.869
MATT: Yeah, you were probably about 300 feet out.

01:54:31.869 --> 01:54:38.225
LAURA: We didn't do any research on that wall, did
we? That spell? Did anybody do any research on

01:54:38.225 --> 01:54:41.018
that spell that we saw her do? Down in the
ziggurat?

01:54:41.018 --> 01:54:43.977
TALIESIN: We kind of figured out what it was. It
was a modified version

01:54:43.977 --> 01:54:45.635
of a spell we've seen before.

01:54:45.635 --> 01:54:50.424
MATT: Kind of, yeah. It seemed to be prismatic.
You've seen Prismatic Spray. It's a prismatic

01:54:50.424 --> 01:54:56.614
spell in nature but you didn't really research any
means of defeating it or bypassing it.

01:54:56.614 --> 01:54:59.181
TRAVIS: Do you still have that Earthquake spell?

01:54:59.181 --> 01:55:02.065
MARISHA: I believe me and Pike both do, yes.

01:55:02.065 --> 01:55:06.235
TRAVIS: We couldn't, like, earthquake the tower to the
ground. Could we?

01:55:06.286 --> 01:55:10.155
MARISHA: Between me, you, and Pike? We can take
this tower down.

01:55:10.155 --> 01:55:11.471
SAM: Is that true?

01:55:11.471 --> 01:55:14.094
TRAVIS: I just don't know about us going to the
top, if we could maybe bring it--

01:55:14.094 --> 01:55:16.138
TALIESIN: Oh, if we could maybe bring the top down
here?

01:55:16.138 --> 01:55:21.154
SAM: That's a good idea, if you can really do it.

01:55:21.154 --> 01:55:22.930
TRAVIS: I just don't know how big around it is. It
might be fucking huge.

01:55:22.930 --> 01:55:24.705
TALIESIN: How big around is the tower?

01:55:24.705 --> 01:55:26.896
MATT: At the very base--

01:55:26.896 --> 01:55:35.344
TALIESIN: He's looking at the tower.

01:55:35.344 --> 01:55:44.545
MATT: -- it's about 170, 180 feet in diameter.

01:55:44.545 --> 01:55:56.093
MARISHA: Hang on, 180 feet in diameter? Hang on.
Pike and I check our spellbooks real quick.

01:55:56.093 --> 01:56:00.653
TALIESIN: Can I do a little engineering? If I were
going to punch at it...

01:56:00.653 --> 01:56:06.893
LIAM: Also, the idea that we're going to sneak
into that tower is farfetched.

01:56:06.893 --> 01:56:09.883
SAM: No, we either have to fly up to the top or
bring it down to us, right?

01:56:09.883 --> 01:56:11.564
LAURA: I like the idea of bringing it down.

01:56:11.564 --> 01:56:15.803
LIAM: Even if it fails, the fight will still come
to-- Either we bring the fight to them, or we rip

01:56:15.803 --> 01:56:17.652
down the tower and bring the fight to us.

01:56:17.652 --> 01:56:21.062
MARISHA: For up to a minute and a hundred foot
radius, centered at a point...

01:56:21.062 --> 01:56:25.696
MATT: It deals 50 bludgeoning damage to any
structure in contact with the ground in the area

01:56:25.696 --> 01:56:29.303
when you cast the spell. If it drops to zero hit
points, it collapses and potentially damages

01:56:29.303 --> 01:56:35.756
nearby creatures. So the question is, do you think
that'll be enough to drop a solid obsidian tower?

01:56:35.756 --> 01:56:39.296
LAURA: It's a tough call. Twice in a row?

01:56:39.296 --> 01:56:42.201
MARISHA: But, I mean, two Earthquake spells and
Grog.

01:56:42.201 --> 01:56:44.908
LAURA: I have a siege arrow.

01:56:44.908 --> 01:56:50.263
MARISHA: I will point out this will be burning
mine and Pike's 8th-level spell,

01:56:50.263 --> 01:56:52.714
but it might be worth it.

01:56:52.714 --> 01:57:00.833
SAM: It feels like it's a 3.2 earthquake, we need
a 6.2 earthquake.

01:57:00.833 --> 01:57:05.891
TRAVIS: That's true, we do. Let's be honest. We
really do need a massive shake.

01:57:05.891 --> 01:57:09.257
LAURA: What if we weaken the outside and then hit
with the earthquake?

01:57:09.257 --> 01:57:11.395
MARISHA: I can tunnel out underneath it.

01:57:11.395 --> 01:57:18.337
TALIESIN: I think whatever was going on up there is
gone. I think it's happened.

01:57:18.337 --> 01:57:22.365
LAURA: Well, Delilah's still up there, so if she
falls at least she takes some damage.

01:57:22.365 --> 01:57:24.136
TALIESIN: That's fair.

01:57:24.136 --> 01:57:33.727
LIAM: I'm just going to throw my vote in the ring
here, that I think we should take the time for the

01:57:33.727 --> 01:57:41.180
Feast. You know, we're not killing piles of rats
in the sewers, here. This is serious.

01:57:41.180 --> 01:57:46.947
SAM: When last time we fought Delilah, were any of
us scared of her?

01:57:46.947 --> 01:57:49.618
TALIESIN: She's not what I'm afraid of.

01:57:49.618 --> 01:57:54.307
LAURA: Wisdom saving throws are major. She could
take control of us.

01:57:54.307 --> 01:58:01.102
TRAVIS: I'm not against that, but I think one
person should stay out of the Feast and keep an

01:58:01.102 --> 01:58:04.496
eye in case they leave in the hour that we're
feasting.

01:58:04.496 --> 01:58:07.918
SAM: Well, if someone's going to stay out of the
Feast, it should be the guy who already has

01:58:07.918 --> 01:58:09.257
advantage on everything.

01:58:09.257 --> 01:58:12.058
TRAVIS: Oh, that too, yeah. I just can't get
afraid, that's all I was going to say.

01:58:12.058 --> 01:58:14.848
LAURA: Yeah, but you can be taken control of with
your brain, Grog.

01:58:14.848 --> 01:58:16.857
TRAVIS: That's assuming a lot.

01:58:16.857 --> 01:58:19.867
TALIESIN: Damn it.

01:58:19.867 --> 01:58:21.538
ASHLEY: Shit.

01:58:21.538 --> 01:58:25.095
TRAVIS: Or we just go get it. We just go after it
and go get it.

01:58:25.095 --> 01:58:28.818
SAM: I'm against the Feast. I think we should just
run in.

01:58:28.818 --> 01:58:31.536
LAURA: I just don't feel like there's time,
honestly.

01:58:31.536 --> 01:58:35.344
SAM: Also, I'm vegan, I don't know if I could eat
everything at the feast.

01:58:35.344 --> 01:58:40.260
LIAM: It is largely GoFiBePo?

01:58:40.260 --> 01:58:47.572
SAM: GoFiBePo? Why didn't you just name it a Poobah
Platter?

01:58:47.572 --> 01:58:49.917
LAURA: Oh, that would have been way easier.

01:58:49.917 --> 01:58:53.941
MARISHA: How far are we from the tower in this
little house?

01:58:53.941 --> 01:59:00.854
MATT: In this house, you're a little over a half
mile away from it.

01:59:00.854 --> 01:59:05.081
TALIESIN: It's a ten-minute walk.

01:59:05.081 --> 01:59:07.974
MATT: So this house is just outside of the
perimeter wall of the inner cloister.

01:59:07.974 --> 01:59:12.759
MARISHA: You guys could do the Feast and some of
us can help tunnel out

01:59:12.759 --> 01:59:14.866
the ground during that hour.

01:59:14.866 --> 01:59:21.092
TALIESIN: I don't know. I don't think we're going
to bring it down.

01:59:21.092 --> 01:59:23.354
GROG: I don't know if we're going to bring it
down. It was a cool idea, but I don't know if we're

01:59:23.354 --> 01:59:25.718
going to do it. We're no white ancient dragon.

01:59:25.765 --> 01:59:27.330
ASHLEY: What's it made of? Obsidian?

01:59:27.330 --> 01:59:30.503
MATT: You haven't been close enough to really
tell, but it looks to be made of a very thick,

01:59:30.503 --> 01:59:34.051
dark obsidian or onyx-like material.

01:59:34.051 --> 01:59:36.372
LIAM: It's also unsettling as fuck, right?

01:59:36.372 --> 01:59:38.530
LAURA: Oh, it's probably magically protected.

01:59:38.530 --> 01:59:40.085
LIAM: Probably.

01:59:40.085 --> 01:59:42.372
TALIESIN: It may just hover there if we knock
this.

01:59:42.372 --> 01:59:44.271
LAURA: That is very true.

01:59:44.271 --> 01:59:47.773
TALIESIN: It may be keeping the ground up as
opposed to being sitting

01:59:47.773 --> 01:59:49.431
on the ground at that point.

01:59:49.431 --> 01:59:51.129
MARISHA: So we're going to try to fly up?

01:59:51.129 --> 01:59:52.373
TALIESIN: Or walk up through the inside.

01:59:52.373 --> 01:59:54.847
GROG: Raise your hand if you want a Heroes'
Feast.

01:59:54.847 --> 01:59:56.834
LIAM: For you all, yes.

01:59:56.834 --> 01:59:58.737
TRAVIS: Four?

01:59:58.737 --> 02:00:00.266
SAM: Is that a raise or not?

02:00:00.266 --> 02:00:01.677
TRAVIS: Are you scratching your ear or are you
raising your hand?

02:00:01.677 --> 02:00:03.937
TALIESIN: Yes, damn it.

02:00:03.937 --> 02:00:05.976
SAM: Wait, so, are we four?

02:00:05.976 --> 02:00:09.901
ASHLEY: I'm just nervous. I know we don't have
time, but what if this is one of those decisions

02:00:09.901 --> 02:00:12.270
where later we're like "We should have fucking
done a Heroes' Feast"?

02:00:12.270 --> 02:00:13.521
TRAVIS: Well, let's do it.

02:00:13.521 --> 02:00:17.018
ASHLEY: I don't know, though, I don't know if we
have the time. This is hard.

02:00:17.018 --> 02:00:20.379
TRAVIS: Well, the transaction upstairs has already
happened, whether they get away or not.

02:00:20.379 --> 02:00:22.969
MARISHA: I have a feeling we're going to be down
here a while.

02:00:22.969 --> 02:00:29.941
LAURA: Maybe we can prepare the Feast, keep an eye
out. If we have to ditch out on the Feast early,

02:00:29.941 --> 02:00:31.097
then we do.

02:00:31.097 --> 02:00:35.128
MARISHA: Keyleth looks out the window again. Are
people panicked, are people running around? Is

02:00:35.128 --> 02:00:36.745
there a rabble in the street?

02:00:36.745 --> 02:00:40.513
MATT: There's no technical window in this
building. There's the door.

02:00:40.513 --> 02:00:42.215
TRAVIS: She just pushes her head against the
wall.

02:00:42.215 --> 02:00:52.217
MATT: So you look out the door and glance through.
You do notice, there's no panic, but you do see a

02:00:52.217 --> 02:00:57.508
number of-- and this is interesting-- you glance
out, and you don't see any undead wandering the

02:00:57.508 --> 02:01:03.551
streets of the inner cloister. At least, not like
the outer area was. You do see-- make a perception

02:01:03.551 --> 02:01:07.062
check, actually.

02:01:07.062 --> 02:01:10.489
MARISHA: Oh, that's good! 30!

02:01:10.489 --> 02:01:15.206
MATT: You see, throughout the street, which, the
street from here gets about halfway to the tower

02:01:15.206 --> 02:01:23.870
before it hits a building and curves around. You
see maybe 35 or 40 total people in matching or

02:01:23.870 --> 02:01:28.381
close cultist robes or similar colors, all making
their way towards the tower.

02:01:28.381 --> 02:01:32.221
TALIESIN: They're dressed for an occasion. Fuck
it. Just go.

02:01:32.221 --> 02:01:35.963
LAURA: We got to go. 35 to 40 people? Let's kill
'em all on the way up.

02:01:35.963 --> 02:01:41.068
MARISHA: Man, you're frosty today. You're just--

02:01:41.068 --> 02:01:44.486
LAURA: They're trying to come over into our
territory. I don't like it. They're all assholes.

02:01:44.486 --> 02:01:46.037
TRAVIS: Shall we go in?

02:01:46.037 --> 02:01:48.623
MARISHA: Well, how are we going to go in, though?
Just flying up?

02:01:48.623 --> 02:01:51.894
TALIESIN: We have one broom, we don't have two
brooms anymore.

02:01:51.894 --> 02:01:54.896
We got a carpet, and we got wings.

02:01:54.896 --> 02:02:00.869
LAURA: And a couple people with wings. Oh god,
the creepy music is starting.

02:02:00.869 --> 02:02:03.603
We gotta go, y'all.

02:02:03.603 --> 02:02:04.865
LIAM: Beeline to the tower.

02:02:04.865 --> 02:02:08.061
MARISHA: And then what? And then what, though?
Once we get there? Play it by ear?

02:02:08.061 --> 02:02:13.769
TALIESIN: Throw everything off the top. Break
everything. Smash everything.

02:02:13.769 --> 02:02:18.541
LAURA: It's Delilah. She's going to destroy us. Do
we have any way to neutralize her magic?

02:02:18.541 --> 02:02:24.184
TRAVIS: Well, you could turn into a... no.

02:02:24.184 --> 02:02:31.238
MARISHA: I can't. I gave Vax Foresight. I cannot
turn into a beholder today.

02:02:31.238 --> 02:02:32.605
SAM: I can.

02:02:32.605 --> 02:02:34.092
TALIESIN: You can?

02:02:34.092 --> 02:02:35.436
SAM: Yes.

02:02:35.436 --> 02:02:37.613
MARISHA: Do you have Shapechange?

02:02:37.613 --> 02:02:39.407
SAM: Something like it.

02:02:39.407 --> 02:02:41.438
(gasping)

02:02:41.438 --> 02:02:44.300
TALIESIN: All right, this is almost a plan. Let's
do this.

02:02:44.300 --> 02:02:45.658
TRAVIS: It's more than we normally have.

02:02:45.658 --> 02:02:47.186
TALIESIN: It's far more.

02:02:47.186 --> 02:02:49.760
LAURA: Are there a lot of gloom stalkers around?

02:02:49.760 --> 02:03:00.843
MATT: You can tell with the loss of magical energy
that they've been tossed askew a bit. Their

02:03:00.843 --> 02:03:05.630
patterns of circling and being intent, they're a
little more scattered a bit, but there are still

02:03:05.630 --> 02:03:11.057
maybe a few dozen that look over the inner
cloister.

02:03:11.057 --> 02:03:15.038
TALIESIN: Let's make our way to the tower and
maybe head up through the tower. We don't have to

02:03:15.038 --> 02:03:17.098
necessarily fly up to the top.

02:03:17.098 --> 02:03:25.862
LAURA: Wait a minute. Did the orb at the top turn
the same way that the orbs in the ziggurat turn?

02:03:25.862 --> 02:03:34.486
MATT: There were faint orbs that were taking the
energy and focusing it towards that center altar,

02:03:34.486 --> 02:03:40.808
and when everything faded after the shock wave,
what you saw looked like the tiniest star. It was

02:03:40.808 --> 02:03:46.619
just a speck of extremely bright light that to
look directly at it hurt.

02:03:46.619 --> 02:03:51.496
TRAVIS: I don't know! I don't! Just go get it.

02:03:51.496 --> 02:03:56.340
MARISHA: I'm honestly still kind of into the
earthquake idea. Bringing down the tower. I'm not

02:03:56.340 --> 02:03:57.355
going to lie.

02:03:57.355 --> 02:03:58.491
SAM: That's not going to work!

02:03:58.491 --> 02:03:59.546
MARISHA: How do you know?

02:03:59.546 --> 02:04:01.228
SAM: You said 50 points of damage?

02:04:01.228 --> 02:04:05.845
TALIESIN: I can take 50 points of damage. I can
take two earthquakes, personally.

02:04:05.845 --> 02:04:09.499
SAM: I mean, just from a metagaming scenario,
that's not even-- that can't even hurt--

02:04:09.499 --> 02:04:13.404
MARISHA: No, no, no. The tremor deals 50
bludgeoning damage to any structure in contact

02:04:13.404 --> 02:04:17.704
with the ground in your area when you cast the
spell, and at the start of each of your turns

02:04:17.704 --> 02:04:20.745
until the spell ends, and the spell lasts a
minute.

02:04:20.745 --> 02:04:23.050
SAM: So you get ten 50s.

02:04:23.050 --> 02:04:24.813
MARISHA: Ten of those. Ten 50s.

02:04:24.813 --> 02:04:26.236
LAURA: Oh, and then times two.

02:04:26.236 --> 02:04:27.793
MARISHA: With Pike and I.

02:04:27.793 --> 02:04:32.850
SAM: So that's 1000 points. Over a minute. That's
better than I thought.

02:04:32.850 --> 02:04:34.455
LIAM: Is it concentration?

02:04:34.455 --> 02:04:40.150
MARISHA: It's concentration for up to a minute,
and it has a 500-foot range, and a 100-foot

02:04:40.150 --> 02:04:45.062
radius. So Pike and I could split, half and half
of the tower.

02:04:45.062 --> 02:04:47.965
TRAVIS: It's pretty fucking Hollywood. I kind of
like it.

02:04:47.965 --> 02:04:49.960
TALIESIN: All right! All right, let's do it.

02:04:49.960 --> 02:04:54.162
MARISHA: I feel like if we go right up to the top
of the tower, it's like walking into the danger.

02:04:54.162 --> 02:04:57.498
TALIESIN: Let's bring the tower down to us.

02:04:57.498 --> 02:05:00.751
MARISHA: This is insane!

02:05:00.751 --> 02:05:04.379
LIAM: And you can still fuck shit up while you got
that earthquake going, right?

02:05:04.379 --> 02:05:06.865
MARISHA: Well, how do you mean?

02:05:06.865 --> 02:05:11.249
LAURA: Oh, yeah, if you have that spell going, you
can do other things in case things attack us?

02:05:11.249 --> 02:05:13.964
LIAM: Are you just doing Earthquake the whole
time, or are you just standing there staring at

02:05:13.964 --> 02:05:15.203
the ground?

02:05:15.203 --> 02:05:19.656
MARISHA: It's my concentration, so I can keep it
going and do an instant reaction spell.

02:05:19.656 --> 02:05:22.302
MATT: Do other things, you can't do another
concentration spell.

02:05:22.302 --> 02:05:24.735
LIAM: But you're not lightning anybody's ass, not
doing anything like that.

02:05:24.735 --> 02:05:26.032
You're focusing on the tower.

02:05:26.032 --> 02:05:28.800
MARISHA: I mean, I can throw a Fireball and keep
it going, yeah.

02:05:28.800 --> 02:05:31.458
LIAM: That's really big. All right.

02:05:31.458 --> 02:05:35.449
TALIESIN: I say the movers and shakers get the
cloaks. Let's head out.

02:05:35.449 --> 02:05:40.400
LAURA: Get up as close as we can to support Pike
and Keyleth.

02:05:40.400 --> 02:05:43.607
TALIESIN: And we keep them safe. We are playing
defense.

02:05:43.607 --> 02:05:44.627
LAURA: Yes.

02:05:44.627 --> 02:05:45.908
MARISHA: God, I hope this works.

02:05:45.908 --> 02:05:47.031
TALIESIN: God, I hope this works, too.

02:05:47.031 --> 02:05:48.409
MARISHA: I don't know if this is going to work!

02:05:48.409 --> 02:05:49.853
LAURA: This is stupid as fuck!

02:05:49.853 --> 02:05:54.118
TALIESIN: We're distance. Anybody gets near them,
we take them out.

02:05:54.118 --> 02:05:58.594
MARISHA: Grog, can you at the right moment just do
a big-- see if you can topple it over?

02:05:58.594 --> 02:06:01.401
TRAVIS: I can try and do whatever you want. I can
run around and punch

02:06:01.401 --> 02:06:03.044
a bunch of holes in it, whatever.

02:06:03.044 --> 02:06:08.508
TALIESIN: We're going to focus everything on one
side of the tower, we're going to try and bring it

02:06:08.508 --> 02:06:11.253
down in a direction. Here we go.

02:06:11.253 --> 02:06:15.227
LAURA: Yes, focus it on one side of the tower.
Both on the same side.

02:06:15.227 --> 02:06:23.749
TALIESIN: Like a tree. Let's do this. This is a
terrible plan. All right.

02:06:23.749 --> 02:06:25.499
LAURA Just trying to gauge Matt.

02:06:25.499 --> 02:06:27.413
MARISHA: I know! Matt's stone cold!

02:06:27.413 --> 02:06:30.049
TALIESIN: Matt's thinking about all the other
people he could be playing D&amp;D with right now.

02:06:30.049 --> 02:06:33.817
(laughing)

02:06:33.817 --> 02:06:36.101
TALIESIN: He's imagining a whole other set of
faces here.

02:06:36.101 --> 02:06:39.575
LIAM: All right, let's teleport inside that
dragon. Come on.

02:06:39.575 --> 02:06:41.154
MATT: Yeah, what's the plan, guys?

02:06:41.154 --> 02:06:42.246
LIAM: That's the plan.

02:06:42.246 --> 02:06:46.820
LAURA: We're going to get close enough so that
they can do their 500 feet distance. But keep a

02:06:46.820 --> 02:06:48.061
distance to the tower.

02:06:48.061 --> 02:06:52.638
MARISHA: And if we can be hidden while we're doing
this, instead of being open. We have a 500-foot

02:06:52.638 --> 02:06:55.568
range here. We've got a dope-ass range.

02:06:55.568 --> 02:06:57.101
TALIESIN: Keyleth's got a cloak. Pike's got a
cloak.

02:06:57.101 --> 02:06:59.503
TRAVIS: I'm huge.

02:06:59.503 --> 02:07:00.664
TALIESIN: He's huge.

02:07:00.664 --> 02:07:04.070
LAURA: We're going to try to get in a building
that's closer to the tower.

02:07:04.070 --> 02:07:08.678
MATT: Okay. Seeming lasts for eight hours, so
you're still under the guise of that illusion.

02:07:08.678 --> 02:07:11.199
SAM: Although we don't--

02:07:11.199 --> 02:07:12.613
LAURA: -- need that anymore.

02:07:12.613 --> 02:07:13.953
TALIESIN: Well, we can look like cultists.

02:07:13.953 --> 02:07:20.358
SAM: Keyleth, you said that there's no other
undead around here, right? Maybe we shouldn't look

02:07:20.358 --> 02:07:21.703
like undead, then.

02:07:21.703 --> 02:07:23.862
TALIESIN: Can you shift what we look like without
changing it?

02:07:23.862 --> 02:07:29.331
SAM: I don't think I can shift it. No, you can't.
That's a one-time thing.

02:07:29.331 --> 02:07:32.570
LAURA: Maybe just drop it and we'll be cultists.

02:07:32.570 --> 02:07:34.312
MARISHA: How many robes did we swipe?

02:07:34.312 --> 02:07:37.490
SAM: We've got the one from the guy whose head we
just crushed.

02:07:37.490 --> 02:07:41.519
MATT: You would have four cloaks, because there's
two you got from the outside at the ritual, and

02:07:41.519 --> 02:07:47.257
there's the one from the guy you killed when you
got here. Well, technically, there was the two

02:07:47.257 --> 02:07:51.273
that you killed when you got there, but you didn't
say you grabbed those. Oh, you did, you grabbed

02:07:51.273 --> 02:07:55.195
them off. So that's two, five, six. You have six
cloaks.

02:07:55.195 --> 02:07:57.360
LAURA: Yeah, and then the one, the guy that we
just killed in front of the --

02:07:57.360 --> 02:07:58.388
MATT: That was included.

02:07:58.388 --> 02:08:00.597
SAM: Me and Pike, she could be on my shoulders and
we could share one cloak.

02:08:00.597 --> 02:08:02.154
LAURA: Yeah! That's good!

02:08:02.154 --> 02:08:04.362
TRAVIS: I have that Cloak of Smashing that Percy
gave me.

02:08:04.362 --> 02:08:07.058
MARISHA: Totally 'Little Rascals' it! Oh, I love
it!

02:08:07.058 --> 02:08:08.659
LAURA: Yeah, we'll just robe it up.

02:08:08.659 --> 02:08:11.811
MATT: You guys all throw on the--

02:08:11.811 --> 02:08:13.609
ASHLEY: I almost feel like it should be the other
way around.

02:08:13.609 --> 02:08:15.057
SAM: Oh, it absolutely should.

02:08:15.057 --> 02:08:18.569
(laughter)

02:08:18.569 --> 02:08:32.459
MATT: Six cloaks, seven players. You guys are
straight-up doing-- I am so proud of everything

02:08:32.459 --> 02:08:34.623
that has just happened.

02:08:34.623 --> 02:08:39.776
(laughter)

02:08:39.776 --> 02:08:43.568
SAM: To make it look like our arms can reach the
ends of the cloak-- are they sleeved cloaks?

02:08:43.568 --> 02:08:44.672
MATT: Yes, they are.

02:08:44.672 --> 02:08:46.500
SAM: I'm going to hold a flute and my sword.

02:08:46.500 --> 02:08:48.929
(laughing)

02:08:48.929 --> 02:08:51.574
LIAM: Mythcarver! You used Mythcarver to pull a
Little Rascals!

02:08:51.574 --> 02:08:55.359
MATT: "There will be no survivors!"

02:08:55.359 --> 02:08:59.857
TALIESIN: "The dread Pirate Roberts is here for
your souls!"

02:08:59.857 --> 02:09:01.860
LIAM: Hey guys, it's the third time Scanlan has
used Mythcarver!

02:09:01.860 --> 02:09:04.343
(laughter)

02:09:04.343 --> 02:09:06.255
MARISHA: That's a vestige right there!

02:09:06.255 --> 02:09:11.363
TALIESIN: It's gone from exalted to shamed.

02:09:11.363 --> 02:09:14.563
MATT: It retracts into a dagger now.

02:09:14.563 --> 02:09:17.943
TALIESIN: Never happens. This never happens.

02:09:17.943 --> 02:09:26.614
MATT: All right. In a hip montage, you pull out
the various cloaks, assemble your materials,

02:09:26.614 --> 02:09:28.205
getting ready.

02:09:28.205 --> 02:09:30.220
TALIESIN: We are a bunch of assholes.

02:09:30.220 --> 02:09:34.951
MATT: Scanlan hops on top of Pike, the cloak is
placed over you. You get your sleeves ready, and

02:09:34.951 --> 02:09:42.442
you all walk out into the cold air of the
Shadowfell, making your way

02:09:42.442 --> 02:09:44.956
towards the center of the city.

02:09:44.956 --> 02:09:48.400
MARISHA: Be cool. Be cool.

02:09:48.400 --> 02:09:52.367
LIAM: I'm also going to say, some time in the last
several hours, I don't remember what the armor is

02:09:52.367 --> 02:09:54.241
set to, to necrotic.

02:09:54.241 --> 02:09:57.134
MATT: I think you may have said that before you
went in, just in case.

02:09:57.134 --> 02:09:58.566
I assumed that was the case.

02:09:58.566 --> 02:09:59.921
LAURA: I think that was already there, yeah.

02:09:59.921 --> 02:10:03.568
TALIESIN: And remember, if anyone looks at you,
close one eye. Just be winking.

02:10:03.568 --> 02:10:08.301
Always be winking. Left eye.

02:10:08.301 --> 02:10:12.501
LAURA: Does everybody have their arms, that we've
run into so far? Or are they missing an arm, too?

02:10:12.501 --> 02:10:14.036
An eye and an arm or just an eye?

02:10:14.036 --> 02:10:18.246
MATT: It varies. Not everyone seems to be missing
a hand, but most of them are missing an eye.

02:10:18.246 --> 02:10:19.487
LAURA: Okay.

02:10:19.487 --> 02:10:21.912
LIAM: You all look like my sister.

02:10:21.912 --> 02:10:28.466
MARISHA: You need to get your eyes checked, then.
Your depth perception may be off.

02:10:28.466 --> 02:10:31.969
SAM: All right, we go!

02:10:31.969 --> 02:10:41.920
MATT: All right. You guys make your way up the
street, following behind the few stragglers that

02:10:41.920 --> 02:10:47.051
you see trying to catch up with the rest of the
groups of people that have filtered out of the

02:10:47.051 --> 02:10:51.009
buildings and made their way towards the center.
You make your way through some of the side roads,

02:10:51.009 --> 02:10:55.052
following around, and you can see now that the
closer you get to the city, the more the

02:10:55.052 --> 02:11:01.367
structures, the buildings here, are built in a
spiral. The roads don't intersect at spokes, they

02:11:01.367 --> 02:11:05.729
all gradually curve in to the tower. If you're
looking at it overhead, it looks like this large

02:11:05.729 --> 02:11:13.455
spiral into the tower, like a pinwheel. You follow
the curvature of the road, which prevents you from

02:11:13.455 --> 02:11:17.969
seeing the end point, and as you begin to get
close to some of the clusters of people that are

02:11:17.969 --> 02:11:23.496
walking with a brisk walk, but still walking
towards the tower, you fall back a little bit to

02:11:23.496 --> 02:11:29.369
not draw any attention. As you're making your way
there, you watch as two individuals hurry up that

02:11:29.369 --> 02:11:34.947
were a little bit behind you, and rush up to the
side and are walking in pace. They glance over.

02:11:34.947 --> 02:11:42.662
MARISHA: Hoods forward.

02:11:42.662 --> 02:11:50.515
MATT: One of them, who appears to be a younger
man, probably 18, 19 or so, who's got this little

02:11:50.515 --> 02:11:59.853
patch of reddish brown chin fuzz and looks a
little malnourished. He still has both eyes. He

02:11:59.853 --> 02:12:04.047
rushes up real fast, his hood pulling back a
little bit, and he's looking around, excited but

02:12:04.047 --> 02:12:10.952
also with trepidation. "So it's happening, huh?
It's really happening!"

02:12:10.952 --> 02:12:12.392
LAURA: I guess so.

02:12:12.392 --> 02:12:14.323
LIAM: It's fucking wild.

02:12:14.323 --> 02:12:15.995
LAURA: So exciting.

02:12:15.995 --> 02:12:18.541
SAM: I'm so excited to be here!

02:12:18.541 --> 02:12:19.721
LAURA: Oh, don't.

02:12:19.721 --> 02:12:21.844
MATT: Make a deception check.

02:12:21.844 --> 02:12:25.049
TRAVIS: Keep your mouth shut! Just keep your mouth
shut!

02:12:25.049 --> 02:12:27.550
MARISHA: Just nod and smile.

02:12:27.550 --> 02:12:29.894
SAM: 24.

02:12:29.894 --> 02:12:43.409
MATT: He looks at you and goes, "Oh! I didn't know
the Whispered One takes the special ones, too!"

02:12:43.409 --> 02:12:45.450
TRAVIS: Yep! Sure does!

02:12:45.450 --> 02:12:49.014
TALIESIN: What are you going to do after?

02:12:49.014 --> 02:12:50.827
MATT: "I don't know."

02:12:50.827 --> 02:12:53.452
TALIESIN: Surely you've thought.

02:12:53.452 --> 02:13:01.307
MATT: "I'm pretty low on the totem pole here. I'm
just excited to be on the right side of history."

02:13:01.307 --> 02:13:05.095
LAURA: Ditto.

02:13:05.095 --> 02:13:08.294
LIAM: Fuck the normies.

02:13:08.294 --> 02:13:12.858
MATT: "All right." And he rushes up past you guys
to try and catch up.

02:13:12.858 --> 02:13:14.306
SAM: So awkward.

02:13:14.306 --> 02:13:18.320
LAURA: I think he bought it. I think we played it
really cool there, guys.

02:13:18.320 --> 02:13:21.577
MARISHA: I'm really bad at holding my eye shut for
this long.

02:13:21.577 --> 02:13:25.861
TALIESIN: So are we close enough now that we can
start this?

02:13:25.861 --> 02:13:29.689
MATT: Not yet. You're about maybe 1,000 feet or so
away.

02:13:29.689 --> 02:13:32.162
TALIESIN: I'm going to see if there's any
structures that are within distance so that once

02:13:32.162 --> 02:13:35.168
they set up and start, I can get to them. Maybe we
can perch.

02:13:35.168 --> 02:13:37.474
MARISHA: We only need to be so far out.

02:13:37.474 --> 02:13:40.126
TALIESIN: We can cover you from a roof.

02:13:40.126 --> 02:13:41.815
MATT: Perception check, Percival.

02:13:41.815 --> 02:13:44.634
LIAM: Also wondering how we're doing in the gloom
stalker department?

02:13:44.634 --> 02:13:51.103
MATT: No one's seen you, currently. It seems that
whatever piercing vision they have, it does not

02:13:51.103 --> 02:13:52.422
seem to pierce robes.

02:13:52.422 --> 02:13:54.579
LAURA: I want to keep an eye out for buildings,
too.

02:13:54.579 --> 02:13:56.072
TALIESIN: 15.

02:13:56.072 --> 02:13:58.270
MATT: Okay. Then you as well make a perception
check.

02:13:58.270 --> 02:13:59.916
TALIESIN: Please.

02:13:59.916 --> 02:14:04.769
LAURA: 23.

02:14:04.769 --> 02:14:11.117
MATT: 23. Okay. You glance about, and there are a
lot of buildings here with vantage points. They're

02:14:11.117 --> 02:14:17.176
all similar heights. There are a few that are
outliers, but most of them are one and a half to

