beholder. (goofy voice) Hi!

02:32:35.996 --> 02:32:39.281
ASHLEY and MARISHA: Hey, you guys!

02:32:39.281 --> 02:32:51.349
MATT: As you guys arrive, the floor is just
surrounded in bodies. Cultists of very ornate

02:32:51.349 --> 02:32:56.965
robes. Mostly you've seen peon-based: black
splatters of sackcloth, what was available.

02:32:56.965 --> 02:32:58.703
LAURA: They've been &lt;i&gt;peed&lt;/i&gt; on?!

02:32:58.703 --> 02:33:05.946
MATT: No. these are well-adorned and appear to
have been very well-regarded within the Remnants.

02:33:05.946 --> 02:33:15.075
You also see, on this side, what appears to be--
sorry, on this side would be Delilah Briarwood.

02:33:15.075 --> 02:33:16.981
LAURA: Bitchface Briarwood.

02:33:16.981 --> 02:33:18.773
MARISHA: Bitchface Briarwood!

02:33:18.773 --> 02:33:27.816
MATT: On this side, you see what appears to be a
black, armored, massive, not quite goliath-sized,

02:33:27.816 --> 02:33:41.526
but a thick, dark black knight of jagged dark
metal armor, what appears to be a longsword that

02:33:41.526 --> 02:33:52.630
emanates this dark energy, and floating above--

02:33:52.630 --> 02:34:01.897
TALIESIN: Oh, balls.

02:34:01.897 --> 02:34:03.956
LAURA: Oh no, what's flying?

02:34:03.956 --> 02:34:05.518
ASHLEY: Put it away.

02:34:05.518 --> 02:34:07.607
LAURA: No, I don't need it!

02:34:07.607 --> 02:34:10.131
LIAM: Those are my platforms, I can take them back
anytime I want!

02:34:10.131 --> 02:34:12.493
LAURA: Oh no! What is that?

02:34:12.493 --> 02:34:27.619
MATT: You see a man, though the flesh is pulled
tight against a skeletal frame. You see long, red

02:34:27.619 --> 02:34:34.112
and purple and black robes that are tattered and
drift below the breeze and cold gently blowing by.

02:34:34.112 --> 02:34:42.146
You see a field of crackling energy just bursting
around the outskirts of his form. You see one hand

02:34:42.146 --> 02:34:50.405
is out, in a welcoming position, while the empty
wrist that once contained a hand is now open on

02:34:50.405 --> 02:34:58.332
the other side. You see the bald, hairless head,
which is covered in spots and tugged open, bits of

02:34:58.332 --> 02:35:04.124
flesh that have curled away from rotten decay. You
see the cheeks sunken in where the skeletal teeth

02:35:04.124 --> 02:35:13.417
are now emblazoned in a terrible grin. You see the
right eye, and the gaping hole where a bright

02:35:13.417 --> 02:35:22.276
green, bursting, flaming vacuous void where an eye
once was now drifts off a trail behind it. You see

02:35:22.276 --> 02:35:33.925
there, reborn before you, the Whispered One, the
Undying King. Vecna himself.

02:35:33.925 --> 02:35:35.810
TRAVIS: Oh god, we're in it!

02:35:35.810 --> 02:35:37.328
TALIESIN: I don't like it being this close.

02:35:37.406 --> 02:35:38.676
SAM: We'll probably all die.

02:35:38.676 --> 02:35:40.206
MATT: I would like you all to roll initiative.

02:35:40.206 --> 02:35:42.220
(screaming)

02:35:42.220 --> 02:35:43.236
TRAVIS: No!

02:35:43.236 --> 02:35:47.485
SAM: Matthew Mercer, may I borrow your Monster
Manual so I know what I am?

02:35:47.485 --> 02:35:51.816
MATT: Marisha actually has a page for it, if you
want that.

02:35:51.816 --> 02:35:53.930
MARISHA: I do have a page. Do you want my beholder
page?

02:35:53.930 --> 02:35:55.176
SAM: Yeah!

02:35:55.176 --> 02:35:56.514
TALIESIN: That's terrible.

02:35:56.514 --> 02:35:58.034
MARISHA: That's terrible for me, too.

02:35:58.034 --> 02:35:59.441
LAURA: My teeth hurt.

02:35:59.441 --> 02:36:01.196
MATT: My teeth hurt?!

02:36:01.196 --> 02:36:08.988
TALIESIN: That's terrible. I'm not okay with that
roll.

02:36:08.988 --> 02:36:11.348
MARISHA: Oh, give me that back page. Sorry.

02:36:11.348 --> 02:36:12.739
TALIESIN: Back page.

02:36:12.739 --> 02:36:16.851
SAM: It doesn't say what his initiative is.

02:36:16.851 --> 02:36:25.040
TALIESIN: You have to roll. It's a dex modifier
plus a d20 if you don't have initiative?

02:36:25.040 --> 02:36:26.675
MATT: What's that?

02:36:26.675 --> 02:36:28.644
TALIESIN: Your initiative is normal.

02:36:28.644 --> 02:36:32.107
MATT: Your initiative is whatever the creature's
initiative is, which is its dex modifier.

02:36:32.107 --> 02:36:33.733
SAM: Okay. All right.

02:36:33.733 --> 02:36:35.105
TALIESIN: Plus a d20.

02:36:35.105 --> 02:36:36.168
SAM: 11.

02:36:36.168 --> 02:36:38.713
LIAM: When was the last time we went to bed?

02:36:38.713 --> 02:36:41.280
LAURA: I mean, it's a normal amount of time.

02:36:41.280 --> 02:36:44.541
LIAM: No, I mean, like, right before coming? I
can't remember the last time we had a full rest.

02:36:44.541 --> 02:36:53.196
MATT: A full rest would have been maybe four or
five hours ago.

02:36:53.196 --> 02:36:57.014
LIAM: Okay. I think I have all my Lucks. That's
why I'm asking.

02:36:57.014 --> 02:36:59.628
TALIESIN: I don't think you've burned since we've
come through.

02:36:59.628 --> 02:37:01.256
LIAM: Not 100% sure.

02:37:01.321 --> 02:37:03.092
MARISHA: I also gave you advantage on everything.

02:37:03.092 --> 02:37:04.622
LIAM: I know it! Girl!

02:37:04.622 --> 02:37:06.587
MARISHA: I think you didn't use anything.

02:37:06.587 --> 02:37:12.434
MATT: Initiative order. 25 to 20?

02:37:12.434 --> 02:37:16.022
TRAVIS: 20. Shit.

02:37:16.022 --> 02:37:18.323
MATT: Fuck, guys. Guys.

02:37:18.323 --> 02:37:21.022
TRAVIS: Me?! Okay.

02:37:21.022 --> 02:37:25.809
LAURA: I have no plan!

02:37:25.809 --> 02:37:28.868
ASHLEY: We're fully Leeroy Jenkins-ing.

02:37:28.868 --> 02:37:33.085
LAURA: Fully. Leeroy Jenkins!

02:37:33.085 --> 02:37:40.322
MATT: Grog, what's your dex?

02:37:40.322 --> 02:37:43.966
TRAVIS: My dexterity? 15.

02:37:43.966 --> 02:37:49.079
MATT: Okay. Technically, you rolled the same
initiative as the death knight,

02:37:49.079 --> 02:37:51.394
so he'll go right after you.

02:37:51.394 --> 02:37:59.913
TRAVIS: Okay. The death knight, by the way, is
what Colonel Arnold Fuck is.

02:37:59.913 --> 02:38:01.465
MATT: 20 to 15.

02:38:01.465 --> 02:38:02.517
LIAM: 16.

02:38:02.517 --> 02:38:03.752
LAURA: 18.

02:38:03.752 --> 02:38:05.117
ASHLEY: 17.

02:38:05.117 --> 02:38:06.541
LAURA: Ooh, nice!

02:38:06.541 --> 02:38:09.296
MATT: You had 18, 17.

02:38:09.296 --> 02:38:18.280
LIAM: 16. Sylas, broomstick-up-his-ass, death
knight Briarwood.

02:38:18.280 --> 02:38:21.057
SAM: 11.

02:38:21.057 --> 02:38:22.763
TALIESIN: 13.

02:38:22.763 --> 02:38:28.416
LAURA: This first round is definitely a surprise
attack on them, right?

02:38:28.416 --> 02:38:30.310
MATT: Oh yeah! Totally!

02:38:30.310 --> 02:38:31.406
MARISHA: Seven.

02:38:31.406 --> 02:38:33.760
TALIESIN: They did not see this shit coming. At
all.

02:38:33.760 --> 02:38:38.991
MATT: All righty. So.

02:38:38.991 --> 02:38:48.245
MARISHA: I had so much hope when we took down
their tower. It went away very quickly.

02:38:48.245 --> 02:38:51.400
TALIESIN: It did, but I think that probably made a
lot of cultists go away.

02:38:51.400 --> 02:38:54.228
LIAM: Guys, we've got to start the new campaign
sometime.

02:38:54.228 --> 02:38:58.629
MATT: Okay. Beginning of the round.

02:38:58.629 --> 02:39:03.207
MARISHA: We all die.

02:39:03.207 --> 02:39:10.535
TALIESIN: I cast Game Over. 20th-level spell.

02:39:10.535 --> 02:39:12.060
MATT: So many options.

02:39:12.060 --> 02:39:13.575
(groaning)

02:39:13.575 --> 02:39:15.115
TALIESIN: Fuck you.

02:39:15.115 --> 02:39:24.165
LIAM: We're going to die. Yep!

02:39:24.165 --> 02:39:27.874
TRAVIS: Obviously, we're not at the top of the
round.

02:39:27.874 --> 02:39:38.655
MATT: Okay, so. Vecna, as he stands there, seeing
the beholder arrive over the edge, seeing the

02:39:38.655 --> 02:39:42.862
paladin in the sky, seeing the rest of these
individuals cluster in, goes,

02:39:42.862 --> 02:39:49.398
"Very well. I wanted to talk more. Please, sit."

02:39:49.398 --> 02:40:11.581
I need Scanlan, Vax, Grog, Keyleth, and Vex 
to all make wisdom saving throws, please.

02:40:11.581 --> 02:40:12.922
TRAVIS: Fuck!

02:40:12.995 --> 02:40:15.022
MARISHA: Ugh, should have done that fucking
Feast!

02:40:15.022 --> 02:40:16.461
LAURA: We knew we were going to say it.

02:40:16.461 --> 02:40:19.704
SAM: Shit, I'm gonna lose my fucking
9th-level spell.

02:40:19.704 --> 02:40:21.725
ASHLEY: Not necessarily!

02:40:21.725 --> 02:40:23.854
MARISHA: 13.

02:40:23.854 --> 02:40:25.931
TRAVIS: Oh fuck, yeah. A natural 19.

02:40:25.931 --> 02:40:29.747
LAURA: I have a feeling I have to roll really high
against fucking Vecna!

02:40:29.747 --> 02:40:31.537
TALIESIN: Do you have a Luck?

02:40:31.537 --> 02:40:34.144
LAURA: Oh yeah, Tary had Luck, not Scanlan.

02:40:34.144 --> 02:40:39.084
SAM: Neither have Luck. I'm a beholder.

02:40:39.084 --> 02:40:40.839
TALIESIN: No, you have all of your other stuff.

02:40:40.839 --> 02:40:42.242
SAM: Are you sure about that?

02:40:42.242 --> 02:40:43.661
MARISHA: Is it like Shapechange?

02:40:43.661 --> 02:40:48.226
SAM: This is True Polymorph. I am this creature.

02:40:48.226 --> 02:40:50.507
MARISHA: Oh, it's True Polymorph.

02:40:50.507 --> 02:40:51.600
MATT: He is that creature.

02:40:51.600 --> 02:40:52.655
LIAM: That's hot.

02:40:52.655 --> 02:40:54.328
SAM: Except it's not, because I'm about to not be
anymore.

02:40:54.328 --> 02:40:56.066
LAURA: Because he's going to cancel it.

02:40:56.066 --> 02:40:57.251
MATT: So.

02:40:57.251 --> 02:40:58.816
SAM: 18.

02:40:58.816 --> 02:41:01.620
LIAM: God damn it.

02:41:01.620 --> 02:41:03.010
TRAVIS: Oh, Jesus.

02:41:03.010 --> 02:41:04.195
MARISHA: 27.

02:41:04.195 --> 02:41:05.998
MATT: You resist.

02:41:05.998 --> 02:41:07.314
LIAM: 18.

02:41:07.314 --> 02:41:09.548
LAURA: Oh god, you have to roll so high in order
to resist.

02:41:09.548 --> 02:41:12.143
SAM: Even with advantage? Oh, fuck.

02:41:12.143 --> 02:41:13.564
TRAVIS: 19.

02:41:13.564 --> 02:41:17.467
MARISHA: They roll disadvantage against you, too.

02:41:17.467 --> 02:41:21.291
TALIESIN: Oh, you didn't say me.

02:41:21.291 --> 02:41:25.013
LAURA: You skipped me. And I rolled a 20.

02:41:25.058 --> 02:41:27.904
MARISHA: You rolled a 20?

02:41:27.904 --> 02:41:36.207
MATT: You feel the force of his magical prowess
coalesce like a cold vise on your brain, and your

02:41:36.207 --> 02:41:49.228
body seizes, holding taut. And you're all held.
You fall straight down 80 feet.

02:41:49.228 --> 02:41:50.640
MARISHA: Oh, no.

02:41:50.640 --> 02:41:56.207
TRAVIS: (nervous laughter) Oh, fuck! Oh man!

02:41:56.207 --> 02:41:59.054
MARISHA: None of us can do anything to help him?

02:41:59.054 --> 02:42:03.019
LAURA: We slow-motion walked into our own death.

02:42:03.019 --> 02:42:05.083
TRAVIS: Oh, shit!

02:42:05.083 --> 02:42:06.350
SAM: Is Pike out?

02:42:06.350 --> 02:42:13.229
MATT: Take 32 points of bludgeoning damage, Vax.
And you are-- Oh god!

02:42:13.229 --> 02:42:15.142
LAURA: Walls brought down.

02:42:15.142 --> 02:42:17.659
MATT: Prone, there.

02:42:17.659 --> 02:42:19.105
MARISHA: Fucking shit.

02:42:19.105 --> 02:42:22.221
MATT: The rest of you are also held.

02:42:22.221 --> 02:42:25.244
TRAVIS: Is this charmed or frightened?

02:42:25.244 --> 02:42:27.391
MATT: No.

02:42:27.391 --> 02:42:28.886
TRAVIS: Okay, it's not.

02:42:28.886 --> 02:42:30.467
LAURA: What does being held mean?

02:42:30.467 --> 02:42:31.796
LIAM: It's paralysis.

02:42:31.796 --> 02:42:38.342
TALIESIN: Until we save, or until his
concentration is broken, I assume.

02:42:38.342 --> 02:42:39.282
MATT: Correct.

02:42:39.282 --> 02:42:40.784
TRAVIS: And rage would have no effect on this?

02:42:40.784 --> 02:42:41.727
MATT: Nope!

02:42:41.727 --> 02:42:43.245
TRAVIS: Fucking shit.

02:42:43.245 --> 02:42:54.179
MATT: And he's going to go ahead and shift up
about 20 more feet and kind of glance over the

02:42:54.179 --> 02:42:56.220
battlefield a bit.

02:42:56.220 --> 02:43:00.286
SAM: He's a god! He's a golden god!

02:43:00.286 --> 02:43:03.925
TRAVIS: He actually is one. And he won't jump off a
1000-foot cliff.

02:43:03.925 --> 02:43:07.683
MATT: (chuckles) Apparently. All right.

02:43:07.683 --> 02:43:11.703
LAURA: T minus ten minutes until he turns into a
goldfish.

02:43:11.703 --> 02:43:15.694
MARISHA: We can only be so hopeful.

02:43:15.694 --> 02:43:17.364
LAURA: That's plenty of time for us to die.

02:43:17.364 --> 02:43:19.616
MATT: That ends his turn. Delilah's now going to
go.

02:43:19.616 --> 02:43:21.105
TRAVIS and LAURA: Oh, good!

02:43:21.105 --> 02:43:23.140
TRAVIS: Wow, what a way to lead off the round!

02:43:23.140 --> 02:43:27.034
SAM: My anti-magic cone is not in effect, I
assume?

02:43:27.034 --> 02:43:31.357
TALIESIN: Actually, isn't it just naturally
wherever they're looking?

02:43:31.357 --> 02:43:34.981
MATT: It's wherever you're facing, but he hasn't
had a turn to go yet, he basically just arrived.

02:43:34.981 --> 02:43:36.762
TALIESIN: Oh, okay.

02:43:36.762 --> 02:43:45.433
MATT: So it would be kind of in this path here,
wherever you would have come in in this regard. So

02:43:45.433 --> 02:43:47.774
it would be this direction.

02:43:47.774 --> 02:43:49.945
LIAM: It's a big fuckin' headlamp.

02:43:49.945 --> 02:44:00.455
SAM: (laughs) Just frozen there. I really want to
swallow and I can't close--

02:44:00.455 --> 02:44:03.604
TALIESIN: I was under the impression that the
eyeball was passive.

02:44:03.604 --> 02:44:05.408
MATT: I'm checking right now, actually.

02:44:05.408 --> 02:44:09.426
SAM: Well, you have to choose. At the start of
each turn--

02:44:09.426 --> 02:44:12.277
MATT: At the start of its turn, which way the cone
faces and whether the cone is active.

02:44:12.277 --> 02:44:14.147
SAM: I haven't had a turn.

02:44:14.147 --> 02:44:15.923
MARISHA: And if it's active?

02:44:15.923 --> 02:44:20.198
TALIESIN: You're holding your action for being
able to move.

02:44:20.198 --> 02:44:21.720
MATT: Anyway.

02:44:21.720 --> 02:44:25.466
TRAVIS: Hey, so... (laughs)

02:44:25.513 --> 02:44:28.389
SAM: We got this, guys. How many of us are still
able to move?

02:44:28.389 --> 02:44:30.291
MATT: Three of you.

02:44:30.291 --> 02:44:31.730
SAM: Hey! Okay!

02:44:31.730 --> 02:44:35.920
TRAVIS: Looking up! Things are looking up. He has
12 hit points, by the way.

02:44:35.920 --> 02:44:37.664
MARISHA: Being held. What's the deal with that?

02:44:37.664 --> 02:44:41.936
MATT: You're paralyzed. Which means you are
incapacitated, you automatically fail strength and

02:44:41.936 --> 02:44:45.716
dexterity saving throws, attack rolls against you
have advantage, and any creature that hits you

02:44:45.716 --> 02:44:47.687
within five feet, it's a critical hit.

02:44:47.687 --> 02:44:51.572
TRAVIS: Basically worst scenario possible. That's
all you had to say: worst scenario possible.

02:44:51.572 --> 02:44:54.731
TALIESIN: It could be worse, but it would take
math. This is bad.

02:44:54.731 --> 02:44:58.878
SAM: Pike's going to solve everything.

02:44:58.878 --> 02:45:00.416
ASHLEY: Oh, yeah.

02:45:00.416 --> 02:45:01.801
SAM: Yeah, she can get us out of this.

02:45:01.801 --> 02:45:03.199
LIAM: Flipping those pages.

02:45:03.199 --> 02:45:11.542
TRAVIS: Remember this look, boys and girls. On
Matt's face. As the chef carefully

02:45:11.774 --> 02:45:14.006
picks the menu of our-- Yes.

02:45:14.006 --> 02:45:16.108
LAURA: Of our destruction? Of our doom?

02:45:16.108 --> 02:45:18.784
TALIESIN: He has been grooming us and fattening us
up for two years.

02:45:18.784 --> 02:45:20.988
MATT: Delilah is going to move.

02:45:20.988 --> 02:45:24.335
SAM: Oh no, lair action, she explodes.

02:45:24.335 --> 02:45:27.016
(laughter)

02:45:27.016 --> 02:45:35.029
MATT: And is going to step over Vax's body on the
ground.

02:45:35.029 --> 02:45:37.228
MARISHA: Oh, bitch! You better back off, bitch!

02:45:37.228 --> 02:45:39.890
LAURA: Hope you're wearing underwear, bitch,
because he just looked up your skirt!

02:45:39.890 --> 02:45:42.227
MATT: And looks at you.

02:45:42.227 --> 02:45:43.765
LAURA: (small voice) Me?

02:45:43.765 --> 02:45:45.512
MATT: It's been a while, my dear.

02:45:45.512 --> 02:45:48.881
(yelling)

02:45:48.881 --> 02:45:56.622
LAURA: No! Why would you do this?! How you do dis
Matt?!

02:45:56.622 --> 02:45:58.323
MATT: Yep, so make a constitution saving throw.

02:45:58.323 --> 02:45:59.743
LAURA: No!

02:45:59.743 --> 02:46:01.981
MATT: You're held, but you still make a
constitution roll.

02:46:01.981 --> 02:46:03.293
MARISHA: Come on...

02:46:03.293 --> 02:46:05.287
ASHLEY: Matt, how do you do this?!

02:46:05.287 --> 02:46:06.702
TRAVIS: Come on.

02:46:06.702 --> 02:46:08.051
MARISHA: Not again.

02:46:08.051 --> 02:46:09.190
LAURA: Natural 20!

02:46:09.190 --> 02:46:10.770
(cheering)

02:46:10.770 --> 02:46:12.261
MATT: No way!

02:46:12.261 --> 02:46:15.668
LIAM: And I said, biiiiitch.

02:46:15.668 --> 02:46:18.320
MATT: So you take half as much damage, which is
good.

02:46:18.320 --> 02:46:20.388
MARISHA: Oh my god.

02:46:20.388 --> 02:46:23.193
LAURA: Oh, I'm really glad we healed.

02:46:23.193 --> 02:46:30.169
LIAM: Vax on the ground just starts going
(unintelligible yells).

02:46:30.169 --> 02:46:32.729
MATT: All right, so instead of 61 points of
necrotic damage,

02:46:32.729 --> 02:46:34.390
you take 30 points of necrotic damage.

02:46:34.434 --> 02:46:35.996
LIAM: I'm shaking, guys.

02:46:35.996 --> 02:46:37.388
TALIESIN: Leroy!

02:46:37.388 --> 02:46:43.358
TRAVIS: Oh my god.

02:46:43.358 --> 02:46:46.043
LIAM: Got to squeeze my spiky dice to wake up.

02:46:46.043 --> 02:46:49.312
LAURA: Ow, ow.

02:46:49.312 --> 02:46:51.208
MATT: You okay?

02:46:51.208 --> 02:46:52.712
LAURA: (whimpering) I'm good.

02:46:52.712 --> 02:46:54.212
TRAVIS: Blood pressure's a thing right now.

02:46:54.212 --> 02:46:56.469
MATT: That'll end her turn. Grog.

02:46:56.469 --> 02:46:57.622
LIAM: Holy shit, Grog.

02:46:57.622 --> 02:46:59.872
MATT: Your turn happens at the same time the lair
action happens.

02:46:59.872 --> 02:47:01.828
TRAVIS: And the Death Knight, right?

02:47:01.828 --> 02:47:05.275
MATT: And the Death Knight. He's going to go
directly after you. You guys going on the same

02:47:05.275 --> 02:47:06.547
