MATT: (gunshot) It blasts, and you see the robe
tear open on one side.

03:02:11.331 --> 03:02:15.093
She's like (cries out, breathes heavily).

03:02:15.093 --> 03:02:18.079
TALIESIN: That's my roll.

03:02:18.079 --> 03:02:24.696
MATT: You glance over with the scope and see as
she turns and looks at you. You can see, what you

03:02:24.696 --> 03:02:31.395
didn't see earlier, is one normal eye she has and
one yellowish-green eye with a cat-slit pupil.

03:02:31.395 --> 03:02:33.336
TALIESIN: Shit.

03:02:33.336 --> 03:02:35.589
LAURA: What does that even mean?

03:02:35.589 --> 03:02:40.859
TALIESIN: Vecna's been busy. Okay. This is going
to get interesting.

03:02:40.859 --> 03:02:42.698
MATT: All right, that ends your turn, Percy.

03:02:42.698 --> 03:02:44.524
TALIESIN: That's all I can do.

03:02:44.524 --> 03:02:46.719
MATT: Scanlan, go ahead and make a wisdom saving
throw.

03:02:46.719 --> 03:02:47.641
SAM: Nope.

03:02:47.641 --> 03:02:49.105
MATT: Okay.

03:02:49.105 --> 03:02:53.433
SAM: I can't move my eyes or anything or turn on
my anti-magic?

03:02:53.433 --> 03:03:03.805
MATT: As far as the ray that you have, the eye
perspective, you're hitting right there, so you're

03:03:03.805 --> 03:03:16.751
just out of range to get rid of the paralysis from
Vex and off Vax. If you manage to break from this

03:03:16.751 --> 03:03:20.461
somehow and you rotate, the spell would have no
effect while it's on them.

03:03:20.461 --> 03:03:27.367
MARISHA: They're broken from it by being in his
gaze? Am I in his gaze?

03:03:27.367 --> 03:03:29.277
MATT: No, you are not.

03:03:29.277 --> 03:03:34.857
MARISHA: So I can still cast spells. But if I move
into his gaze, I cannot.

03:03:34.857 --> 03:03:38.697
MATT: Correct. Or if you shoot something through
the cone, it will dissipate.

03:03:38.697 --> 03:03:41.416
MARISHA: If I shoot up at Vecna, will it go
through the cone?

03:03:41.416 --> 03:03:44.848
MATT: Yeah, probably. You're just outside of it.

03:03:44.848 --> 03:03:46.760
MARISHA: I will not go through the cone?

03:03:46.760 --> 03:03:52.671
MATT: Probably. You can angle it that way, yeah.
Keyleth, what are you doing?

03:03:52.671 --> 03:03:54.301
MARISHA: It is now my turn.

03:03:54.301 --> 03:03:58.458
MATT: Also, I need you to make a concentration
check.

03:03:58.458 --> 03:04:01.299
SAM: Oh, my spell.

03:04:01.299 --> 03:04:02.834
MATT: Yeah, transformation.

03:04:02.834 --> 03:04:06.359
SAM: I get advantage as a gnome.

03:04:06.359 --> 03:04:11.857
MATT: You do. How much damage did you take on that
one, total, from the blast? From the blast that

03:04:11.857 --> 03:04:14.226
you took on that.

03:04:14.226 --> 03:04:15.411
SAM: 70 points.

03:04:15.411 --> 03:04:17.736
MATT: You have to beat a 35.

03:04:17.736 --> 03:04:20.585
SAM: Okay. As a wisdom?

03:04:20.585 --> 03:04:24.131
MATT: That would have been concentration.
Constitution saving throw.

03:04:24.131 --> 03:04:26.000
SAM: Constitution saving throw.

03:04:26.000 --> 03:04:33.254
MATT: In theory, Scanlan, before it came to your
turn, you dropped your beholder form.

03:04:33.254 --> 03:04:35.790
SAM: Oh! I'm no longer paralyzed.

03:04:35.790 --> 03:04:38.951
MATT: The spell maintains itself.

03:04:38.951 --> 03:04:41.260
SAM: No! But I'm a different guy!

03:04:41.260 --> 03:04:43.776
MATT: It's your mind it affects.

03:04:43.776 --> 03:04:45.601
MARISHA: Why?

03:04:45.601 --> 03:04:50.772
MATT: Any spell still carries over the effects on
you. You can't wild shape and--

03:04:50.772 --> 03:04:52.452
MARISHA: He lost concentration?

03:04:52.452 --> 03:04:54.529
MATT: He lost concentration on his big spell,
yeah.

03:04:54.529 --> 03:04:57.919
SAM: Hey, guys.

03:04:57.919 --> 03:04:59.515
LAURA: Hey, Scanlan!

03:04:59.515 --> 03:05:04.418
MATT: I'll let you remake that saving throw with
your constitution. Sorry, your wisdom. With

03:05:04.418 --> 03:05:05.984
Scanlan's wisdom.

03:05:05.984 --> 03:05:09.962
SAM: Okay, do I get advantage because of magic?

03:05:09.962 --> 03:05:13.846
MATT: Yes, because it is magic.

03:05:13.846 --> 03:05:17.065
SAM: And can I inspire myself?

03:05:17.065 --> 03:05:18.172
MATT: Yes, you can.

03:05:18.172 --> 03:05:25.273
SAM: All right. I will inspire myself. 24.

03:05:25.273 --> 03:05:26.702
MATT: 24 is just enough.

03:05:26.702 --> 03:05:30.982
(relieved laughter)

03:05:30.982 --> 03:05:34.613
MATT: You shrug off the paralysis at the end of
your turn. You're now free to move.

03:05:34.613 --> 03:05:37.906
SAM: Just move. I can't act, right?

03:05:37.906 --> 03:05:42.285
MATT: No, that's the end of your turn. Keyleth,
what are you doing?

03:05:42.285 --> 03:05:45.152
MARISHA: Is he 60 feet away from me? Is he within
range?

03:05:45.152 --> 03:05:47.028
MATT: Who?

03:05:47.028 --> 03:05:49.349
MARISHA: Should I handle Delilah, or should I
handle him?

03:05:49.349 --> 03:05:53.594
TRAVIS: What're you doing? Which one do you want?

03:05:53.594 --> 03:05:56.062
SAM: I can move now, or just in general?

03:05:56.062 --> 03:05:57.932
MATT: No, next turn you'll be able to move.

03:05:57.932 --> 03:06:00.711
MARISHA: Is he within 60 feet of me? Vecna.

03:06:00.711 --> 03:06:03.283
MATT: You're not sure. You'd have to eyeball it.

03:06:03.283 --> 03:06:13.558
MARISHA: (counting) He's exactly 60 feet in the
air. I have to get directly under his butthole.

03:06:13.558 --> 03:06:15.373
Can I get directly under his butthole?

03:06:15.373 --> 03:06:19.000
MATT: You can move through Trinket. You'll get two
attacks of opportunity from two skeletons.

03:06:19.000 --> 03:06:22.882
MARISHA: Jesus, balls.

03:06:22.882 --> 03:06:24.533
LIAM: Jesus balls.

03:06:24.533 --> 03:06:27.252
MATT: You'd have to leapfrog over Trinket to get
there, but you can do it.

03:06:27.252 --> 03:06:32.827
MARISHA: What about Delilah. Where is she?

03:06:32.827 --> 03:06:36.258
MATT: Delilah's over here. She and two skeletons
right now are lording over

03:06:36.258 --> 03:06:38.345
the paralyzed Vax on the ground.

03:06:38.345 --> 03:06:46.572
MARISHA: If I move at all, I'm going to take
opportunity from skeletons.

03:06:46.572 --> 03:06:50.145
MATT: Yep. They don't do a whole lot of damage,
but damage adds up.

03:06:50.145 --> 03:07:03.878
MARISHA: Jesus. Okay, I am going to head to
Delilah. I can move up to her, correct?

03:07:03.878 --> 03:07:06.628
MATT: You're going to move straight up to her?

03:07:06.628 --> 03:07:07.761
MARISHA: Can I?

03:07:07.761 --> 03:07:17.231
MATT: You can, yeah. Both skeletons get attacks of
opportunity on you. That's a nine and a 12. They

03:07:17.231 --> 03:07:24.383
both hit you, but the mantle writhes out in front
of you. You watch as various leaves unfurl almost

03:07:24.383 --> 03:07:27.606
like a cat's fur on the back of its neck, and it
deflects the blows

03:07:27.606 --> 03:07:29.832
from the skeletons as you rush past.

03:07:29.832 --> 03:07:39.860
MARISHA: I can give her disadvantage on
constitution checks, and whenever she takes

03:07:39.860 --> 03:07:42.451
damage, she's stunned, or should I do the
confusion thing?

03:07:42.451 --> 03:07:46.533
TALIESIN: Either one. They're both good. Go for
the first one. Pick one.

03:07:46.533 --> 03:07:52.750
MARISHA: I'm turning into Ashley Johnson. Okay.

03:07:52.750 --> 03:07:54.039
ASHLEY: Okay!

03:07:54.039 --> 03:08:12.656
MARISHA: I'm going to go up to Delilah. (pants)
Cotton mouth. Oh boy. Yeah. Okay, I'm going to go

03:08:12.656 --> 03:08:20.063
up to her and be like, experience what you've been
putting all of us through. And I'm going to touch

03:08:20.063 --> 03:08:25.385
her and I'm going to try and cast Contagion on her
with Mind Fire?

03:08:25.385 --> 03:08:28.017
MATT: Okay.

03:08:28.017 --> 03:08:29.671
LAURA: Mind Fire!

03:08:29.671 --> 03:08:33.143
LIAM: Sounds good.

03:08:33.143 --> 03:08:35.999
TALIESIN: Hit her with a mind bullet.

03:08:35.999 --> 03:08:38.500
TRAVIS: Mind bullets!

03:08:38.500 --> 03:08:40.971
TALIESIN and MARISHA: That's telekinesis, Kyle!

03:08:40.971 --> 03:08:44.187
TRAVIS, TALIESIN, and MARISHA: (singing) How about
the power to move you?

03:08:44.187 --> 03:08:46.781
MATT: Make a melee spell attack.

03:08:46.781 --> 03:08:50.370
MARISHA: I have a bonus to my spell attacks.

03:08:50.370 --> 03:08:55.503
LAURA: You've got this!

03:08:55.503 --> 03:09:08.398
MARISHA: It's cocked. That's even worse. Not
great. 18?

03:09:08.398 --> 03:09:12.065
MATT: 18 is exactly what you needed. That's her
armor class.

03:09:12.065 --> 03:09:15.499
LIAM: (singing) We'll fucking lead as two kings!

03:09:15.499 --> 03:09:19.665
TRAVIS: (laughing) Tenacious D for the rest
of this fight, please.

03:09:19.665 --> 03:09:22.211
MATT: She now is affected by Mind Fire.

03:09:22.211 --> 03:09:26.116
MARISHA: Her mind becomes feverish, and she has
disadvantage on intelligence checks and

03:09:26.116 --> 03:09:29.330
intelligence saving throws, and she becomes
confused.

03:09:29.330 --> 03:09:32.337
SAM: What does that mean? What does confused
mean?

03:09:32.337 --> 03:09:33.872
MARISHA: For seven days.

03:09:33.872 --> 03:09:36.002
LIAM: It sounds like she can't cast spells too
well.

03:09:36.002 --> 03:09:37.444
MARISHA: Hopefully.

03:09:37.444 --> 03:09:44.483
MATT: She's now considered confused. She's under
the effects of the Confusion spell

03:09:44.483 --> 03:09:46.072
for as long as it lasts.

03:09:46.072 --> 03:09:48.607
TALIESIN: That's me under the effects of being
confused about the Confusion spell.

03:09:48.607 --> 03:09:50.463
MATT: Does that end your turn, Keyleth?

03:09:50.463 --> 03:09:53.838
TALIESIN: What do you have for a bonus?

03:09:53.838 --> 03:10:01.111
MARISHA: I don't have a lot for a bonus. I can go
into an elemental form.

03:10:01.111 --> 03:10:05.476
TRAVIS: If we attack her, is that going to drop
the confusion?

03:10:05.476 --> 03:10:07.229
TALIESIN: Yeah, can we attack her?

03:10:07.229 --> 03:10:10.212
MARISHA: No, it just lasts for seven days.

03:10:10.212 --> 03:10:14.272
MATT: It lasts for seven days if she fails the
saves. She has three saves in a row, and if she

03:10:14.272 --> 03:10:17.167
succeeds, it goes away. If she fails, it lasts for
seven days.

03:10:17.167 --> 03:10:26.773
MARISHA: Okay. She has to make constitution saving
throws. But she's under the effects right now,

03:10:26.773 --> 03:10:31.337
correct? We've been through this before, haven't
we?

03:10:31.337 --> 03:10:35.157
LAURA: Oh, yeah. This is one of the ones we tried
a long time ago.

03:10:35.157 --> 03:10:41.437
MARISHA: It says after failing three of these
saving throws, the disease effects last for the

03:10:41.437 --> 03:10:45.924
duration, so that would make me assume that she
has it at least for three rounds.

03:10:45.924 --> 03:10:53.151
MATT: We had this discussion before, because in
the ability, it has Slimy Doom, which whenever it

03:10:53.151 --> 03:10:56.237
takes damage, it becomes stunned, which is the
most broken--

03:10:56.237 --> 03:10:58.007
MARISHA: I almost did that.

03:10:58.007 --> 03:11:01.517
MATT: I know, but I think the DND ruling,
technically, they have to

03:11:01.517 --> 03:11:03.314
fail three saves before it affects them.

03:11:03.314 --> 03:11:05.701
MARISHA: But it's a 5th-level fucking spell.
That's a lot!

03:11:05.701 --> 03:11:07.032
MATT: I know.

03:11:07.032 --> 03:11:11.110
MARISHA: That's lame. Three rounds for a 5th-level
spell?

03:11:11.110 --> 03:11:14.618
MATT: Look. I'll say this. I'll let Mind Fire work
on her for now.

03:11:14.618 --> 03:11:19.440
MARISHA: Oh, he doesn't look happy. I feel like I
just pissed off the DM.

03:11:19.440 --> 03:11:23.980
MATT: No, you didn't piss off the DM. This spell
has a lot of contention in the community, but the

03:11:23.980 --> 03:11:27.300
official DND ruling was it doesn't affect until
they fail all three rolls, but as it's written, it

03:11:27.300 --> 03:11:31.241
doesn't say that. It says they're afflicted on
being hit, so I'm letting it go through because

03:11:31.241 --> 03:11:33.860
you didn't choose the cheesy-ass stun-lock broken
spell.

03:11:33.860 --> 03:11:36.670
MARISHA: It does say that after succeeding on three of
these, the creature &lt;i&gt;recovers&lt;/i&gt; from the disease,

03:11:36.744 --> 03:11:39.753
so they were already affected.

03:11:39.753 --> 03:11:45.711
MATT: Which is what I'm saying. This is between
what's written in the spell and the arguments that

03:11:45.711 --> 03:11:49.559
people have made with DND on Twitter, and they
clarified that's not how it works. It's a

03:11:49.559 --> 03:11:54.269
mis-type. It wasn't clear. I'm letting it work. Be
happy with the book.

03:11:54.269 --> 03:11:59.675
LAURA: Stop making eye contact. Look down!

03:11:59.675 --> 03:12:06.414
MATT: At the end of your turn, Vecna's going to
use some legendary actions to cast a spell.

03:12:06.414 --> 03:12:08.462
(groaning)

03:12:08.462 --> 03:12:10.963
TRAVIS: How about you just say he did, and 
don't?

03:12:10.963 --> 03:12:13.312
ASHLEY: Yeah. Let's not and say we did.

03:12:13.312 --> 03:12:16.230
LIAM: He could just evil monologue a little bit,
tell us his plan?

03:12:16.230 --> 03:12:18.119
LAURA: He's really good at evil monologuing.

03:12:18.119 --> 03:12:19.904
TALIESIN: We were talking about how much you
wanted a monologue.

03:12:19.904 --> 03:12:21.723
I really feel like this is the moment.

03:12:21.723 --> 03:12:26.506
MATT: He's going to cast a 7th-level Fireball
right there.

03:12:26.506 --> 03:12:30.142
TRAVIS: 7th-level Fireball?

03:12:30.142 --> 03:12:32.283
TALIESIN: That's the end of Vax.

03:12:32.283 --> 03:12:34.788
TRAVIS: We've got to go.

03:12:34.788 --> 03:12:40.480
MATT: I need Keyleth, Vax-- you don't auto-save,
yeah.

03:12:40.480 --> 03:12:41.873
LIAM: Good night.

03:12:41.873 --> 03:12:47.630
TRAVIS: Maybe the Raven Queen will use you or
something.

03:12:47.630 --> 03:12:50.891
LIAM: I can't. It's an automatic fail because I'm
paralyzed.

03:12:50.891 --> 03:12:52.483
MATT: Yeah.

03:12:52.483 --> 03:13:00.685
SAM: That's actually good. He'll lose the
paralysis because he'll be in a coma. We'll just

03:13:00.685 --> 03:13:03.428
wake you back up and you'll be fine. It's actually
kind of good.

03:13:03.428 --> 03:13:06.416
MATT: Keyleth, I need you to make a dexterity
saving throw, please.

03:13:06.416 --> 03:13:09.292
The skeletons are obliterated.

03:13:09.292 --> 03:13:14.240
MARISHA: That's a natural one.

03:13:14.240 --> 03:13:18.164
TRAVIS: Are you serious?! Are you serious?

03:13:18.164 --> 03:13:19.895
TALIESIN: I'm looking at it.

03:13:19.895 --> 03:13:27.835
MATT: That's a surprisingly shitty roll. 38 points
of fire damage to Vax. 38.

03:13:27.835 --> 03:13:30.004
TRAVIS: On a 7th-level Fireball?

03:13:30.004 --> 03:13:31.539
MATT: I know. I rolled really shitty.

03:13:31.539 --> 03:13:32.935
MARISHA: 38?

03:13:32.935 --> 03:13:38.797
MATT: 38 to you, as well. 38 to Vex. And 38 to
Trinket.

03:13:38.797 --> 03:13:47.148
TALIESIN: That's a small-- that's a dire
armadillo. That's okay.

03:13:47.148 --> 03:13:53.614
LAURA: 38 to Trinket?

03:13:53.614 --> 03:13:55.839
TRAVIS: Did Delilah take all that damage, too?

03:13:55.839 --> 03:14:05.135
MATT: Delilah? Yeah, she did. She can't save
against his shit. She takes it and (grunts).

03:14:05.135 --> 03:14:08.085
LIAM: She probably kind of likes it.

03:14:08.085 --> 03:14:10.231
LAURA: She's like, ooh.

03:14:10.231 --> 03:14:12.241
TALIESIN: Burn. Sick burn.

03:14:12.241 --> 03:14:18.317
MATT: It made sense for the circumstance. She's up
for the sacrifice. All righty, that ends Keyleth's

03:14:18.317 --> 03:14:21.381
turn. Top of the round. Now it's Vecna's go.

03:14:21.381 --> 03:14:23.842
TRAVIS: I thought that &lt;i&gt;was&lt;/i&gt; Vecna's go.

03:14:23.842 --> 03:14:25.677
LAURA: That was his legendary.

03:14:25.677 --> 03:14:28.273
TRAVIS: Oh god.

03:14:28.273 --> 03:14:34.252
LAURA: I like that you have an enlarged figure
Grog. That's cool.

03:14:34.252 --> 03:14:37.077
TRAVIS: I thought you were complimenting the DM. I
was like, yeah, keep it up.

03:14:37.077 --> 03:14:39.652
LAURA: I like that you made an enlarged figure for
Grog.

03:14:39.652 --> 03:14:42.302
SAM: I'll kill you last.

03:14:42.302 --> 03:14:44.627
LAURA: Oh my god, this map is so pretty.

03:14:44.627 --> 03:14:49.121
(laughter)

03:14:49.121 --> 03:14:51.139
SAM: What is that thing in the middle of the
field?

03:14:51.139 --> 03:14:52.367
MATT: This is the altar.

03:14:52.367 --> 03:14:53.953
LAURA: Whatever it is, it's really cool.

03:14:53.953 --> 03:14:55.836
ASHLEY: Can we see what's in it?

03:14:55.836 --> 03:14:58.656
MATT: You'd have to go check it out, if there was
anything.

03:14:58.656 --> 03:15:00.463
MARISHA: Is he moving towards the altar?

03:15:00.463 --> 03:15:11.377
MATT: He's shifting in the center and looking down
for a bit. He goes, "Well, sleep."

03:15:11.377 --> 03:15:16.656
TALIESIN: Can he do that with concentration?

03:15:16.656 --> 03:15:20.405
MATT: This is not a concentration spell.

03:15:20.405 --> 03:15:25.665
LAURA: Magic can't put me to sleep.

03:15:25.665 --> 03:15:27.751
MATT: He casts Power Word Kill.

03:15:27.751 --> 03:15:29.586
SAM: Oh. Well, that's different.

03:15:29.586 --> 03:15:31.217
LIAM: Where did Sleep go?

03:15:31.217 --> 03:15:32.480
MATT: That's just what he said.

03:15:32.480 --> 03:15:34.891
SAM: He meant metaphorical. He meant death.

03:15:34.891 --> 03:15:37.458
MATT: You utter a word of power that can compel
one creature you see within range to die

03:15:37.458 --> 03:15:41.668
instantly. If the creature you chose has 100 hit
points or fewer, it dies.

03:15:41.668 --> 03:15:43.265
How many hit points do you have?

03:15:43.265 --> 03:15:45.608
LAURA: I'm dead. Insta-full death?

03:15:45.608 --> 03:15:47.242
MATT: Insta-full death.

03:15:47.242 --> 03:15:48.613
MARISHA: No saving from it?

03:15:48.613 --> 03:15:49.744
MATT: No.

03:15:49.744 --> 03:15:51.144
ASHLEY: Wait, what?

03:15:51.144 --> 03:15:52.251
TALIESIN: What?

03:15:52.251 --> 03:15:53.484
SAM: Perma-death?

03:15:53.484 --> 03:15:56.647
MATT: No death saving throws. You watch as the
life suddenly fades from Vex's eyes,

03:15:56.647 --> 03:15:58.468
and she falls to the ground.

03:15:58.468 --> 03:16:05.269
LIAM: Vax is watching, frozen.

03:16:05.269 --> 03:16:06.833
TRAVIS: Oh my god.

03:16:06.833 --> 03:16:11.328
LAURA: Hey, don't compliment the map, you guys.
Matt really doesn't like it.

03:16:11.328 --> 03:16:16.953
MATT: I'm sorry. It's now Delilah's turn.

03:16:16.953 --> 03:16:18.798
TALIESIN: This is not going well.

03:16:18.798 --> 03:16:20.214
SAM: Maybe we should leave.

03:16:20.214 --> 03:16:21.547
TRAVIS: Plane Shift?

03:16:21.547 --> 03:16:27.129
MATT: She turns and looks at you, Keyleth, and
goes--

03:16:27.129 --> 03:16:28.801
SAM: Is this Delilah?

03:16:28.801 --> 03:16:37.025
MATT: This is Delilah. "You took him from me. Now
I'm going to take him from you." She points down.

03:16:37.025 --> 03:16:39.222
SAM: I thought she was confused.

03:16:39.222 --> 03:16:42.535
MATT: I have to check what she does now. This may
make the change.

03:16:42.535 --> 03:16:48.264
LIAM: Well, we weren't technically dating when we
killed her, so I'm not really sure if she'd know.

03:16:48.264 --> 03:16:52.447
MATT: I get to roll a d10.

03:16:52.447 --> 03:16:55.557
MARISHA: Let's hope he doesn't roll a nine or a
ten, y'all.

03:16:55.557 --> 03:16:56.630
MATT: A ten.

03:16:56.630 --> 03:16:59.855
MARISHA: You are fucking lying to me! (groans)

03:16:59.855 --> 03:17:03.477
MATT: It's right there.

03:17:03.477 --> 03:17:06.473
TRAVIS: Yeah, I see it.

03:17:06.473 --> 03:17:09.110
TALIESIN: Oh shit. Wow, you really went down.

03:17:09.110 --> 03:17:15.097
MATT: I'm sorry. I'm rolling really well. I'm
sorry, guys.

03:17:15.241 --> 03:17:17.688
LIAM: Yeah, but that Fireball was super low.

03:17:17.688 --> 03:17:25.426
MATT: All right, so do I have to roll for an
attack on this? Creature has to make a dexterity

03:17:25.426 --> 03:17:33.506
saving throw. Hold on.

03:17:33.506 --> 03:17:37.845
TALIESIN: I don't know what to do.

03:17:37.845 --> 03:17:41.869
MATT: That's 76 points of damage from the
Disintegrate spell.

03:17:41.869 --> 03:17:45.261
LIAM: Halved from the Deathwalker's Ward. It's set
to necromantic.

03:17:45.261 --> 03:17:49.263
MATT: It's force damage. Disintegrate's force
damage.

03:17:49.263 --> 03:17:51.543
LIAM: Oh. Well, then I'm down.

03:17:51.543 --> 03:17:55.160
MARISHA: No, that means he's disintegrated.

03:17:55.160 --> 03:18:01.299
MATT: You watch as Vax's form (fluttering noise)
turns to dust.

03:18:01.299 --> 03:18:03.213
SAM: Wait, what?

03:18:03.213 --> 03:18:09.459
MATT: Leaving the armor of the Raven Queen empty
on the ground, the daggers (clattering).

03:18:09.459 --> 03:18:11.189
LAURA: No body left?

03:18:11.189 --> 03:18:12.960
MARISHA: There's no recovering from that, dude.

03:18:12.960 --> 03:18:15.061
LAURA: Bro. We're gone.

03:18:15.061 --> 03:18:16.871
TALIESIN: Wow.

03:18:16.871 --> 03:18:21.080
MATT: Grog, it's your turn.

03:18:21.080 --> 03:18:23.513
SAM: What's happening?

03:18:23.513 --> 03:18:28.819
LAURA: I thought this campaign was going to last
longer than this.

03:18:28.819 --> 03:18:32.949
LIAM: I said this was the last episode, and I
meant it.

03:18:32.949 --> 03:18:36.850
TALIESIN: You are a terrible person. Oh no.

03:18:36.850 --> 03:18:43.066
SAM: With Foresight? Oh, because you're paralyzed.
Oh fuck.

03:18:43.066 --> 03:18:45.825
MARISHA: She doesn't have to roll against that?

03:18:45.825 --> 03:18:49.812
MATT: It's a dexterity saving throw, but he's
still paralyzed.

03:18:49.812 --> 03:18:51.754
MARISHA: He doesn't get advantage?

03:18:51.754 --> 03:18:54.701
MATT: You automatically fail dex saving throws
when you're paralyzed.

03:18:54.701 --> 03:18:57.672
TALIESIN: You can't dex out of something if you
can't move.

03:18:57.672 --> 03:19:03.717
TRAVIS: If I throw you over to her, can you
Revivify?

03:19:03.717 --> 03:19:06.927
SAM: I'm too far to do anything, right?

03:19:06.927 --> 03:19:09.688
MATT: At the moment?

03:19:09.688 --> 03:19:13.536
SAM: It has to be within 60 feet.

03:19:13.536 --> 03:19:19.377
MATT: From Delilah? She's within 40 feet of you.

03:19:19.377 --> 03:19:23.474
SAM: Can I retroactively Counterspell? (laughs)

03:19:23.474 --> 03:19:31.482
MATT: Yeah. I'll let you do it. You have your
ability back, so I'll let you try for it.

03:19:31.482 --> 03:19:35.496
MARISHA: Wait, with the Disintegrate? Go, Scanlan,
go!

03:19:35.496 --> 03:19:39.199
TRAVIS: Do you have to roll for this?

03:19:39.199 --> 03:19:41.146
SAM: I think I have to roll for this.

03:19:41.146 --> 03:19:43.804
MATT: You roll and add your charisma modifier.

03:19:43.804 --> 03:19:57.395
SAM: No. Charisma modifier? It's just an 11.

03:19:57.395 --> 03:20:00.937
MATT: Plus two, because you get plus two bonus, so
13.

03:20:00.937 --> 03:20:04.230
SAM: I can't add anything else.

03:20:04.230 --> 03:20:06.466
LAURA, TALIESIN, and MARISHA: Can you inspire
yourself?

03:20:06.466 --> 03:20:09.337
SAM: Not on a reaction, I don't think.

03:20:09.337 --> 03:20:11.558
MARISHA: But you're a war bard, right?

03:20:11.558 --> 03:20:13.447
MATT: He's not a war bard. He's a lore bard.

03:20:13.447 --> 03:20:16.014
MARISHA: War caster.

03:20:16.014 --> 03:20:21.203
TALIESIN: Oh man, this does not feel good.

03:20:21.203 --> 03:20:23.418
SAM: Doesn't feel good.

03:20:23.418 --> 03:20:25.239
TALIESIN: It does not feel good.

03:20:25.239 --> 03:20:33.134
MATT: Peerless skill. When you make an ability
check. It's an ability check, technically.

03:20:33.134 --> 03:20:34.375
SAM: What's that mean?

03:20:34.375 --> 03:20:39.928
MATT: That means you can spend another bardic
inspiration to it because you're at a 13.

03:20:39.928 --> 03:20:49.457
SAM: (nervous laughter) It's cocked. It would have
been 11. Four.

03:20:49.457 --> 03:20:54.983
MATT: It's a 17? The spell is a 6th-level spell.
The DC is 16.

03:20:54.983 --> 03:20:56.537
TALIESIN: Oh god!

03:20:56.537 --> 03:20:58.179
LAURA: You're not disintegrated?

03:20:58.179 --> 03:21:00.041
TRAVIS: Are you serious?

03:21:00.041 --> 03:21:01.743
SAM: Matt is a gentle god.

03:21:01.743 --> 03:21:12.662
MATT: In this flash of vision, Keyleth, you see
this happen, and then the bit of inspiration from

03:21:12.662 --> 03:21:18.557
the Raven Queen that's been trying to push through
whatever is keeping her vision at bay here. Your

03:21:18.557 --> 03:21:23.279
vision flashes back, and then you see Vax on the
ground, the extended finger of Delilah as the

03:21:23.279 --> 03:21:27.238
green energy begins to spiral up from her finger,
and Scanlan in the back just says?

03:21:27.238 --> 03:21:38.080
SAM: Oh. Hey, you know what the problem is with
your face? I can see it!

03:21:38.080 --> 03:21:41.119
(laughter)

03:21:41.119 --> 03:21:47.646
MATT: Delilah goes, "What?" and the spell
(fluttering noise) dissipates. (sighs)

03:21:47.646 --> 03:21:52.197
MARISHA: That was a 6th-level spell?

03:21:52.197 --> 03:21:53.619
MATT: Yeah.

03:21:53.619 --> 03:21:55.120
MARISHA: Does she have any more of those?

03:21:55.120 --> 03:21:56.573
LAURA: We don't know.

03:21:56.573 --> 03:21:58.764
MARISHA: Because I only have two.

03:21:58.764 --> 03:22:12.889
MATT: That being the case, Delilah is going to go
ahead and go. You do get an attack of opportunity

03:22:12.889 --> 03:22:14.496
on her, Keyleth.

03:22:14.496 --> 03:22:16.108
MARISHA: Just straight melee?

03:22:16.108 --> 03:22:17.107
MATT: Straight melee.

03:22:17.107 --> 03:22:18.812
TALIESIN: Hit her with a stick.

03:22:18.812 --> 03:22:24.727
MARISHA: My dice suck.

03:22:24.727 --> 03:22:27.999
LAURA: You've rolled shit on that dice every
time tonight.

03:22:27.999 --> 03:22:35.316
MARISHA: It's not good. 13.

03:22:35.316 --> 03:22:38.837
MATT: 13? No, that misses, unfortunately.

03:22:38.837 --> 03:22:41.366
MARISHA: Fuck it.

03:22:41.366 --> 03:22:45.479
MATT: Okay. Grog, it's your turn now.

03:22:45.479 --> 03:22:53.504
TRAVIS: Sure. Can I use my-- are we doing this?

03:22:53.504 --> 03:22:54.765
ASHLEY: Yeah.

03:22:54.765 --> 03:23:01.195
TRAVIS: Can I use my action to pick up my buddy
Pike, and I'm going to try and throw her as far as

03:23:01.195 --> 03:23:04.833
I can towards where Vex's body is laying.

03:23:04.833 --> 03:23:07.128
MATT: Okay, so you're going to pick her up and
move?

03:23:07.128 --> 03:23:10.479
TRAVIS: There's no difference, right?

03:23:10.479 --> 03:23:13.548
MATT: You can pick her up and move and then throw
her to give her the most distance, but you can

03:23:13.548 --> 03:23:18.444
only move half your speed as you're carrying her.
It's essentially an agreed-upon grapple. You'd be

03:23:18.444 --> 03:23:20.292
able to move 25 feet with her.

03:23:20.292 --> 03:23:23.995
TRAVIS: Versus picking her up and throwing her for
an athletics check, or something?

03:23:23.995 --> 03:23:27.777
MATT: You can, but I don't know how far you'll
throw her that way. It's up to you. You can stay

03:23:27.777 --> 03:23:29.659
where you are, if you'd like to.

03:23:29.659 --> 03:23:32.841
ASHLEY: I'll make it.

03:23:32.841 --> 03:23:34.617
TRAVIS: You think so?

03:23:34.617 --> 03:23:38.191
ASHLEY: Yeah. I can make it to her.

03:23:38.191 --> 03:23:40.643
LIAM: The initiative is Grog, Pike, Vax right
now.

03:23:40.643 --> 03:23:43.320
TRAVIS: I should just go unload?

03:23:43.320 --> 03:23:45.140
ASHLEY: Yeah, do your thing.

03:23:45.140 --> 03:23:48.829
TRAVIS: I would like to rage.

03:23:48.829 --> 03:23:51.861
MATT: You are raging.

03:23:51.861 --> 03:23:55.919
TRAVIS: Can I use my full speed to head towards
Delilah?

03:23:55.919 --> 03:24:07.704
MATT: (counting) That's as far as you can get
right there.

03:24:07.704 --> 03:24:13.745
TRAVIS: With my bonus action, can I use my Boots
of Feral Leaping to leap horizontally 20 feet? I

03:24:13.745 --> 03:24:15.243
want to get within melee.

03:24:15.243 --> 03:24:18.098
MATT: Okay, make an athletics check.

03:24:18.098 --> 03:24:22.284
TRAVIS: That's a million. 25.

03:24:22.284 --> 03:24:26.675
MATT: (impact) You land right in front of her. She
watches you as you (footsteps) run around the

03:24:26.675 --> 03:24:30.915
side, leap, (impact) right in front of her, this
giant, hulking form of muscle.

03:24:30.915 --> 03:24:34.945
TRAVIS: Yeah. Reckless, great weapon master.

03:24:34.945 --> 03:24:38.275
TALIESIN: Turn her to fucking paste.

03:24:38.275 --> 03:24:39.583
MATT: You have two attacks.

03:24:39.583 --> 03:24:41.675
TRAVIS: Yeah, two attacks.

03:24:41.675 --> 03:24:44.572
MARISHA: Why am I light-headed?

03:24:44.572 --> 03:24:47.216
TRAVIS: Everything's going wrong.

03:24:47.216 --> 03:24:50.633
TALIESIN: Well, that, and those drinks were really
inappropriate.

03:24:50.633 --> 03:24:54.600
TRAVIS: 28?

03:24:54.600 --> 03:24:57.246
MATT: 28? Yeah, that hits.

03:24:57.246 --> 03:25:20.500
TRAVIS: 19. 29. 35, and four because I'm enlarged.
35, total on the first one. And the second one,

03:25:20.500 --> 03:25:30.649
19. Should have taken that other thing. That would
have been a crit. Minus five. 27?

03:25:30.649 --> 03:25:33.277
MATT: 27 does hit, yes.

03:25:33.277 --> 03:25:49.366
TRAVIS: Boy, she's got a high AC, doesn't she? 10,
24, 34, three points of necrotic for 37. That's a

03:25:49.366 --> 03:25:54.328
d8. That's the wrong one. 36 points of damage.

03:25:54.328 --> 03:26:00.596
MATT: As you rush forward and cleave into her with
hit after hit on the axe, you watch as her

03:26:00.596 --> 03:26:06.469
imposing form is battered around and slashed
apart, and as you finish and withdraw the axe from

03:26:06.469 --> 03:26:10.389
the two strikes, you see her already clutching her
stomach. (panting)

03:26:10.389 --> 03:26:15.309
TRAVIS: An action surge is a bonus action, right?

03:26:15.309 --> 03:26:16.846
MATT: No. Just an action surge.

03:26:16.846 --> 03:26:18.416
TALIESIN: You can just do it.

03:26:18.416 --> 03:26:20.113
TRAVIS: Should we empty the tank?

03:26:20.113 --> 03:26:21.046
LAURA: Yeah.

03:26:21.046 --> 03:26:22.518
TRAVIS: I'll use the action surge.

03:26:22.518 --> 03:26:24.093
MATT: Okay. Go for it.

03:26:24.093 --> 03:26:25.569
TALIESIN: Is that three more attacks?

03:26:25.569 --> 03:26:26.813
MATT: Two more.

03:26:26.813 --> 03:26:32.317
TRAVIS: Reckless, great weapon, all the shit.
Goddamn, that was two 19s in a row. If I'd picked

03:26:32.317 --> 03:26:36.234
that other thing, they would have been criticals.
28.

03:26:36.234 --> 03:26:38.167
MATT: 28 hits, definitely.

03:26:38.167 --> 03:26:53.708
TRAVIS: 17, 27, 29. That's a fucking d8 again.
31.

03:26:53.708 --> 03:26:55.629
MATT: 31?

03:26:55.629 --> 03:26:57.250
TRAVIS: 31 points of damage.

03:26:57.250 --> 03:27:00.511
MATT: All righty. Second attack?

03:27:00.511 --> 03:27:09.390
TRAVIS: 27.

03:27:09.390 --> 03:27:11.632
MATT: Jesus. Yes, that hits.

03:27:11.632 --> 03:27:26.661
TRAVIS: I'm a monstrous thing. That's a 12, 26,
36, 38, 40,

03:27:26.661 --> 03:27:29.303
including the enlarged and the necrotic.

03:27:29.303 --> 03:27:34.502
MATT: You slam her with the two extra attacks,
knocking her back. As the two additional axe blows

03:27:34.502 --> 03:27:38.237
slice across the front of her chest, one gets her
on the side of her chin. You can see, you've

03:27:38.237 --> 03:27:43.707
carved the cheek open and broken teeth, and now
when she looks back to you, you can see all of her

03:27:43.707 --> 03:27:48.786
back molars and teeth now, this horrible Joker
grin on one side of her face as the blood leaks

03:27:48.786 --> 03:27:57.516
out. You can see the one gleaming greenish-yellow
glowing eye flares open at you. She (spits).

03:27:57.516 --> 03:28:00.345
TRAVIS: Don't stop smiling on my account.

03:28:00.345 --> 03:28:17.212
MATT: That ends your turn, Grog... All right, so
ghostly claws begin to spring up from the ground

03:28:17.212 --> 03:28:18.690
in a 20-foot radius.

03:28:18.690 --> 03:28:21.767
TRAVIS: Did you say claws?

03:28:21.767 --> 03:28:22.912
MATT: Claws, yes.

03:28:22.912 --> 03:28:24.576
SAM: Ghostly claws.

03:28:24.576 --> 03:28:36.419
MATT: Right there. I need-- Vax fails. I need
Keyleth and Grog and Trinket to all make dexterity

03:28:36.419 --> 03:28:38.614
saving throws. Sorry, strength saving throws.

03:28:38.614 --> 03:28:41.363
LAURA: He can't do anything.

03:28:41.363 --> 03:28:43.010
MARISHA: Don't fuck me, Gil!

03:28:43.010 --> 03:28:44.381
TALIESIN: Trinket can.

03:28:44.381 --> 03:28:47.739
LAURA: Trinket can't still attack if I'm not
alive.

03:28:47.739 --> 03:28:52.566
MATT: I'll let you. I'll let you, in the purposes
of you being dead, Trinket is going to act on his

03:28:52.566 --> 03:28:54.950
own to defend you.

03:28:54.950 --> 03:28:56.856
LAURA: He rolled a seven.

03:28:56.856 --> 03:29:03.913
TALIESIN: He's about to be in a pocket dimension
really quick.

03:29:03.913 --> 03:29:06.753
LAURA: Yeah, he might go into the pocket
dimension.

03:29:06.753 --> 03:29:07.558
MATT: Grog?

03:29:07.558 --> 03:29:08.626
TRAVIS: 22.

03:29:08.626 --> 03:29:14.689
MATT: 22. You take five points of necrotic damage,
and are not grappled. You take ten points of

03:29:14.689 --> 03:29:20.888
necrotic damage, reduced to half, five, because of your
armor, and you are

03:29:20.888 --> 03:29:24.791
grappled and paralyzed. Keyleth?

03:29:24.791 --> 03:29:25.873
MARISHA: 22.

03:29:25.873 --> 03:29:27.907
MATT: 22. You take five points of necrotic
damage.

03:29:27.907 --> 03:29:32.086
LAURA: And Trinket takes how much necrotic
damage?

03:29:32.086 --> 03:29:46.822
MATT: Ten, and is grappled. Trinket's speed is
zero. All right. Welcome to the God Wars, guys.

03:29:46.822 --> 03:29:50.541
TALIESIN: Not cool.

03:29:50.541 --> 03:29:54.634
MARISHA: Why didn't we Heroes' Feast?

03:29:54.634 --> 03:29:56.577
LAURA: It wouldn't have mattered.

03:29:56.577 --> 03:30:01.392
LIAM: Let's get a god in here. Light or dark meat.
I don't care. One or the other. Get one of those

03:30:01.392 --> 03:30:02.979
ladies in here!

03:30:02.979 --> 03:30:13.338
MATT: (heavy footfalls) With these heavy, armored
footfalls as it walks, with its fingers forward,

03:30:13.338 --> 03:30:20.473
it begins carving this sigil in the air. Grabs it
and turns it, and as it turns, you watch the same

03:30:20.473 --> 03:30:25.590
sigil runes appear around Grog and begin to spiral
around you. Make a charisma saving throw, please.

03:30:25.590 --> 03:30:32.386
TRAVIS: Fuck, balls. Hey, y'all, plus one. Don't
worry. Four.

03:30:32.386 --> 03:30:36.713
MATT: Grog, you vanish.

03:30:36.713 --> 03:30:39.759
(groaning)

03:30:39.759 --> 03:30:42.564
MATT: Banished from this realm of existence.

03:30:42.564 --> 03:30:44.684
TRAVIS: No!

03:30:44.684 --> 03:30:53.616
MATT: You appear on the ground in the Shadowfell,
in the gaping crater where Thar Amphala once

03:30:53.616 --> 03:31:03.568
stood. You look around, up to the familiar cloudy,
dark sky, and are alone.

03:31:03.568 --> 03:31:06.221
TRAVIS: Wait. Y'all aren't in the Shadowfell
anymore?

03:31:06.221 --> 03:31:07.257
TALIESIN: No.

03:31:07.257 --> 03:31:08.743
TRAVIS: Oh, right. Snow's falling.

03:31:08.743 --> 03:31:11.767
LAURA: Wildemount, or some shit.

03:31:11.767 --> 03:31:14.938
TRAVIS: Without a perception check, is anybody
around, or is it just me?

03:31:14.938 --> 03:31:18.537
MATT: Nobody's around you, although you do look up
and see maybe a dozen or so of the gloom stalkers,

03:31:18.537 --> 03:31:21.522
swirling up ahead. They haven't noticed you yet.

03:31:21.522 --> 03:31:23.732
TALIESIN: God fucking damn it.

03:31:23.732 --> 03:31:27.488
SAM: You've been banished to another dimension.
You can punch your way out of it.

03:31:27.488 --> 03:31:30.483
TRAVIS: You know what? I only have one thought.

03:31:30.483 --> 03:31:35.938
MARISHA: Oh no. He's going to turn to the cards,
y'all. He's going to turn to those cards.

03:31:35.938 --> 03:31:37.651
TRAVIS: We've got this.

03:31:37.651 --> 03:31:39.735
MATT: Keyleth, perception check.

03:31:39.735 --> 03:31:40.783
MARISHA: What?

03:31:40.783 --> 03:31:42.074
MATT: Perception check.

03:31:42.074 --> 03:31:49.475
MARISHA: Ugh! Okay. That's good. 14 plus 13, so
27.

03:31:49.475 --> 03:31:54.582
MATT: You do notice, the armored death knight
still has a hand out after Grog's banishing.

03:31:54.582 --> 03:31:58.105
LAURA: Okay.

03:31:58.105 --> 03:32:00.023
TALIESIN: Okay, that's good!

03:32:00.023 --> 03:32:03.308
MATT: This doesn't appear to be Plane Shift.

03:32:03.308 --> 03:32:11.832
MARISHA: So if I kill him, he'll come back? Or if
I kill him, Grog won't ever come back?

03:32:11.832 --> 03:32:13.302
What does that mean?!

03:32:13.302 --> 03:32:18.865
TALIESIN: We'll find out. We'll just lay waste to
shit until it stops happening. We're going to keep

03:32:18.865 --> 03:32:22.999
doing terrible shit until terrible shit stops
happening.

03:32:22.999 --> 03:32:26.065
LIAM: Pickle time.

03:32:26.065 --> 03:32:32.512
TRAVIS: This is the worst grin you've ever given
us. It's so great.

03:32:32.512 --> 03:32:37.248
MATT: We are at the end of the death knight's
turn. Vecna's going to use two legendary actions

03:32:37.248 --> 03:32:39.430
to cast another spell.

03:32:39.430 --> 03:32:46.553
ASHLEY: This feels like when we played in Liam's
one-shot when we got on the beach.

03:32:46.553 --> 03:32:49.583
LIAM: I was just about to say, this is revenge for
Demogorgon!

03:32:49.583 --> 03:32:51.505
TALIESIN: This is very much the beach, isn't it?

03:32:51.505 --> 03:33:01.154
MATT: Vecna's going to shift further back on the
field to there.

03:33:01.154 --> 03:33:03.957
