03:48:59.161 --> 03:49:08.130
MARISHA: I'm going to do a bonus action and I'm
going to go air elemental. Full-on, wrath of my

03:49:08.130 --> 03:49:15.827
people and my hometown, and I'm going to levitate
in a cool tornado-y thing.

03:49:15.827 --> 03:49:25.572
MATT: Are there any material components for Fire
Storm? No, there is not. You can cast that in your

03:49:25.572 --> 03:49:33.365
form. You levitate up. We'll say right there.

03:49:33.365 --> 03:49:37.283
TALIESIN: There's a lot of dead bodies on the
ground, man.

03:49:37.283 --> 03:49:46.378
MATT: I know. This is rough, man. We'll say
there.

03:49:46.378 --> 03:49:49.470
MARISHA: That's high, but that's okay.

03:49:49.470 --> 03:49:51.094
MATT: How high did you want it?

03:49:51.094 --> 03:49:58.997
MARISHA: In between, but don't worry about it. I'm
going to right onto Vecna and try and swarm it down

03:49:58.997 --> 03:50:01.370
towards the death knight.

03:50:01.370 --> 03:50:02.999
MATT: How many cubes is it?

03:50:02.999 --> 03:50:04.652
MARISHA: Ten ten-foot cubes.

03:50:04.652 --> 03:50:19.032
MATT: That's ten, nine, eight, seven, six, five,
four, three, two, one.

03:50:19.032 --> 03:50:21.645
Just barely get him. Just barely.

03:50:21.645 --> 03:50:29.013
TALIESIN: That will do.

03:50:29.013 --> 03:50:31.811
MATT: Hold on.

03:50:31.811 --> 03:50:33.504
MARISHA: What do you mean, hold on?

03:50:33.504 --> 03:50:37.296
TRAVIS: There are some legendary things that I
think might be happening.

03:50:37.296 --> 03:50:38.534
TALIESIN: I get that vibe.

03:50:38.534 --> 03:50:43.991
MATT: Not legendary. As you swarm up and begin to
formulate the spell, Vecna looks at at you, and

03:50:43.991 --> 03:50:49.579
you can see with the vacant space where the hand
is, there's almost an arcane flash of a hand that

03:50:49.579 --> 03:50:52.368
goes, (clicks tongue). He's going to attempt to
Counterspell you.

03:50:52.368 --> 03:50:55.110
TALIESIN: Roll a one!

03:50:55.110 --> 03:50:59.917
MARISHA: What does he have to roll? Under my DC?

03:50:59.917 --> 03:51:08.334
MATT: It has to beat your DC. No, sorry. The level
of the spell, which would be 17. Which succeeds.

03:51:08.334 --> 03:51:16.932
He rolled a 14 plus ten, so 24. As you formulate
the spell, you watch as the flames sputter out.

03:51:16.932 --> 03:51:18.896
LAURA: Can you come back down to the ground?

03:51:18.896 --> 03:51:20.857
MARISHA: Yeah, I'll try and levitate down a bit.

03:51:20.857 --> 03:51:24.395
MATT: You were about there, and with your flying
speed, you can land back down on the ground if you

03:51:24.395 --> 03:51:32.110
want. Sorry. Is that your turn, Keyleth?

03:51:32.110 --> 03:51:34.777
MARISHA: I guess so.

03:51:34.777 --> 03:51:36.556
MATT: Okay.

03:51:36.556 --> 03:51:43.726
LAURA: What does it look like when you're looking
out at all of us and we're so sad?

03:51:43.726 --> 03:51:45.114
MATT: It feels awful.

03:51:45.114 --> 03:51:46.849
TRAVIS: I love it!

03:51:46.849 --> 03:51:48.825
TALIESIN: You're a liar. You're a lying liar.

03:51:48.825 --> 03:51:53.495
MATT: It legitimately feels awful, but we were
building to this for a long time.

03:51:53.495 --> 03:51:54.948
I've got to play it.

03:51:54.948 --> 03:51:56.116
TRAVIS: There's a god floating in the air.

03:51:56.116 --> 03:51:57.093
MATT: Not a god yet.

03:51:57.093 --> 03:51:58.141
TRAVIS: Not a god yet.

03:51:58.141 --> 03:51:59.499
MATT: That you know of.

03:51:59.499 --> 03:52:04.110
LAURA: He'll be a god in our next damn campaign
when we're all dead.

03:52:04.110 --> 03:52:09.973
MATT: He's going to use his last legendary action
at the end of Keyleth's turn to cast a cantrip at

03:52:09.973 --> 03:52:15.471
you, Vex, as you just got back to consciousness.
He's going to reach out with a Flame Bolt.

03:52:15.471 --> 03:52:19.927
LAURA: It's because I called him a dipshit when he
was talking earlier.

03:52:19.927 --> 03:52:21.540
TRAVIS: You did blurt that out.

03:52:21.540 --> 03:52:23.328
MATT: You did. You did taunt him.

03:52:23.328 --> 03:52:29.401
LAURA: He is a dipshit. Before he does his
cantrip, I'm going to go, you can go ahead and

03:52:29.401 --> 03:52:33.270
live forever, but you'll still be fucking ugly the
whole damn time!

03:52:33.270 --> 03:52:36.439
(laughter)

03:52:36.439 --> 03:52:44.792
MATT: Disadvantage because you're prone on the
ground and it's a ranged attack. That is a two

03:52:44.792 --> 03:52:46.760
plus 16. That is an 18.

03:52:46.760 --> 03:52:48.631
LAURA: To my armor class? He doesn't hit.

03:52:48.631 --> 03:52:53.291
MATT: I rolled a natural 20 and a two, by the way,
so if you weren't prone?

03:52:53.291 --> 03:52:55.363
TALIESIN: He would have--

03:52:55.363 --> 03:52:56.848
LAURA: Destroyed me.

03:52:56.848 --> 03:52:59.221
TRAVIS: You would be dust.

03:52:59.221 --> 03:53:07.791
MATT: As he points down with his still-missing
hand, releases this bolt and you see this flare up

03:53:07.791 --> 03:53:12.095
in the air and rush towards you, and you roll out
of the way and it (impact noise) slams into the

03:53:12.095 --> 03:53:15.837
stone below you. You hear it crack and break the
area where your head once was.

03:53:15.837 --> 03:53:19.193
Now it's Vecna's turn.

03:53:19.193 --> 03:53:21.729
TRAVIS: Now. (laughs) Now?

03:53:21.729 --> 03:53:25.926
ASHLEY: That wasn't his turn?

03:53:25.926 --> 03:53:27.796
MATT: That was a legendary action.

03:53:27.796 --> 03:53:32.722
ASHLEY: That was a legendary action? That's right.
I don't want any of it!

03:53:32.722 --> 03:53:34.714
TALIESIN: None of us want this.

03:53:34.714 --> 03:53:36.426
TRAVIS: I don't want it! I don't like it!

03:53:36.426 --> 03:53:38.874
ASHLEY: I don't even want to play.

03:53:38.874 --> 03:53:46.723
TRAVIS: Taryon's back in Whitestone having a
fucking ball.

03:53:46.723 --> 03:53:48.572
TALIESIN: Taryon's sitting with a cup of tea.

03:53:48.572 --> 03:53:52.837
SAM: No, Taryon's on the floor, weeping, holding
his necklace.

03:53:52.837 --> 03:53:56.894
ALL: Oh!

03:53:56.894 --> 03:54:00.273
ASHLEY: He doesn't know who it is.

03:54:00.273 --> 03:54:03.649
TALIESIN: We've got one way down. We are all
having the thumpa-thumpa right now.

03:54:03.649 --> 03:54:06.256
LAURA: It's red. All flashing red.

03:54:06.256 --> 03:54:07.723
MATT: Okay.

03:54:07.723 --> 03:54:10.701
ASHLEY: Why did you say okay that way?

03:54:10.701 --> 03:54:14.366
SAM: Liam can be Taryon now! (laughs)

03:54:14.366 --> 03:54:17.714
TALIESIN: You're terrible.

03:54:17.714 --> 03:54:24.984
SAM: No! It's an established character we already
have artwork for. Why let it go to waste? He's

03:54:24.984 --> 03:54:27.495
done prissy boys before.

03:54:27.495 --> 03:54:29.463
TRAVIS: Look at Matt's face.

03:54:29.463 --> 03:54:36.194
MATT: Vecna's going to lean down, seeing that you
just brought life back to Vex--

03:54:36.194 --> 03:54:37.930
TRAVIS: Don't you do it!

03:54:37.930 --> 03:54:42.314
LAURA: Matthew, don't do it!

03:54:42.314 --> 03:54:44.141
MATT: "Join your friend."

03:54:44.141 --> 03:54:45.832
ALL: No!

03:54:45.832 --> 03:54:47.966
SAM: I will 6th-level Counterspell.

03:54:47.966 --> 03:54:51.012
(cheering)

03:54:51.012 --> 03:54:53.841
TRAVIS: We will not go quietly into the night!

03:54:53.841 --> 03:55:00.893
SAM: I will sing at him, (singing) Counterspell,
baby don't hurt me.

03:55:00.893 --> 03:55:05.844
Don't hurt me no more. Counterspell!

03:55:05.844 --> 03:55:07.977
MATT: Okay. Roll a d20.

03:55:07.977 --> 03:55:11.572
MATT: It's a 7th-level Finger of Death.

03:55:11.723 --> 03:55:13.383
LAURA: Is that a natural 20?

03:55:13.383 --> 03:55:14.667
TALIESIN: No.

03:55:14.667 --> 03:55:17.754
MARISHA: Scanlan! No!

03:55:17.754 --> 03:55:21.716
TRAVIS: What is this up and down cardiac arrrest
game?

03:55:21.716 --> 03:55:23.357
MATT: Natural one?

03:55:23.357 --> 03:55:24.971
TALIESIN: Stop rolling that die.

03:55:24.971 --> 03:55:27.158
LAURA: And you're below 100?

03:55:27.158 --> 03:55:28.697
TRAVIS: It really is a one?

03:55:28.697 --> 03:55:30.080
TALIESIN: It really was a one.

03:55:30.080 --> 03:55:33.089
SAM: I can add things to it, right?

03:55:33.089 --> 03:55:34.172
TALIESIN: No, you can't.

03:55:34.172 --> 03:55:38.125
MATT: 7d8. I need you to make a constitution
saving throw.

03:55:38.125 --> 03:55:40.595
ASHLEY: I make a constitution saving throw? Okay.

03:55:40.595 --> 03:55:41.673
SAM: You're still inspired.

03:55:41.673 --> 03:55:43.026
LAURA: You're inspired!

03:55:43.026 --> 03:55:45.077
ASHLEY: "You're spired!"

03:55:45.077 --> 03:55:47.040
LAURA: Inspired. Use it!

03:55:47.040 --> 03:55:48.543
ASHLEY: Okay.

03:55:48.543 --> 03:55:53.235
TRAVIS: It's a d10, right?

03:55:53.235 --> 03:55:54.894
SAM: d12 on top of that.

03:55:54.894 --> 03:55:56.427
MATT: What did you roll?

03:55:56.427 --> 03:55:57.729
ASHLEY: 13.

03:55:57.729 --> 03:56:00.647
LIAM: Plus the inspiration.

03:56:00.647 --> 03:56:06.520
ASHLEY: No, just the 13. Plus-- 19?

03:56:06.520 --> 03:56:10.695
MATT: No. You take 67 points of necrotic damage.

03:56:10.695 --> 03:56:13.706
LAURA: It wasn't Power Word Kill, it was Finger of
Death?

03:56:13.706 --> 03:56:18.372
MATT: No, he'd already used his Power Word Kill.
Remember, he's not a god yet.

03:56:18.372 --> 03:56:21.011
ASHLEY: Okay.

03:56:21.011 --> 03:56:22.872
LAURA: Just the one. Just the one Power Word
Kill.

03:56:22.872 --> 03:56:25.197
TRAVIS: The fact that he's not a god gives me
diarrhea feelings.

03:56:25.197 --> 03:56:28.256
ASHLEY: Okay.

03:56:28.256 --> 03:56:36.990
MATT: All right, and he's going to move back a
bit, frustrated at the--

03:56:36.990 --> 03:56:41.369
SAM: At everything.

03:56:41.369 --> 03:56:48.629
MATT: At your attempts to Counterspell. Actually,
no. He laughed at that. "Nice try."

03:56:48.629 --> 03:56:51.303
SAM: It wasn't my best performance.

03:56:51.303 --> 03:56:56.796
MATT: All right, that's going to end his turn.
Delilah's out. Grog.

03:56:56.796 --> 03:56:59.791
TRAVIS: (laughs)

03:56:59.791 --> 03:57:05.377
MATT: Make a stealth check.

03:57:05.377 --> 03:57:08.590
TRAVIS: Cool. Right. Pass Without a Trace is still
going, right?

03:57:08.590 --> 03:57:09.735
MATT: Nope.

03:57:09.735 --> 03:57:12.568
TRAVIS: That's a one.

03:57:12.568 --> 03:57:15.808
TALIESIN: Hello?

03:57:15.808 --> 03:57:29.393
MATT: As you're there, Grog, you hear
(screeching). A cloud of screeches, as about nine

03:57:29.393 --> 03:57:35.116
of these gloom stalkers all start (whoosh) going
into a dive towards you.

03:57:35.116 --> 03:57:37.486
SAM: Maybe one of them is our friend Mr.
Mistoffelees.

03:57:37.486 --> 03:57:39.777
MARISHA: Mr. Mistoffelees, come back!

03:57:39.777 --> 03:57:44.772
TRAVIS: Am I going to do anything? How far away is
the nearest structure?

03:57:44.772 --> 03:57:52.432
MATT: Nothing. It's a crater. You're where the
city used to be. You have at least a mile to each

03:57:52.432 --> 03:57:54.216
side of nothing but crater.

03:57:54.216 --> 03:57:55.600
TALIESIN: Fuck!

03:57:55.600 --> 03:57:59.119
ASHLEY: He's all by his lonesome!

03:57:59.119 --> 03:58:01.559
TALIESIN: One more round.

03:58:01.559 --> 03:58:05.948
SAM: He doesn't know.

03:58:05.948 --> 03:58:07.769
MARISHA: He could be stuck there forever!

03:58:07.769 --> 03:58:10.295
TALIESIN: There's nothing we can do right now.

03:58:10.295 --> 03:58:21.672
TRAVIS: I'm going to go into a frenzied rage, and
I'm going to use my second wind to heal 1d10 plus

03:58:21.672 --> 03:58:31.129
my fighter level. Three, six. Six points, yay.

03:58:31.129 --> 03:58:34.156
TALIESIN: How close to you do we have to be?

03:58:34.156 --> 03:58:35.801
MARISHA: We have to be touching.

03:58:35.801 --> 03:58:38.527
SAM: And you have to not be wind.

03:58:38.527 --> 03:58:40.877
MARISHA: I can be wind now.

03:58:40.877 --> 03:58:43.413
TRAVIS: I don't have any fighter things, so that's
my turn.

03:58:43.413 --> 03:58:59.777
MATT: That's your turn. Okay. Ending your turn.
Dark energy suffuses the landscape in the area.

03:58:59.777 --> 03:59:05.478
Actually, no. I'm not going to use that one
because nobody has necrotic resistance right now.

03:59:05.478 --> 03:59:10.021
More undead are going to pop up. Let's see how
many. That's actually a shitty roll.

03:59:10.021 --> 03:59:14.558
Four undead pop up.

03:59:14.558 --> 03:59:23.449
TALIESIN: They're bullshit. We don't care.

03:59:23.449 --> 03:59:33.856
MATT: All righty. That's going to be an attack on
you. It has advantage because you're prone and

03:59:33.856 --> 03:59:39.655
it's in melee. That's a 17. Still doesn't hit.
High armor. You're ducking out of the way. The

03:59:39.655 --> 03:59:46.842
skeleton is (tink) hitting the ground. It's also
attacking at you, Pike. That's cocked. Natural

03:59:46.842 --> 03:59:52.999
one. It goes to strike you, and it doesn't even
hit you. The holy symbol of Sarenrae flares, and

03:59:52.999 --> 03:59:59.486
it (raspy cry) pulls away from the blast of
vibrant, radiant energy. There's going to be one

03:59:59.486 --> 04:00:03.280
attacking you, Scanlan. That is a 20 to hit?

04:00:03.280 --> 04:00:04.452
SAM: Oh yeah.

04:00:04.452 --> 04:00:11.705
MATT: All right. You take eight points of slashing
damage. And attacking you,

04:00:11.705 --> 04:00:13.668
Percival, that's another 20.

04:00:13.668 --> 04:00:15.000
TALIESIN: That is my armor class.

04:00:15.000 --> 04:00:20.941
MATT: It hits you. You take 11 points of slashing
damage as it cuts through you.

04:00:20.941 --> 04:00:29.807
TALIESIN: I don't even acknowledge its existence.
I am definitely not amused.

04:00:29.807 --> 04:00:36.533
MARISHA: What was the name of that one city, you
guys?

04:00:36.533 --> 04:00:38.636
TALIESIN: Where is your dad from?

04:00:38.636 --> 04:00:41.402
MARISHA: Syngorn. Is Syngorn still in the
Feywild?

04:00:41.402 --> 04:00:42.771
LAURA: No.

04:00:42.771 --> 04:00:44.287
TALIESIN: Damn it.

04:00:44.287 --> 04:00:47.740
MARISHA: Where did we go? What city in the Feywild
did we go to?

04:00:47.740 --> 04:00:50.641
LAURA: We can go to the pond.

04:00:50.641 --> 04:00:52.283
TRAVIS: The death knight.

04:00:52.283 --> 04:00:59.096
MATT: Steps forward, seeing Scanlan attempt to
shrug off all these spells, comes rushing forward,

04:00:59.096 --> 04:01:06.703
and you watch as its blade begins to empower this
dark, black shadow, similar to the gloom stalkers

04:01:06.703 --> 04:01:11.929
you've seen before. As he brings the sword and
arcs it down with tremendous might, you hear the

04:01:11.929 --> 04:01:18.226
crack of thunder as this Staggering Smite slams
into you, or tries to, at least.

04:01:18.226 --> 04:01:19.862
SAM: That sounds bad.

04:01:19.862 --> 04:01:22.789
TALIESIN: That's bad. Do you have a reaction?

04:01:22.789 --> 04:01:24.478
SAM: I used it already.

04:01:24.478 --> 04:01:25.755
MATT: Shitty roll. 16 to hit?

04:01:25.755 --> 04:01:27.089
SAM: Oh yeah, that hits.

04:01:27.089 --> 04:01:28.147
MATT: Okay.

04:01:28.147 --> 04:01:31.864
SAM: I think I'm not attuned-- yeah.

04:01:31.864 --> 04:01:46.827
MATT: You take ten points of slashing damage, plus
17 points of necrotic damage.

04:01:46.827 --> 04:01:49.813
TALIESIN: 27.

04:01:49.813 --> 04:02:02.543
MATT: And as part of the Staggering Smite, you
also take 14 points of psychic damage, and make a

04:02:02.543 --> 04:02:04.084
wisdom saving throw.

04:02:04.084 --> 04:02:11.246
SAM: Against magic? That's better. 17.

04:02:11.246 --> 04:02:19.504
MATT: 17? His spell DC is 18, unfortunately. On a
failed save, you have a disadvantage on attack

04:02:19.504 --> 04:02:23.759
rolls and ability checks, and you can't take
reactions until the end of your next turn, so you

04:02:23.759 --> 04:02:25.135
can't Counterspell.

04:02:25.135 --> 04:02:26.859
TALIESIN: Scanlan's getting whaled on.

04:02:26.859 --> 04:02:30.223
SAM: Disadvantage on all attack rolls?

04:02:30.223 --> 04:02:34.077
MATT: Oh, but that's a concentration spell, so
he's not going to maintain the concentration. You

04:02:34.077 --> 04:02:38.915
take the damage, and he lets it go. You don't have
a disadvantage. Otherwise, he would lose other

04:02:38.915 --> 04:02:40.215
bits of concentration.

04:02:40.215 --> 04:02:42.160
LAURA: Other bits of concentration.

04:02:42.160 --> 04:02:48.314
MATT: All right, so that brings us to Vex. Your
turn.

04:02:48.314 --> 04:02:50.574
LAURA: (laughing) I get to go?

04:02:50.574 --> 04:02:52.426
MATT: Yeah. Sorry!

04:02:52.426 --> 04:02:53.812
SAM: You're alive.

04:02:53.812 --> 04:02:58.066
MATT: Sorry, guys. You walked into the lion's
den.

04:02:58.066 --> 04:02:59.881
LAURA: Oh yeah, we did.

04:02:59.881 --> 04:03:01.714
LIAM: I never did a single thing in this fight.

04:03:01.714 --> 04:03:07.581
LAURA: I know. This is the first thing I've done.
I stand up.

04:03:07.581 --> 04:03:12.094
TALIESIN: If we're smart--

04:03:12.094 --> 04:03:13.740
MARISHA: I can bring you back.

04:03:13.740 --> 04:03:19.223
TALIESIN: I'm heading towards where you are. I'm
heading towards the deceased body of Delilah.

04:03:19.223 --> 04:03:33.013
LAURA: I'm going to, as a bonus action, down my
biggest healing potion, which is one greater

04:03:33.013 --> 04:03:34.648
healing potion.

04:03:34.648 --> 04:03:36.059
MATT: Go for it.

04:03:36.059 --> 04:03:41.241
LIAM: There's also a superior healing potion lying
on the ground amongst all my shit.

04:03:41.241 --> 04:03:43.897
LAURA: No. It's in your armor.

04:03:43.897 --> 04:03:47.375
MATT: Greater is 4d4 plus four.

04:03:47.375 --> 04:03:49.351
SAM: Okay, it's something.

04:03:49.351 --> 04:04:10.557
LAURA: 13 plus four is 17 healing points, and I'm
going to move closer to Keyleth.

04:04:10.557 --> 04:04:15.480
TALIESIN: She can move to us. Never mind.

04:04:15.480 --> 04:04:18.639
MARISHA: We have to all be holding hands, y'all.

04:04:18.639 --> 04:04:24.057
LAURA: Can I put myself in between Percy and
Keyleth so I can reach my hand out?

04:04:24.057 --> 04:04:28.574
TALIESIN: I'm going to be making a beeline for
everybody else. Everybody's in that big clump.

04:04:28.574 --> 04:04:32.009
LAURA: We're all in a clump, so we can still
touch? I don't need to move anywhere in order to

04:04:32.009 --> 04:04:34.575
be able to touch her?

04:04:34.575 --> 04:04:36.986
TALIESIN: You'll be able to move before you cast
Plane Shift, right?

04:04:36.986 --> 04:04:37.842
MARISHA: Yes.

04:04:37.842 --> 04:04:44.158
TALIESIN: So as long as we're all touching, she
can get to us. We just need to clump, and I move

04:04:44.158 --> 04:04:48.009
last, so I'm fine. Is that right? Yeah, I move
last.

04:04:48.009 --> 04:04:53.065
MATT: Keyleth moves last. Keyleth and Scanlan.

04:04:53.065 --> 04:04:59.360
