04:20:32.649 --> 04:20:35.083
TRAVIS: I knew that's what you were waiting for!

04:20:35.083 --> 04:20:41.623
MATT: That was some old-school Magic: The
Gathering shit, right there.

04:20:41.623 --> 04:20:45.143
LIAM: Do it, Scanlan. Do it.

04:20:45.143 --> 04:20:47.134
ASHLEY: You just pulled out the wild Uno card.

04:20:47.134 --> 04:20:50.184
(laughter)

04:20:50.184 --> 04:20:51.687
TALIESIN: We're not happy yet.

04:20:51.687 --> 04:21:02.229
MATT: So 7th-level Counterspell. Yeah, you don't
have to roll.

04:21:02.229 --> 04:21:04.312
(cheering)

04:21:04.312 --> 04:21:12.879
MATT: Yeah. Let me check real fast. I need to
confirm this real fast.

04:21:12.879 --> 04:21:15.568
LAURA: Scanlan's back.

04:21:15.568 --> 04:21:17.087
LIAM: Shorthalt's back.

04:21:17.087 --> 04:21:20.274
TRAVIS: "I'd rather not use it."

04:21:20.274 --> 04:21:28.385
MATT: Yeah, no. The only spell he even had left to
Counterspell was 7th level. Yeah, (poof).

04:21:28.385 --> 04:21:30.402
SAM: Let's go.

04:21:30.402 --> 04:21:38.414
MATT: As the glyph of shattering begins to
coalesce around his fingers in one hand and the

04:21:38.414 --> 04:21:42.502
wrist on the other, you strike up a Counterspell
of your own.

04:21:42.502 --> 04:21:51.453
SAM: Sure. I will say to him, this time-- I've got
nothing left. I will sing to him, (singing) I'm

04:21:51.453 --> 04:22:08.209
beautiful. I'm beautiful, it's true. You saw my
face in a crowded place, and you didn't know what

04:22:08.209 --> 04:22:12.114
to do because I just took a shit on you.

04:22:12.114 --> 04:22:14.869
ASHLEY: Oh my god.

04:22:14.869 --> 04:22:23.014
MATT: The last thing you hear as the spell begins
to take effect is the whispered voice of Vecna

04:22:23.014 --> 04:22:27.824
throughout all of your heads say, "What?"

04:22:27.824 --> 04:22:30.001
(laughter)

04:22:30.001 --> 04:22:37.218
MATT: Before (spell noise) you are all yanked
through a familiar tunnel of darkness and then

04:22:37.218 --> 04:22:46.262
thrust out into the center of a clustered, dense
forest in the Feywild.

04:22:46.262 --> 04:22:49.437
SAM: Oh god. Have I been there? Wait, was that me?
Yes. Okay.

04:22:49.437 --> 04:22:57.081
MARISHA: I'm sorry. I would have taken us home,
but we were already there, and I had to go

04:22:57.081 --> 04:22:59.038
somewhere else.

04:22:59.038 --> 04:23:00.455
LAURA: Where's Vax?

04:23:00.455 --> 04:23:01.991
MATT: And that's where we're going to end.

04:23:01.991 --> 04:23:04.275
(groaning)

04:23:04.275 --> 04:23:13.281
LIAM: (fake crying) You sadistic motherfucker! You
cut it right there?! I was okay until right then!

04:23:13.281 --> 04:23:16.279
TALIESIN: That's not nice.

04:23:16.279 --> 04:23:19.836
MATT: I'm so sorry.

04:23:19.836 --> 04:23:23.793
TALIESIN: Nothing feels good.

04:23:23.793 --> 04:23:26.705
LIAM: I was okay until right then!

04:23:26.705 --> 04:23:31.806
ASHLEY: Let's do one more hour.

04:23:31.806 --> 04:23:40.655
TRAVIS: That was amazing. That was brutal. We
didn't have a fucking chance.

04:23:40.655 --> 04:23:42.849
TALIESIN: No, there was not a fucking prayer.

04:23:42.849 --> 04:23:49.795
LIAM: What else were we going to do? Set up an
Orange Julius stand by that tower? Of course we

04:23:49.795 --> 04:23:51.526
were going to go into that tower.

04:23:51.526 --> 04:23:55.365
TRAVIS: Of course! But we didn't know how fucked
we were until we got up there. We had to go.

04:23:55.365 --> 04:23:59.115
MARISHA: I thought that we were pretty badass when
we took the tower down, and we were not.

04:23:59.115 --> 04:24:01.503
ASHLEY: No.

04:24:01.503 --> 04:24:06.661
MARISHA: I can get you back, man. I can get you
fucking back!

04:24:06.661 --> 04:24:08.487
SAM: Can you? Without a body?

04:24:08.487 --> 04:24:11.309
MATT: We're going to have some discussions.

04:24:11.309 --> 04:24:13.368
SAM: Without a body?

04:24:13.368 --> 04:24:16.834
MARISHA: But True Resurrection says I can.

04:24:16.834 --> 04:24:26.470
MATT: Marisha. We'll have some discussions.
Anyway. Thank you guys so much for watching.

04:24:26.470 --> 04:24:35.284
Thanks for kicking in for a taste of the final
arc. Holy shit.

04:24:35.284 --> 04:24:38.865
TALIESIN: You know what, I'm grateful that we're
not--

04:24:38.865 --> 04:24:47.884
MATT: Oh man. There was part of me, where either
they were going to end up waiting-- if that didn't

04:24:47.884 --> 04:24:52.370
break concentration, they were either going to
wait for you and probably lose a lot more,

04:24:52.370 --> 04:24:57.727
possibly Keyleth once she realized what was going
on. Or left without you.

04:24:57.727 --> 04:24:59.404
You would have come back.

04:24:59.404 --> 04:25:01.510
LAURA: And we would have been gone.

04:25:01.510 --> 04:25:05.798
TRAVIS: And I would have to have won the game all by
myself.

04:25:05.798 --> 04:25:07.849
SAM: Which you've already done.

04:25:07.849 --> 04:25:12.767
TRAVIS: Or I would have taken the Deck and been
like--

04:25:12.767 --> 04:25:22.750
LIAM: Number one lesson. The one takeaway tonight.
The one takeaway is just how OP Vax'ildan is.

04:25:22.750 --> 04:25:26.044
(laughter)

04:25:26.044 --> 04:25:27.325
MATT: This is true.

04:25:27.325 --> 04:25:28.862
LAURA: If he can't move, he's fucked.

04:25:28.862 --> 04:25:30.278
TRAVIS: Boots no longer.

04:25:30.278 --> 04:25:33.181
MARISHA: I can't believe I fucking dumped my
9th-level spell in you, and then you got tied

04:25:33.181 --> 04:25:35.489
down. It made zero fucking difference.

04:25:35.489 --> 04:25:37.709
LIAM: You did great.

04:25:37.709 --> 04:25:39.722
MARISHA: We both wasted our fucking 9th-level
spells.

04:25:39.722 --> 04:25:42.183
SAM: They're hard to use. We've got to learn to
use them better.

04:25:42.183 --> 04:25:45.307
LIAM: You've got one chance to do something
fucking amazing.

04:25:45.307 --> 04:25:49.352
LAURA: Vecna is out and ready to fucking destroy.

04:25:49.352 --> 04:25:52.426
MATT: We'll pick up on this next week.

04:25:52.426 --> 04:25:54.820
SAM: Wow. I'm shaking.

04:25:54.820 --> 04:26:01.548
MATT: Me, too. All right, guys. Thank you so much.
Have a wonderful night. We'll see you soon, and is

04:26:01.548 --> 04:26:02.953
it Thursday yet?

04:26:02.953 --> 04:26:04.681
TRAVIS: Nope! It's Thursday right now!

04:26:04.681 --> 04:26:06.134
LIAM: Last Thursday.

04:26:06.134 --> 04:26:07.233
MATT: Good night, guys.

04:26:07.233 --> 04:32:19.641
[music]

